title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In large pan, boil whole chicken until it falls apart.
Debone, cut into small pieces.
Set aside.
(Do not pour out chicken broth.)
Use broth to boil pkg. spaghetti.
Boil until tender.
In small skillet, combine chopped onions, chopped celery, and chopped mushrooms in 2-3 Tbsp of margarine.
Saute until onions are slightly brown and mushrooms are cooked.
After spaghetti is fully cooked, add soups and mix well.
Add the skillet mixture.
Season to taste.
If necessary, add extra water until a medium consistency.
Let it set for 30 - 60 minutes before serving.
Serve with green salad, and garlic bread.

title: vanilla bread pudding(with cinnamon-sugar topping)
directions: In small saucepan, heat milk until very hot but not boiling. In bowl, whisk eggs and granulated sugar to mix.
Whisk in hot milk; add 1/2 tsp. cinnamon and the vanilla.

title: barbecued cocktail franks
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients except franks. Bring to a boil, stirring frequently; reduce heat.
Add franks; simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Add the water to the raisins; bring to boil for 3 minutes. Let cool.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add the eggs; beat well.
Add the vanilla and cooled raisins with juice.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon; add to creamed mixture and blend.
Add the chopped nuts. Drop by spoons onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: sugarless applesauce cake
directions: Combine raisins, fruit and water in a saucepan; cook, uncovered, until water in saucepan has evaporated and fruit is soft.
Set aside to cool.
Meanwhile, in a large mixing bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
In another bowl combine eggs, applesauce, sweetener, oil and vanilla.
Add nuts and reserved fruit mixture.
Stir in dry ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Pour into a greased 10-inch fluted pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake is done.

title: hot vegetables
directions: Mix thawed and drained vegetables with soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream and 1/2 onions.
Put in 2-quart baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes, covered, at 350°.
Put rest of cheese and onions over and bake 5 minutes more, uncovered.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Place in loaf pan; spread catsup on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream butter; add other ingredients and work with fingers until well blended.
Pinch off bits and roll in balls the size of large marbles.
Bake on slightly buttered cookie sheet in moderately hot oven (375°) about 10 minutes.
Roll while hot in powdered sugar.
Makes about 60.
If too crumbly to make into balls, add just a little milk.

title: boil cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Let come to a full rolling boil, stirring often.
Let boil 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter and oats.
Stir until well mixed. Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
let cool until firm.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil onion, Cajun seasoning, bouillon cube, chicken pieces, celery and garlic salt for 15 to 20 minutes.
While chicken is cooking, saute 2 pounds of sliced, fresh mushrooms in butter (do not overcook).
Squeeze fresh lemon juice over them.
Remove chicken, debone and let cool.
Add 15 ounces of spaghetti to broth and let cook.
Layer cooked chicken, celery and onion on bottom of a large casserole dish.
Pour 1 can of cream of mushroom soup and 1 can cream of celery soup over chicken.
Spread 1 bag of frozen peas on top of chicken mixture.
Put cooked spaghetti on top of peas and add salt and pepper.

Layer mushrooms on top of spaghetti and add grated Cheddar to the top of the casserole (about 2 1/2 cups). Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top of all and bake 20 minutes at 350°. This can be put together the night before and cooked the next day.

title: old fashioned peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients.
In large bowl, beat together margarine and peanut butter.
Beat in sugars until blended, then eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Beat until well blended. Chill dough if it is too sticky.

title: fudge 2
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter for 8 minutes.
Remove from stove and add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Spread in a buttered pan.
Let cool.

title: petite cherry cheesecakes
directions: Cream together the first 5 ingredients.
Use cupcake pan and line with cupcake papers.
Put one vanilla wafer in the bottom and pour mixture over it.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes; when cool, top with cherry pie filling.

title: comfortable freeze
directions: Place ice in blender.
Add ingredients and blend enough to freeze.
Pour into stemmed tulip glass.
Add cherry.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Pour 2 cups sugar over cabbage, pepper, onions and pimientos. Allow to set.
Bring to a boil the oil, vinegar, sugar, celery seed and salt.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: potato topper
directions: Combine sour cream, season-all, parsley flakes, and chives. Spoon over baked potato halves.
Makes 8 (1/2 potato) servings.

title: homemade butter
directions: Mix together in mixer or by hand.
Add yellow food coloring if desired.
Place in covered containers and keep in refrigerator. This will also freeze for later use.
If garlic butter is desired, add garlic salt or powder to taste.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Cut wings into thirds.
Boil tip of wings for broth.
Sprinkle other pieces of wings with garlic salt.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Dip wings in egg and coat with cornstarch.
Fry in Crisco or oleo. Place in baking dish.
Pour sauce over wings.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, butter and bananas in blender until smooth.
Pour this into large mixing bowl.
Add combined dry ingredients until well mixed.
Stir in nuts.
To make 2 large loaves, bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.
Let cool 5 to 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: lazy day cobbler
directions: Melt butter in deep dish.
Mix next 3 ingredients, then pour into butter.
Do not stir.
Put juice and peaches in dish. Sprinkle 1/2 cup of sugar over batter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Drain well and then mash.
Add all other ingredients except cheese.
Place in dish.
Top with cheese and bake 30 minutes on 350°.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Pour milk and apple juice over marshmallows and let stand 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Combine cookie crumbs, nuts, raisins, candied fruit and cherries in a large bowl.
Add marshmallow mixture and mix well.
Line a 9 x 5-inch baking dish with foil. Pack mixture into dish.
Refrigerate several days before slicing.

title: hearty beef and potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes on bottom and up sides of 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes.
Brown beef in large chunks; drain.
Place beef, broccoli, 1/2 can French fried onions and tomatoes in potato shell.
Combine soup, milk, 1/2 cup cheese and seasoning.
Pour over beef mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onion.
Bake, uncovered, for 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry-nut salad
directions: Dissolve gelatine in boiling water.
Fold in strawberries, drained pineapple, bananas and walnuts.
Turn 1/2 of strawberry mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until firm.
Spread top with sour cream and gelatin.
Spoon on remaining strawberry mixture.
Refrigerate; cut into 12 squares and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: jalapeno pepper corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour half of the batter in greased iron skillet that has been heated.
Sprinkle ground meat over, then cheese.
Add rest of the batter. Don't let the cheese touch side of pan or the cornbread will stick.

title: salad green chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, mayonnaise, green onions and garlic powder in large bowl.
Line 4 bread slices with salad greens. Evenly spoon chicken salad on top.
Place pineapple slice over chicken.
Top with remaining bread slices.
Serves 4.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Bone chicken breasts.
Combine all the other ingredients and pour on chicken breasts.
Marinate at least 2 hours, then grill. (A large Ziploc bag works fine for this.)

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in pineapple.
Fold in bread cubes.
Pour in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with baked ham.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon in a mixing bowl.
Add milk, oil, egg and stir until blended.
Lightly stir in blueberries.
Use 2 paper baking cups in each muffin pan. Fill cups slightly more than half full.
Combine sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over top of each muffin.
Bake until brown at 350°. Yields 12 muffins.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Clean the chicken and cut into pieces.
Add the salt, minced garlic and pepper to the chicken.
Put in a kettle and add the bay leaf, vinegar and water.
Cover and let simmer until the chicken is tender and the liquid is partially evaporated.
(Filipinos let most of the liquid evaporate; my family prefers to save some to use as gravy with our rice.)
Take the tender chicken pieces and stir-fry them in a little oil.

title: sparkling summer fruit compote
directions: Combine the honey, orange juice and mint, if using, in a medium-size serving bowl.
Add the honeydew, nectarines and strawberries; gently toss together.
Cover and refrigerate for about 1 hour to chill and blend the flavors.
Just before serving, stir in the club soda.
Garnish with mint leaves, if you wish.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Blend together with pastry blender the 1 1/2 cups of flour, shortening and salt.
Mix the additional 1/2 cup of flour with water and stir into first mixture with a fork.
Put on floured surface and make into a ball.
Divide in half and roll out each half into a circle and place in 8-inch or 9-inch pie pan.
Makes two single crusts.
(Second half may be used for top crust on a fruit pie.)

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; beat well. Stir in oats.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture. Roll into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: george-ann's hot sauce for roast beef
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer on stove top for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: radish dip
directions: Spoon plain low-fat yogurt onto several layers of heavy-duty paper towels.
Spread to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cover with additional paper towels and let stand 5 minutes.
Scrape into a small bowl, using a rubber spatula and set aside.
Position knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add radishes and pulse 5 times or until coarsely chopped. Add mayonnaise and next 3 ingredients and pulse 5 times or until combined. Add to yogurt. Stir well.
Cover and chill.
Garnish with sliced radish, if desired.
Serve with assorted vegetables, such as steamed asparagus, steamed green beans, carrot strips, sliced yellow squash and sliced radishes. Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: cabbage frances(sweet-sour flavor)
directions: In skillet, melt margarine; add onion.
Cook gently until golden brown.
Add cabbage, apple and water.
Mix well.
Cover tightly and simmer, stirring occasionally for about 20 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Continue to simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Cabbage should still be tender-crisp. Makes 6 servings.

title: carnation famous fudge
directions: Butter 8-inch square pan.
In medium saucepan, combine butter, evaporated milk, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly; remove from heat.

title: cherry apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8-inch square baking pan. Combine cherry pie filling and apples in pan.
Add a dash of lemon juice.
Stir together the flour, sugar, cinnamon and Raisin Bran. Add butter; mix well.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes, or until apples are tender.
Makes 6 servings.
Serve plain or top with ice cream.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Grease a large bowl.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Place in 9 x 13 pan; pack down making sides higher.
Mix together 3 eggs, sugar and cream cheese.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: luncheon salad
directions: Cut avocado in half lengthwise; remove seed and peel. Brush with lemon juice. Combine chicken, celery, salt, pepper and mayonnaise. Fill avocado halves. Mix corn flakes with butter and sprinkle over salad. Place stuffed avocado halves on lightly greased baking pan. Bake in oven at 325° about 15 minutes or until warmed through.

title: apple walnut ring cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream
the
margarine, sugar and eggs.	Add cream; beat on low speed.
Add
dry
ingredients and vanilla.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot curlers
directions: Combine deviled ham and shredded cheese with prepared mustard. Separate biscuits.
Pat or roll each into a 4-inch circle. Spread each slice with about 1 tablespoon of the ham mixture. Roll up.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Beat butter, sugar and soup.
Add spices, flour and baking powder; mix well.
Add nuts and/or raisins.
Last, add water and soda.
Bake in a bread loaf pan which has been greased and floured for about 3/4 hour to 1 hour at 350°.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: no cholesterol pie shell
directions: Mix together salt and flour.
Cut in margarine; add water. Press firmly into ball and roll out; place in pie pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.
Makes single crust.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown beef with onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Drain. Add catsup, chili sauce, kidney beans, chili seasoning, water and seasoning flakes.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Add more water as needed.

title: kiwi and ginger sparkle(makes two 10 ounce servings)
directions: Blend the cut up kiwi, peach and ice in a blender until liquified, at least 1 minute.
Half-fill 2 tall glasses.
Fill with ginger ale.
Garnish each with a slice of kiwi.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add salt and pepper.
Add 3 tablespoons of melted butter, a little at a time, beating constantly.
Slowly add the rest of the butter alternately with lemon juice.
If made the day before, chill until serving time.
Stir until softened over lukewarm (not hot) water.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into an uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: double toffee delight
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine the first 3 ingredients and set aside.
In large mixer bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, puddings, water, oil, vanilla and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour 1/2 batter into prepared pan and sprinkle with 1/2 brown sugar mixture, rest of batter, then sprinkle with rest of brown sugar mixture.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 300°, until top springs back when touched lightly in center.

title: o'henry bars(no bake)
directions: Mix together the oatmeal, corn syrup, butter and sugar and press into a buttered 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: aunt vera's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Put in an 11 x 13-inch pan.

Cut onions in half, carrots in 2 to 3-inch pieces and potatoes in quarters. Place vegetables and spices on meat. Mix instant soup and water. Add to pan. Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours until meat is fork-tender.

title: heath candy
directions: In heavy skillet, melt butter and add sugar over medium high heat.
When mixture starts to boil, cook 7 minutes stirring constantly.
It will be a light brown.
Pour into lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Place chocolate bars on top and spread over surface.
Add chopped nuts (break up candy when cool).

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Put in pot with about 4 quarts water and bring to boil.
Simmer until tender.
Debone.
Mix together flour, salt, baking powder, egg and 1 cup broth.
Roll dough on floured surface until thin.
Cut into small strips and drop a few at a time into boiling broth.
Carefully stirring, cook until done.
Add chickens and stir in.
Pour a can of cream of chicken soup over the top of chicken dumplings.
Don't stir.
Cover and let sit a few minutes before serving.

title: pinch me cake
directions: Split biscuits in four; roll in buttered hands, then roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Put in a well buttered tube pan.
Sprinkle some sugar and cinnamon and nuts between biscuits.
Sprinkle more sugar and cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert immediately.

title: old-fashioned chicken salad
directions: Drizzle with French dressing.
Refrigerate for several hours. Just before serving, add rest of the ingredients, except eggs. Arrange on crisp greens on salad plates.
Serve cut eggs on side of plate.

title: toll house oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend butter, sugars, vanilla and water.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture, mix well.
Stir in oatmeal and chocolate chips. Drop by 1/2 teaspoon. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: turkey lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray bottom of large skillet with nonstick vegetable spray.
Crumble ground turkey into pan; add onion.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat, 5 to 7 minutes or until turkey is lightly browned.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Reserve 1 cup meat sauce.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Then add flour, baking soda and bananas.
Cook at 350°.

title: baked pork & rice
directions: Salt and pepper pork and roll in flour. Brown meat in shortening in a skillet. In a greased casserole dish, combine the tomatoes, onion, peppers, rice, salt and pepper. Put in meat and drippings. Add sugar. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a large bowl, mix well.
Spoon chicken mixture into a lightly greased shallow 2-quart casserole (or use 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan).
Sprinkle cheese over mixture.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sauce a la bari
directions: Simmer olive oil in large saucepot with 2 cloves garlic and 1 tablespoon onion.
Meanwhile, brown sausage and pork on both sides. Pour all cans (tomatoes, puree and paste) into the large pot that contains the garlic and onion.
Add 1 cup water and the sugar to the tomato sauce.
Add sausage and pork to sauce and sprinkle with fresh parsley.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine cornbread mix, egg and milk.
Spoon into 8-inch square pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Crumble and set aside.

title: hart's nacho dip
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Place in slow cooker on low.
Add garlic powder, Ro-Tel tomatoes, and cheese stirring occasionally until smooth.
Add water.
Do not leave for very long.
May burn on sides.
When serving, add a dish of sour cream to the side.
Some may enjoy this addition.

title: sensible double chocolate chip brownies
directions: Over low heat, melt 1 cup chips, sugar, applesauce and margarine; stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add egg whites; stir well.
Stir in flour, baking soda and vanilla.
Stir in rest of chips and nuts.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 16 to 20 minutes, or just until set.
Cool completely.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: mom's plum tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients except jam.
Grease and flour 4 (8-inch) round cake pans.
Press dough in pans.
Spread plum jam on top of each.
Bake on top rack for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 (8-inch) tarts.

title: shoestring salad
directions: Mix carrots, celery and onion. Add tuna or other meat and mayonnaise. Just before serving, add shoestring potatoes.

title: crock-pot chicken in mushroom gravy
directions: Place chicken pieces in crock-pot.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix wine and soup and pour over chicken.
Add mushrooms. Cover and cook on low, 7 to 9 hours or high, 3 to 4 hours.

title: lil's spinach dip
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Refrigerate for a couple hours. Delicious with crackers as a dip or in hollowed out kaiser rolls or sheepherders bread.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix beans in saucepan until they begin to boil.
Drain and pour cold water over beans.
Mix ingredients.
Stir twice after refrigerating.

title: "buttermilk pie"(quick, easy and delicious)
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla, flour and melted margarine and mix until smooth.
Blend in buttermilk and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell (deep dish) and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Pie will be very brown on top when done.

title: italian cheese ball
directions: In a small mixer bowl at medium speed, beat all ingredients until creamy and well blended.
Divide mixture in half.
With wet hands, shape each half into a ball.
Or, spoon all of the mixture into a crock.
Cover balls or crock and chill at least 1 hour.
To serve, roll balls in parsley or pecans up to 1 hour before serving. Let mixture come to room temperature for easier spreading.

title: barbecued lima beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Next day, drain and add water and bacon. Cook slowly until tender.
Drain reserving 1 1/2 c. liquid.
Brown onion and garlic in fat.
Add mustard, worcestershire sauce, chili powder and salt.
Cook 5 minutes.
Alternate lima beans and sauce in greased casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 400 degrees.
Serves 8.

title: fried catfish
directions: Cut fish into filets or pan size pieces.
Mix egg and milk in bowl for batter.
Dip fish in egg batter and roll in mixture of meal, salt and pepper.
Deep fry in hot fat until brown.

title: jalapeno marinade
directions: In plastic bag or nonporous bowl, mix all ingredients and combine with 2 pounds of chicken breasts or 1 1/4 pounds of beef or pork.
Marinate for 2 to 24 hours.
Grill or broil.
Yields 5 servings.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Bring water, sugar and cream of tartar to a boil, then drop in crackers.
Place in uncooked pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Put dabs of margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Tastes like real apple pie.

title: zucchini beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in oil.
Add rice and seasoning.
Stir a few minutes. Drain off excess grease.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch casserole half the sliced zucchini, all of the meat mixture, cottage cheese, remainder of zucchini, soup and grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or longer.

title: pesto
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor or blender.
Blend until consistency of mayonnaise.
Serve over pasta.

title: hot lettuce salad
directions: Cut up desired amount of romaine or leaf lettuce.
Mix in some crumbled fried bacon.
Mix equal amounts of oil, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over lettuce at last minute and serve.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Mix until blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Shape into ball and chill.
Roll into finely chopped nuts.
Allow to soften at room temperature for 2 hours or so before serving.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Combine nuts, sugar, salt and syrup in bowl.
Stir well.
Cook on High 4 minutes.
Stir.
Cook another 4 minutes on High.
Stir. Add butter and vanilla and cook on High 1 minute.
Add baking soda.
Stir immediately.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet.
Allow to cool.
Break into pieces.

title: baked peas in tomatoes
directions: Remove pulp from tomatoes, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Combine pulp, peas, cheese, bread crumbs and seasonings in a medium bowl. Mix lightly.
Fill tomato shells with mixture.
Arrange in a lightly greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook elbows 2/3 of the time indicated on box. Mix the soups, tuna fish and approximately 1/2 to 3/4 of the soup can of milk with drained macaroni in a large casserole dish. Spread Cheez Whiz over top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail butter sauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into lightly floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cold taco dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and spread on bottom of an 8 x 8-inch Tupperware.
Put some mild taco sauce over this, then a layer of shredded cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: steak and mushrooms
directions: Salt and pepper steaks.
Quick-fry in oil until both sides are brown.
Drain oil off.
Cut onions and mushrooms up.
Add to meat in skillet along with the water.
Put lid on it and simmer for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve meat topped with some mushrooms and onions.

title: zebra deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Remove yolks; mash.
Blend in sandwich spread and salt and red pepper to taste.
Refill whites.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: corn puff
directions: Make a white sauce with butter, flour, milk and salt.
Add green pepper.
Beat egg yolks and add to sauce.
Then add corn. Beat egg whites until stiff and add to corn mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix cake and dry pudding with fork.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Pour about 1/2 cup sauce in dish.
Cover with uncooked noodles, laid side by side.
Evenly distribute half the Ricotta, half the Mozzarella and 1/3 of sauce over noodles.
Repeat this step.
Top with third layer of noodles and remaining sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Remove from oven and leave for 20 minutes, covered, then uncover and eat.

title: potters soup
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer for 1 to 2 hours.

title: peach or blackberry cobbler
directions: Blackberries may be used instead of peaches.

title: peanut-pretzel bark
directions: Melt chocolate, peanut butter chips and peanut butter in double boiler.
Add peanuts and pretzels.
Pour and spread on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: smoky mountain jam cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 baking pans.
Cream sugar and butter with mixer in bowl until fluffy.
Add vanilla; blend.
Add eggs; blend. Sift flour, cinnamon, cloves, allspice and baking soda into separate bowl.
Alternately beat flour mixture and buttermilk into creamed mixture.
Stir in preserves and blackberries.
Pour into pans and bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes until done.
Cool; turn out of pans.
Place bottom layer on cake plate.
Spread plum jelly over layer.
Add top layer.
Frost with caramel icing.

title: clam scallop
directions: Beat eggs; add clams and crushed crackers.
Blend with a fork. Add milk and melted butter or margarine, salt and pepper.
Bake in a greased casserole at 400° for 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grandma's buttermilk chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat all ingredients together until smooth. Pour into greased 10-inch pie plate. Bake for about 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool completely before serving.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix all together, except soup.
Shape into small meat loaf shapes.
Brown on both sides.
Place in loaf pan.
Add mushroom soup and a little water to rinse can.
Bake 2 hours at 300° to 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a greased casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until done.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients except stuffing mix.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle stuffing mix on top.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt in pan.
Blend in water.
Add milk and bring to boil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in butter and vanilla.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Let sit and when stiff, whip.
Beat whipping cream and fold into Jell-O mixture.
Beat cream cheese with a fork and add to Jell-O mixture, along with crushed pineapple.
Let set in refrigerator until reset.

title: spoon cornbread
directions: Mix
first
4 ingredients with fork or whisk.
Add warm water until
the	consistency of cake batter.
Spoon into hot oil in frying pan.
Cook until golden brown on both sides.

title: hard sauce
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add bourbon slowly, mixing to incorporate.
May add more to get a softer consistency.
Chill. Serve with steamed cranberry or plum pudding.

title: baptist pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and shortening with sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating well with each addition.
Sift flour.
Add baking powder and sift again.
Add milk and flour alternately to mixture, blending well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Put into cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: corn pea salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, and sugar together.
Bring this mixture to a boil.
Set this off to cool about five minutes.
pour over corn and pea mixture.
Set in refrigerator until cool.
Eat and enjoy!

title: coleslaw
directions: Toss the cabbage, carrot and pepper in a large salad bowl. In a saucepan, combine vinegar, mustard seed, sugar and celery seed.
Bring mixture to a boil for 1 minute; allow to cool.
Pour over cabbage mixture and serve chilled.

title: butter pecan bars
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add brown sugar and granulated sugar. Pour melted butter over egg mixture and blend.
Add flour, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan and bake in 350° preheated oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut into bars while slightly warm.

title: lemon angel food dessert
directions: Put angel food cubes in cake pan about 10 x 13-inch.
Cool lemon filling.
Pour over angel food cake.
Cover top with Dream Whip.
You may want to put a few cherries on top.

title: chicken casserole *
directions: Cook, bone and cube chicken.
Mix together Escort crackers and butter to make crust.
Line pan with 1/2 mixture leaving 1/2 for top.
Mix chicken, water chestnuts, pimentos, mushroom and chicken soup (rinse soup cans with 1/4 cup chicken broth).
Add sour cream and pour this mixture into lined pan.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until desired brownness is reached.
This casserole may be made a day in advance and refrigerated before baking.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all these ingredients together and pour into casserole dish.

title: pear tart
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch spring pan.
Toss pears with lemon juice.
Cream 1/2 cup butter with 3/4 cup sugar.
Add beaten eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to mixture.
Add almond extract.
Stir batter.
It will be thick. Spread batter in pan.
Top with pear mixture.
Top with 1/4 cup each butter and sugar.
Top with slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: play dough
directions: Mix food coloring and a few drops of oil of cloves.
Add dry ingredients and enough water to make the right consistency.
Store in a plastic bag.

title: tiny magic fruit cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Pour into tiny, well-greased muffin pans.
Be sure to grease well or use tiny paper cups.
Top each cake with cherry.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Let cool.
This may also be baked in a loaf pan or a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Put in buttered casserole.
Dash of cinnamon on top, if desired.
Bake in oven approximately 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fried chicken
directions: Put roast in a large covered pot and brown on medium-high heat 2 to 3 minutes on all sides.
Add onion soup mix, mushroom soup and water.
Stir well.
Cut heat to low when it comes to a boil; cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add potatoes, carrots and mushrooms. Cover and simmer 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
When meat is very tender, add the cornstarch mixture and stir until slightly thickened for your gravy.
You do not need to add salt because of the salt in the dry onion soup mix.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook potatoes until tender in very little water.
Add milk; thicken with flour base.
Add clams and Old Bay to milk and potato mixture.
Heat on medium temperature until all is hot.
Do not boil.

title: cheese loaf
directions: Grate and cream the cheese.
Add cream, mayonnaise and pepper and mix well.
Add chopped pecans.
Mold with hands in any shape desired and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, pour strawberry preserves over the cheese loaf.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: country pork roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place pork loin on a roasting rack. Combine salt, garlic and 1 teaspoon chili powder and rub it over the pork surface.
Roast meat, uncovered, in the center of preheated oven for 30 to 60 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Then in a blender, add all other ingredients and blend.
Put drained sausage into a greased square baking dish or pan and then pour blended ingredients over the sausage and bake at 400° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: yam cobbler
directions: Prepare
yams
by
boiling
skins.
When tender, remove skins, mash
and
beat
until
light.
Add
sugar to yams; add spices
to taste.
One ground clove will improve it.
Proceed to fill
dish the same as for layer cake.
Roll out the layer of dough quite thin; spread yam mixture on in layers about 1/4 inch thick, proceed
until
dish
is full.
Add to each layer just
enough water
to cook the crust.
Bake until thoroughly done and serve with drawn butter or hard sauce.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add undiluted soup and cheese.
Let cheese melt and add other seasonings.
Cook and drain broccoli. Add to mixture.
Top with crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Add the last 3 ingredients to apples and mix.
Cream sugar, eggs, oil, baking powder and orange juice.
Add salt and vanilla. Add flour, one cup at a time.
Mix well.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Add a layer of batter, a layer of apple mixture, a layer of batter, apple mixture and then top with a layer of batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Spread in baking dish and bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: moonlight mushroom soup
directions: Melt butter in dutch oven over medium heat. Add onion and saute until almost tender. Add mushrooms and saute briefly. Stir in bouillon, parsley, tomato paste, garlic and pepper. Reduce heat and add wine. Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Ladle hot soup into serving bowls and sprinkle with cheese. Serve immediately.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cut sausage in 1/2 inch slices, then cut slices into fourths. Roll each fourth into a ball and place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet and drain well. Place in a deep bowl.
Bring sugar, vinegar and catsup to a boil in a small saucepan.
Pour over sausage balls.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator at least 48 hours.
Stir gently after 24 hours.
Heat before serving.
Yields 60.

title: sour cream drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, beating well. Add vanilla.
Add sour cream with mixed in soda.
Add salt and flour that has been sifted together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: parmesan cheese puff rounds
directions: Mix together cream cheese, onion, mayonnaise and Tabasco sauce.
Add Parmesan cheese and chill.

title: fish marinade
directions: Combine the ingredients in glass bowl and add fish, coating well.
Cover the fish and refrigerate for 1 hour or longer.
Grill.

title: wild card chili
directions: Brown beef with onions in a Dutch oven; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: artichoke frittata
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and reserve marinade.
Saute artichoke hearts, onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon of marinade.
Beat eggs in a bowl.
Add bread crumbs, salt, pepper, oregano and Tabasco. Stir in cheese, parsley and artichoke/onion mixture.
Turn into pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
When toothpick comes out clean, it is done.

title: low-fat fries
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into medium strips.
Spread fries onto cookie sheet.
Brush lightly with oil.
Season to taste.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: cubed pork casserole
directions: In the Wesson oil, place basil, rosemary, garlic and paprika. Be sure to ask your butcher to remove the fell.
Use the spiced oil mixture and rub the leg of lamb thoroughly and set it aside for 3 to 4 hours.
In a preheated oven at 325°, place leg of lamb, fat side up, in a roasting pan.
Roast for 2 1/2 hours.
Remove pan from oven and spread mint jelly over entire surface of lamb. Return to oven for another hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add beaten eggs.
Sift flour, add salt, soda and cocoa together, mix well.
Add milk, vinegar and food coloring and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. Frost with white (cream cheese) frosting.

title: banana pie
directions: Prepare pudding according to packaged directions and chill. Mix the 4 oz. of softened cream cheese with 1/2 cup of Cool Whip. Spread mixture in the bottom of the pie shell.
Top with sliced bananas.
Once pudding is chilled, mix pudding with the remaining softened cream cheese.
As you are mixing, add 1 cup of Cool Whip. Blend until the consistency is smooth.
Pour the pudding mixture over the sliced bananas.
Top the pie with a generous amount of Cool Whip.
Chill overnight.

title: pear relish
directions: Run all through a food chopper.
Have sweetened vinegar boiling hot when fruit is added.
Cook 40 minutes.
Place in sterilized jars and seal.
Hot pepper may be used if hot relish is liked.

title: goombaughs
directions: Combine cake, butter, milk and nuts.
Bake 1/2 of cake mix in 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 10 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramel.
Pour caramel over cake mix.
Add chocolate chips.
Top with rest of cake mix.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
This recipe will serve 5 people.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: For each ice cream sandwich, use two cookies.
Put a tablespoon of ice cream on one cookie and top with the second cookie.
Put sandwiches on a cookie sheet and freeze until firm. When frozen, wrap each ice cream sandwich in plastic wrap.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown together the ground chuck and onion.
Add spaghetti sauce, tomato juice, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Cook lasagna noodles until tender.
Blend together cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Layer the noodles, sauce and cheese mixture in a 12 x 15-inch pan, ending with layer of cheese mixture.
Top with a heavy coating of Parmesan cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: maple popcorn
directions: Heat maple syrup in saucepan over medium heat until syrup reaches soft-ball stage. Lightly oil a large mixing bowl. Mix popcorn, nuts and syrup with lightly oiled spoon. Allow to cool. Break off pieces to eat.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Now to this mixture, add your service through a sieve, the fault will sift away and cause no one to grieve.
Stir lightly with a son (or daughter), make every stroke a prayer.
Pour gently in the pan of kindness, love and care.
Bake slowly in the heart; when done, allow to cool.
Share kindly with thy neighbor and serve with Golden Rule.

title: easy brownies
directions: Sift flour, cocoa and salt together.
Make well in center. Add oil, sugar and eggs; beat well with mixer.
Add vanilla and nuts last.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: jello squares
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl; stir until dissolved.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass or Tupperware container.
Put in fridge until set.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: guacamole
directions: Using a sharp knife, cut avocados in half and remove the pits. Scoop the flesh into a medium sized bowl and roughly crush with a fork. Stir in lime juice.

title: mexican sunset
directions: Pour the orange juice into a tall glass.
Add grenadine and allow to settle on the bottom.
May be served over ice.
Makes 1 serving.

title: tabbouli
directions: Mix bulgur wheat and water and let set until absorbed. Drain off excess water and cool in refrigerator.	When cooled, add olive oil and mix.
Squeeze garlic into mixture.	Add remaining ingredients to mixture.
Mix and place in refrigerator for three to four hours.

title: tiger butter(candy)
directions: Melt white chocolate in double boiler.
Mix in peanut butter. Pour into cookie sheet lined with waxed paper.
Melt dark chocolate and pour over first mixture.
Take knife and swirl through both mixtures deep enough to give it a marbled look.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: rosemary lemon chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in rest of ingredients for 30 minutes to several hours.
Broil 5 minutes per side.

title: date loaf
directions: Cook sugar and milk over medium heat (stirring constantly) to soft ball stage (235°).
Add dates and pecans.
Let cool.
Turn into a buttered pan.
Knead until creamy and stiff.
Shape into a roll.
Wrap in damp dish towel or waxed paper.
Chill and then slice.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 pounds.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients together in skillet or saucepan.
Cook until tender.
Serve over baked potato or steak.

title: spinach stuffed tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut a star shape out of the bottom of each tomato.
Scoop out the pulp.
Place shells in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine spinach souffle, Swiss cheese and nutmeg. Spoon into tomato shells.
Bake 20 minutes.
Place tops in pan also.
Bake until filling is puffed and golden.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt oleo; blend in flour, salt, pepper and milk.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in cheese until melted.

title: pie crust
directions: Cream together salt and shortening.
Add flour and water; roll out.

title: cowboy bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir together the water, milk and sugar. Sprinkle the yeast over the top and let stand for 5 minutes to dissolve. Stir the egg and butter into the yeast mixture, then stir in the salt, nutmeg and 2 cups of the flour. Mix until everything is well blended. Mix in remaining flour, 1/2 cup at a time, until the dough pulls away from the side of the bowl. Turn out onto a floured surface and knead for 10 minutes (no cheating!). Place dough into a greased bowl and let rise until doubled in size. Divide the dough into 8 balls and let rest for another 20 minutes. Roll each ball out to 8 to 10-inches in diameter.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften, then mix all ingredients together, except nuts.
Line small plastic bowl with plastic wrap and pour nuts in bottom.
Add cheese mixture to bowl and form to sides.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: no bake chocolate-oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix; drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: onion rings
directions: Combine flour and salt in bowl.
Add milk and 2 tablespoons oil.
Beat in egg until smooth.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix in a blender until smooth.
Pour in 9-inch buttered pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until it has set.
Cool; refrigerate.

title: tortilla torte
directions: In medium saucepan, melt chocolate chips over low heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in 2 cups sour cream.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Place 1 tortilla onto a plate.
Spread about 1/3 cup chocolate mixture on top.
Repeat with 8 of the remaining tortillas and the remaining chocolate mixture.
Top with the last tortilla.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Pour into a medium-large casserole dish or aluminum pans. Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Should be golden brown. Let stand for about 10 minutes before serving so that it can settle.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Combine meat, egg, 3/4 cup crumbs, salt and pepper and mix well.

title: sweet potato yummy
directions: Boil potatoes on medium heat for about 15 minutes, then add all other ingredients.
Put into buttered casserole dish.

title: potato soup
directions: Cube potatoes and cover with water, about 2 inches above the potatoes.
Cook until potatoes start to get tender; put milk and tablespoon of butter in.
Add salt, pepper and Cajun seasoning. Cook until potatoes get tender and juice gets thick.
If juice doesn't get thick, thicken with flour and water.
Some potatoes will not cook and thicken on juice.

title: texas corn bread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, oil and sour cream and stir until blended.
Stir in corn and peppers. Pour half the batter in a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Add rest of batter and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix all together in order. Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes. Use 9 x 9 or 5 x 9 greased pan. While warm, cut and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: carrot cake
directions: Add all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and beat thoroughly.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
When the cake is cool, remove it from the pan.
Prepare cream cheese frosting.

title: sausage chili
directions: Combine and brown first 6 ingredients.
To combined and browned mixture add rest of ingredients and simmer over low heat for several hours.
Better the next day.

title: crockpot chicken creole
directions: Place raw chicken in bottom of crock pot.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Do Not stir!
Cover and simmer on low for 7-8 hours or on High for 4-5 hours.
Stir before serving over bed of freshly cooked rice.

title: firestation casserole
directions: Brown ground beef. Add onions and cook for 2 minutes. Mix cream of mushroom soup, 2/3 can of milk (about 7 ounces) and chopped (diced) green chilies in a bowl. Grate Cheddar cheese. Next, cut or tear 1 dozen corn tortillas into 2-inch squares and place a layer of tortillas in bottom of small oblong or 8-inch square ovenproof baking dish. Top with 1/3 ground beef, 1/3 soup mixture and 1/3 cheese. Repeat layers 2 times. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: meatless chili
directions: In a large saucepot, heat vegetables and oil over medium heat. Add onion, garlic, chili powder, basil, oregano and cumin.
Cook, stirring until onion is tender.
Add zucchini and carrots, cook stirring 1 or 2 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, chickpeas and kidney beans.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple dream cake
directions: Prepare vanilla pudding and cool thoroughly.
Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Cut in margarine and egg yolk with pastry blender until well mixed.
Firmly press mixture onto a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix cooled vanilla pudding with drained crushed pineapple and spread over baked crust.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions on package and spread over pudding mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cut into squares.
Chill.
(This recipe may be cut in half.)

title: applesauce cake
directions: Blend sugar and margarine.
Add egg and applesauce.
Add soda to boiling water and add to the flour and spices.
Add 1 cup of raisins and 1/2 of chopped nuts.
Pour batter into a greased and floured round cake mold.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: fluffy waffles
directions: Mix and cook in waffle iron.

title: angel food cake surprise!(great for holidays)
directions: Mix Oreos, butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar together and set aside.
Leave part of Oreo mixture for top.
Mix pudding and milk together and let refrigerate to thicken.
Fold Cool Whip into pudding.

title: crescent cream cheese bars
directions: Roll out 1 tube of crescent rolls and lay in bottom of ungreased 9x13 cake pan.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, vanilla and spread over dough.
Roll out second tube of crescent rolls and lay on top of filling.
Mix melted butter, 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and pour over all.

title: vegetables mexican style
directions: Drain pinto beans, and corn.
Cut bell pepper into small pieces also dice onion.
Mix all ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Serve with crackers or restaurant chips.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: With electric mixer; cream butter well.
Gradually add 1/2 cup confectioners sugar and cream until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pinch off small pieces of dough and roll with hands into finger shapes (if too soft to handle, chill about 15 minutes).
Preheat oven to 375°.
Put on ungreased cookie sheets and bake about 10 minutes.
While hot, roll in confectioners sugar.
Cool on rack.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: aplets
directions: Soak gelatine and cooked applesauce for 10 minutes.
Bring 3/4 cup applesauce and 2 cups sugar to a boil.
Add the gelatin mixture to sugar and sauce.
Boil 20 minutes watching carefully. Remove from heat; add nutmeats and vanilla.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan; let stand 24 hours.
Cut into squares. Roll in powdered sugar and place on waxed paper to dry.

title: hungarian stuffed cabbage
directions: Core cabbage and place in enough boiling salted water to cover.
Brown onion in shortening.
Add meat, seasoning and rice and mix well.
Take off one cabbage leaf at a time and cut off heavy vein.
Fill leaf with 1 tablespoon mixed ingredients and roll loosely.
Fold in one side of leaf as you roll and tuck in the other side with fingers when rolled.
Cut up remaining cabbage leaves and mix with sauerkraut.
Put cabbage rolls into deep pot lined with the mixed sauerkraut and save some to put on the top of cabbage rolls.
Pour salted water to cover all the rolls.
Cover and cook slowly until the rice is tender, for about 1 1/2 hours. Serve hot with 2 tablespoons sour cream over the cabbage rolls.

title: sauteed chicken livers
directions: Cover chicken livers with ice water for 1 1/2 hours.
Drain and dry.
Flour lightly.
Saute in butter with grated onion.
Add sherry and parsley.
Cook until most of sauce disappears.

title: lemon chiffon pudding
directions: Blend the sugar, flour, butter and salt.
Add the lemon juice, lemon rind, egg yolks and milk.
Fold in the egg whites.
Pour into buttered baking dish and set in a pan of hot water.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.
The flour and eggs form a cake on top with a delicious lemon pudding on the bottom.
Delicious and so much quicker and easier to make than a lemon pie.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook meat, tomato juice, onion and 6 cups water.
Simmer 2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Simmer 1 more hour.
Remove bay leaves and serve.

title: doughboys(method:  stick)
directions: Roll biscuit between hands to make a "snake" that is about 1/2-inch thick.
Wrap biscuit in a spiral around a toasting stick. (Be sure to keep spirals close together.)
Pinch ends of biscuit tight against the stick.
Toast over coals, turning continuously to brown evenly.
Remove from stick and fill hole with butter and jelly.
Cooking time:
5 to 10 minutes.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Sprinkle cucumber slices with sugar and salt.
Add vinegar. Press slices with back of spoon to release juice.
Cover tightly and chill about 4 hours.

title: breakfast tacos
directions: In medium skillet over medium heat, heat butter. Add potato and cook until lightly browned. Add eggs and bacon and cook until eggs are set, but still moist. Warm tortillas according to package directions. Spoon about 1/2 cup potato mixture down center of each tortilla. Top with cheese and picante sauce. Roll up.

title: crab pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until blended.
Stir in crab meat, cheese and onion.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant; cut into small pieces and boil in salted water until tender; drain and mash.
Put oleo into skillet; add onions and fry slowly until tender, but not brown.
Add eggplant, tomatoes, cheese and the 1/3 cup bread crumbs.
When hot, add beaten eggs, cooking and stirring until eggs are cooked.
Pour into baking dish.
Put buttered crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until browned on top (about 30 minutes).

title: ultimate macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni according to package instructions.

title: mother's chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients in large pan.
Add chicken wings and marinate as long as possible (at least overnight).
Cook in 325° oven for approximately 1 1/4 hours, or until nice and brown.
Turn once or twice.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Combine with 1/2 stick butter.
Add onion, sour cream, soup and cheese; mix well.
Pour into large baking dish.
Cover with corn flakes; sprinkle with 1/4 cup melted butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon basil cookies
directions: Blend butter and cream cheese and egg yolk until fluffy.
Turn into cake mix 1/3 at a time.
Fix last portion by hand.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by level tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until lightly browned.
For bar cookies use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: shanghai noodles with spicy beef sauce
directions: Heat wok or large skillet until hot; add the oil, garlic, ginger root and pepper flakes.
Saute about 5 seconds.
Add onion; stir-fry until onion is transparent.
Crumble in ground beef; stir-fry until the meat is light brown.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix hash browns and 1/4 cup butter, onions, sour cream, cheese and soup.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1/4 cup butter and corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: chicken salad mousse
directions: Place chicken in large pot and cover with water.
Add salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until chicken is tender and falls from bones.
When cool, discard skin and bones.
Cut chicken in 1/2-inch pieces (about 4 cups).
Reserve 1 1/2 cups chicken broth.
Remove fat and pour into saucepan.
In large bowl, mix chicken, peas, relish, lemon juice, curry powder, eggs, celery, mayonnaise and sour cream in a cup.
Dissolve gelatin in water and stir into reserved broth.
Heat to boiling, stirring continuously.
Cool slightly and combine with chicken mixture. Spray a 10-cup mold or 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour mixture into mold.
Refrigerate until firm, 1 hour or overnight.
Unmold.
Slice on bed of lettuce.

title: crab salad
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Combine with mayo, cream cheese and crab meat.

title: spanish hamburg
directions: Put all in bowl and mix.
Make patties and dip in flour. Brown in cake pan.
Put small bottle of ketchup on top.
(Might throughout baking have to add a little water.)
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: favorite cookie
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in Carnation milk and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; chill 1 hour.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick and sausage.
Melt cheese; pour into mixture. Roll into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Put soup in pan.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk, oleo and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Mix all ingredients and put cooked broccoli in casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with bread croutons, if desired.
Serves 12.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon.
Arrange bacon across top of mixture.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 325°.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Layer One:
Take 1 cup of cake mix out and save.
Mix rest of cake mix with 1 egg and 1/2 cup soft butter.
Mix and pat into bottom of buttered and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: macaroni and bacon casserole
directions: Combine sour cream, cheese, salt and paprika in saucepan. Stir in hot macaroni.
Heat, covered, over low heat 5 minutes or until heated.
Stir in bacon.
Pour mixture into baking dish. Combine bread crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle evenly.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes or until bread crumbs are browned.

title: snowball cake
directions: Add boiling water to gelatin.
Mix well gelatin, juice, pineapple, sugar, lemon and salt and place in refrigerator to jell. Beat Dream Whip and stir into mixture.
Tear angel food cake into small pieces and place in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cover with mixture.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Sprinkle coconut on top when ready to serve.

title: fudge sundae sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, combine chocolate, cream, coffee and salt. Heat on low, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Cover and refrigerate.
Reheat to serve over your favorite ice cream.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: large meat sandwich
directions: Cut half off top of sandwich bread.
Scoop out bread.
Layer with cream cheese mixture, cheese, meat, etc., until all used. Wrap and let set overnight.

title: body builders
directions: Mix cereals and peanuts in large roasting pan and set aside. Melt butter in pan.
Add sugar, cinnamon and peanut butter.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour liquid over cereals and stir well, coating cereals.
Bake in 300° oven for 20 minutes.
Stir again; cool and serve.

title: fresh apple cake(no eggs or milk)
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, using a large glass pie pan sprayed with Pam.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook the first three ingredients in a heavy skillet.
When syrup begins to thicken, add nuts, butter and salt.
Cook until golden brown.
Quickly add baking soda.
Pour evenly into a greased cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: old-fashioned candied yams
directions: Peel and cut yams in quarters.
Sprinkle with sugar and nutmeg.
Add butter, vanilla, salt and water.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix all ingredients, using only half the cheese; mix together and heat through.
Pour mixture into tortillas and roll up seam side down.
If some of the mixture is leftover, pour on top of with the rest of the cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, covered.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 9-inch loaf pan.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add raisins.
Combine eggs, buttermilk and melted butter.
Add to dry ingredients.
Put batter in pan.
Bake about 1 hour.
Remove from pan.

title: swiss egg bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except eggs. Heat, stirring, until cheese melts.

Pour into a shallow casserole or baking pan. Break the eggs carefully into the sauce. Bake until eggs are of desired firmness, approximately 25 to 30 minutes. Serve over toasted English muffins. As a dinner dish, eggs could be served on a bed of wheat pilaf.

title: sweet hot mustard
directions: In top of double boiler, put one 4 ounce can Coleman's dry mustard.
Pour 1 cup tarragon vinegar in.
Do not stir!
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Beat in 6 whole eggs, one at a time with wooden spoon. Add 1 cup sugar.
Stir and cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Stir until thickens.
Add 1 stick margarine.
Stir until melted.
Let cool in glass jars.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind and put into colander or cheesecloth bag all except apples; strain well. Put into large pot and add vinegar, sugar, salt, allspice and cinnamon. Cook approximately 15 minutes. Add apples. When mixture begins to boil, put in sterilized jars and seal. Makes approximately 8 pints. This relish is especially good with fried eggs or any kind of beans.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Note:
Sauce may be hot or mild.

title: potato boats
directions: Bake potatoes in preheated 425° oven until soft, about 60 minutes.
Meanwhile, peel squash; cut into slices and steam for 15 minutes or until very soft.
Cool potatoes slightly.
Cut in half and gently scrape pulp from skin; be careful not to tear skin. Combine squash, potato pulp, 1/4 cup melted butter, cumin and salt in food processor until you have a creamy puree.
(Doesn't work in a blender; I've tried it, duh!)
Heap mixture into empty potato skins.
Brush with 2 teaspoons melted butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Place under broiler 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Serves 2 to 4, depending on size of potatoes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Bake in long pans.
Combine all ingredients into mixing bowl; beat well.
Bake at 325° until done.
Top with 7 Minute Icing.

title: chicken nut puffs
directions: Combine chicken with almonds.
Blend broth, oil, salt, celery seed, parsley flakes and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil. Add flour.
Cook over low heat, beating rapidly until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a smooth, compact ball.
Remove from heat and add one egg at a time, beating until mixture is shiny. Stir in chicken mixture.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon mixture on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot. Makes 25 servings.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; put in pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat egg yolks, 2 cups sugar and half and half.
Add rhubarb and spread over above crust.
Bake 45 minutes or longer. Whip egg whites, 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla and spread on filling; bake until brown.

title: korean meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into a loaf.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all together.
Add enough milk for mixture to drop off spoon.
Drop by tablespoon in a deep fry pot.
Fry 1 minute on each side, or until brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: joseph's coat
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Pour over vegetables while still hot.
Let set for 24 hours.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Steep tea bags in the 1 cup boiling water, 2 to 3 minutes. Remove tea bags.
Stir in sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until sugar is dissolved.
Pour into freezer container.
Freeze firm.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.

title: cooked winter squash
directions: Put all ingredients in pan and cook over medium heat until tender.

title: pretzel salad(a delicious dessert)
directions: Mix together pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 minute.
Cream the cheese and mix with Cool Whip and 1 cup of sugar.
Spread over cooled pretzels.
Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water.
When cool, add strawberries with juice.
Pour over cheese mixture and refrigerate.

title: broccoli and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice according to instructions.
Layer half the rice in a greased 1 1/2 qt. baking dish.
Place drained broccoli over the rice.
Place remainder of rice over broccoli. Spread mushroom soup on next.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese melts and is bubbly.

title: black forest torte
directions: Prepare two 9-inch cake layers as directed on package.
Bake and cool.
Spoon 1 cup whipped topping around outside edge of bottom layer.
Fill center of 1st layer with one-half of pie filling.
Place second layer on top.
Spoon 1 1/2 cups whipped topping around top edge and spoon remaining pie filling into center top of cake.
Chill and serve.
Keep leftover cake refrigerated.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Beat all ingredients, except crab meat, in mixer until smooth. Add crab meat and mix gently.
Heat in oven until warm.
May also be served cold.

title: cheese balls
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Mix in beef chips, onions (chopped with tops) and salt.
Form into a ball.
Roll in nuts. Wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate a few hours or overnight for more flavor.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour well.
Add next 5 ingredients in order given.
Pour into 8-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: lemon coconut cream cake
directions: The day before serving: Prepare angel food cake mix and bake in a 10-inch tube pan as package directs.
Let pan hang over neck of bottle at least 2 hours until cake is completely cool.

title: grandmother's crock pickles
directions: Put all ingredients in a pan; heat to simmer.
Have the small and medium cucumber pickles scrubbed, trimmed and each pickle cut partially down lengthwise (quartered, but not cut apart).
Pack pickles in small crocks that will fit in your refrigerator, or use big clean jar.

Pour hot liquid over pickles in crock, cool and put china plate on top of pickles to hold them down in liquid. When cool, cover with a couple of layers of plastic wrap or aluminum foil; secure tightly with rubber band.
Put in refrigerator to ripen for 2 to 3 weeks.
Delicious and long lasting.
This was my grandmother's recipe.

title: gooey butter squares
directions: Mix cake mix and melted margarine.
Put in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together eggs, cream cheese and sugar.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sift confectioners sugar over top.
Cut in squares while still warm.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Partially boil or bake potatoes; cool and peel.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices and arrange in buttered baking dish.
Make syrup of sugar, water and salt.
Add flavoring and butter.
Pour over potatoes and cook at 325° for 1 hour or more, basting often.

title: fudge cupcakes
directions: Combine sugar, flour and eggs; blend well.
Do not beat.
Melt chocolate and margarine in saucepan.
Add nuts and stir.
Combine chocolate mixture with flour mixture and add vanilla.
Blend; do not beat.
Pour in paper-lined muffin tins.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
The top of the muffin will form a crackle glaze.

title: blueberry pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough in pizza pan and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool in refrigerator.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled cookies. Then spread chilled pie filling on top.
Cut into pizza slices and serve.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large airtight container and stir well.

title: baked shrimp and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute mushrooms in butter for 10 minutes or until tender.
Lightly mix in shrimp and rest of ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake for 25 minutes until golden.

title: chicken tavern style
directions: Blend flour into butter.
Add evaporated milk and liquid from mushrooms.
Add chicken broth to make 4 cups of liquid.
Add turmeric, salt and oregano to liquid.
Cook until sauce is thickened.
Add grated cheese.
In flat baking dish, put 2 to 3 cups of cooked rice.
Layer chicken and mushrooms over rice.
Pour cream sauce on top and top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid in container and fill halfway with water, then add pineapple juice.
Chill punch until ready for use.
Add 7-Up and pineapple sherbet.
This is great for any party.

title: don't peek chicken
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan; set aside.
In a large bowl, mix together the rice, soups, water, garlic, parsley and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour the mixture into the baking pan.
Press the chicken into the mixture. Sprinkle the top with paprika.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except reserving 1 cup of crackers.
Put reserved crackers on top of casserole with a dot of butter.
Cook for approximately 35 minutes at 350°.
Very good!

title: asparagus frittata casserole(makes 4 servings; carb count: 7 grams)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, beat eggs. Add milk and salt; blend well. Pour mixture into greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan; top with asparagus. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 15 minutes or until egg mixture is set.

title: rose petal rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
When dissolved, mix remaining ingredients.
Pinch off small amount and put in greased muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until browned.
This recipe can be kept in refrigerator and used as needed.
Dip out into muffin pan and let set for 10 minutes at room temperature before baking.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump all together.
Mix 10 minutes and bake 1 hour or until done at 325°.
Serve plain or with your favorite icing.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Rinse navy beans. Place in 4-quart pot. Add water, covering beans 3 to 4-inches.
Bring to a boil. Boil 2 minutes. Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 1 to 2 hours. Drain beans and discard soaking water.

Return beans to pot. Cover with 2 quarts of water. Add onion, bay leaf and garlic. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cover. Simmer until beans are tender, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Remove bay leaf.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken-artichoke-cheese spread
directions: Stir together all ingredients in a large bowl until blended. Spoon into a 9x5 loaf pan lined with plastic wrap.
Cover and chill for 8 hours.
Invert chilled mixture onto a serving plate. Garnish if desired, to look like a present using the onion stem as a ribbon and the chili pepper as a bow.
Serve with crackers or toasted French baguettes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook green beans; drain.
Mix with mushrooms, water chestnuts, pimento, soy sauce, soup and melted butter.
Put in a 2-quart casserole.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix with Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle on top of bean mixture.
Bake until bubbly and brown on top, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce(serves 8)
directions: Chop onions, green peppers and celery fine; fry in oil in a skillet until brown and tender.

Fry the hamburg, bacon, salt, pepper and garlic in oil in a separate skillet until cooked. Then mix all these ingredients together. In a soup pot, mix tomato soup with tomato paste. Add the onion, peppers, celery, hamburg, bacon and garlic mixture. Cook slowly for 4 hours. Boil the spaghetti in water until cooked. Drain. Serve sauce on top of spaghetti. Add Italian grated cheese over the top of the sauce and serve with hot peppers, if desired.

title: shrimp appetizers
directions: Melt cheese and butter together over low heat in saucepan. Mix remaining ingredients with cheese mixture.
Using a small spatula, spread over English muffins.
Broil just until cheese starts to bubble.
Cut into small pie shapes.

title: tomato pork chops
directions: Lay pork chops flat in casserole dish.
Place slice of onion on each pork chop.
Add can of tomatoes over top of pork chops. Bake at 350° until pork chops are tender.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Heat together cream of celery soup and cheese until cheese melts.
Mix vegetables and soup mixture together in casserole. Top with crushed Ritz crackers. Bake at 350° for approximately 20 to 35 minutes.

title: almond pound cake
directions: Optional:
Put slivered almonds in pan before you put mix in.

title: first down dip
directions: Microwave process cheese spread and sour cream in small bowl on High for 1 1/2 to 3 minutes or until melted, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve warm with soft pretzels and vegetable dippers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: apple goodie
directions: Mix together and put in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: zucchini and tomato bake
directions: Coat a skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Melt butter and saute onions until transparent.
Add zucchini and tomatoes; simmer 15 minutes, covered.
Sprinkle cheese over vegetables.
Cover and simmer until the cheese melts.
Serves 4. Contains 148 calories and 8 grams fat.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Spread refried beans in casserole dish or platter.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning mix and water.
Cook and stir on medium heat, 10 to 15 minutes.

Spread over refried beans. Arrange layers of lettuce, salsa and cheese on top of meat. Garnish with desired toppings: sour cream, guacamole, black olive slices and jalapeno slices. Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 14 to 16 appetizer servings.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Divide the sausage meat into 6 (4 ounce) portions.
Shell the eggs; dip in flour.
Coat each egg with egg and bread crumbs.
Fry in hot (but not smoking) oil, turning carefully (roll over) every minute or two to cook evenly until browned all over, about 25 minutes cooking time in all.
Cut each egg in half. Serve hot with tomato sauce or cold with salad greens.

title: green bean almondine
directions: Cook 2 tablespoons slivered almonds in 2 tablespoons butter or margarine over low heat until golden, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon lemon juice.
Pour over 2 cups hot, cooked, drained French-style green beans.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender, also cook chicken until done. Grease the bottom of a large casserole dish.
First put in broccoli, then chicken and in another bowl mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and broccoli, then sprinkle grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked country ham with spicy mustard glaze
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place meat, fat side up, on a rack in baking pan; score ham.
Mix remaining ingredients until well blended. Set aside half of marmalade mixture. Brush ham with remaining marmalade mixture.
Roast 2 hours or until meat thermometer registers 140°, brushing with marmalade mixture every 15 minutes.
(Temperature will rise 5° to 10° during standing.) Let stand 10 minutes.
Serve with reserved marmalade mixture. Makes 10 to 12 servings.
Preparation time:
15 minutes plus standing. Cooking time: 2 hours.

title: grandma's homemade noodles
directions: In small mixing bowl, mix flour and salt.
Make a hole in flour.
Put egg in hole.
Add water; mix well.
May need a little more water.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut in strips.
Drop in hot boiling chicken broth.
Can thicken if needed.

title: creamy cauliflower and ham soup
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat.
Add onions and garlic and cook until tender.
Add water, cauliflower, chicken broth and potatoes.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer for 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in ham, 1/2 cup of half and half, chives, white pepper and nutmeg.
In a small bowl, combine remaining half and half with the flour; blend well.
Slowly stir into soup; cook and stir constantly
until slightly thickened and bubbly.
Makes 8 (1 1/4 cup) servings.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Rub potato skins with oil; prick with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until tender.
Allow potatoes to cool to the touch. Slice a small portion off top of each potato.
Carefully scoop out pulp, leaving a thin shell.
In a large bowl, mash the pulp with butter, chives, salt, pepper and enough milk to obtain desired consistency.
Carefully stuff shells; sprinkle with paprika.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Potatoes may be stuffed ahead and refrigerated or frozen.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: banana smash
directions: Mix sugar and water.
Boil 5 minutes.
Cool.
Mash bananas and add lemon juice right away.
Mix everything together except 7 Up and freeze.
Thaw for 1 hour before serving.
Add 7 Up when ready to serve.

title: tater tot casserole (2)
directions: Spread hamburger in bottom of roaster pan.
Top with sliced onions, and then with green beans.	Mix soups and water and pour over the above.
Top with tater tots, do not cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with melted margarine for crust. Put in bottom of a square or oblong dish for first layer.
Add layer of sliced bananas.
Mix Eagle Brand milk with lemon juice and sugar; layer over bananas.
Drain crushed pineapple and mix with chopped pecans.
Pour over Eagle Brand milk mixture.
Whip Dream Whip and spread over this.
Sprinkle Angel Flake coconut over this.
Top with cherries.
Put in refrigerator to set.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: turkey vegetable stir-fry
directions: Stir together cornstarch, ginger, broth and soy sauce until smooth; set aside.
In skillet, in 2 tablespoons hot oil, stir-fry the turkey until browned.
Remove and set aside.

title: country beef pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pat meat mixture into bottom and sides of greased 9-inch pie plate.
Flute sides.
Set aside.

title: german strudel dough
directions: Have Strudel Filling prepared before rolling dough.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add ice. Serves about 25 punch cups.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring first 2 ingredients to a boil; add rice.
Simmer 45 minutes, stirring frequently.
In a bowl mix heavy cream, milk, whole eggs and vanilla.
After first mixture cooks 45 minutes, check and make sure rice is done.
Bring both mixture to
full boil and then let cool before refrigerating.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.

title: walnut bourbon balls
directions: Mix well crumbs, cocoa, 1 cup confectioners sugar and nuts. Add corn syrup and bourbon.
Mix well.
Form into balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Store in covered container a day or so to ripen.
Keeps very well.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: pie crusts
directions: Work Crisco in flour with fork. Sprinkle water around all at once and mix with fork just so it sticks together. Do not touch with hands. Scrape mix into ball. Dump dough on floured bleached cloth or flour sack. Using floured rolling pin, pat down rolling lightly. Start with edge nearest you and roll edge around rolling pin loosely sliding pie plate under. Trim with sharp knife. Slide wooden handle between edge of pie plate and crust to crinkle. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400° or until lightly brown.

title: shrimp bayou oaks
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper.
Add soups and cheeses and stir until blended on medium-low fire.
Add seasonings and shrimp to mixture.
Then add noodles and heat.
Ready to serve.

title: pineapple heart shake
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix well.

title: cole slaw
directions: Cut the cabbage very fine. Cook the vinegar, sugar, oil, salt, mustard and celery seed together until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over cabbage and allow to stand for 6 hours.

title: fried cabbage in the crock
directions: Shred cabbage; brown bacon in skillet.
Put cabbage, bacon, onion salt, pepper and oleo in crock-pot.
Stir occasionally.

title: lasagna
