directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add tomato sauce and paste, whole tomatoes (save the juice), oregano, minced garlic, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Cook lasagna noodles as per package instructions. Place 3 cooked noodles in bottom of low baking dish.
Over this layer, spread sauce to cover noodles, then spread Ricotta cheese, Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese.
Add another layer of noodles, sauce and cheeses and repeat.
Add tomato juice to top layer.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Pour pizza sauce over top and bake 30 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for additional 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, Karo and water; bring to a rolling boil.
Stir in peanuts gradually so as not to lose boil.
Cook until peanuts pop and turn light brown; remove from heat.
Add soda and salt; stir well.
Pour onto a large well-greased cookie sheet.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, 3/4 cup butter and 3 tablespoons sugar. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.

title: very best syrup cake
directions: Place all ingredients
in
mixing
bowl
and beat well. Bake in greased and floured
x 13-inch loaf pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased casserole. Sprinkle lightly with crushed potato chips.
Bake in 325° oven until hot.

title: mexican fiesta dip
directions: Combine sour cream and taco seasoning mix.
Spread refried beans onto a 9-inch serving plate; spoon sour cream mixture evenly over the beans.
Layer with jalapeno peppers and the next four ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Yield:
10 to 12 appetizer servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown turkey
and
onion together.
In a large pot, put rest of ingredients together.
Add turkey mixture.
Simmer for about 30 minutes
to 1 hour.
You can add water if you like it soupier.

title: carrots with grapes(makes 10 to 12 servings)
directions: Scrape carrots, cut into julienne strips.
Place in saucepan with basil and enough water to cover and cook until just tender; then drain.

title: sausage bread
directions: Thaw dough in fridge or microwave (carefully) without letting it rise.
Spread dough over 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Cook sausage; drain well and reserve grease.
Mix in bowl, sausage, eggs, cheese and spices.
Spread mixture over dough.
Beginning on long side, roll dough lengthwise and place on cookie sheet, seam side down.
Pinch ends together and pinch seam together.
Drizzle sausage grease over top and sprinkle with paprika.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit waldorf
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients together well.
Chill thoroughly before serving on a bed of lettuce.

title: holiday mulled cider
directions: Stir ingredients in Dutch oven or large saucepan over low heat for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Do not boil.
Remove cinnamon sticks and cloves.
Makes 16 (1 cup) servings.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: Combine ingredients and toss amount needed with shredded cabbage, carrots and onion.

title: trail mix(make your own)
directions: In a large bowl, combine the cereals, crackers, pretzels, raisins, cashews and dried banana slices. Snack away!

title: rocky road ice cream
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and then pour in ice cream freezer. Finish filling freezer by pouring half and half or milk to the line.
Then start ice cream freezer.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt morsels in top of double boiler; add peanut butter and mix well.
Add corn flakes.
Drop about a teaspoon at a time on cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Let set until firm or put in refrigerator for a few minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: Cook meat; drain off grease.
Cut cheese in chunks.
Melt in microwave.
Add meat, sour cream, salsa and taco sauce.
Put in crock-pot.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Dump together and stir well to coat all the crackers.
Serve.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cool Whip and coconut.
Chill and let set.
Before serving, spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into 1/8-inch slices and arrange on lightly greased pizza pan, letting slices overlap.
Press lightly together to seal.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° until edges begin to brown; top will not be brown.
Blend the cream cheese with whipped topping and add sugar and vanilla; spread evenly over crust.
Arrange fruit attractively over crust.
Pour glaze over all.

title: becky's microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Cook on High 5 minutes.
Mix catsup, mustard and sugar.
Spread over meat loaf.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes on High, uncovered.
Use deep pan (microwave-safe), e.g. glass bread pan.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Combine oil, salt and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over veggies while hot.
Must set overnight.
Keeps 3 to 4 weeks.

title: lazy day stew
directions: Put all ingredients in pot.
Cover and bring to boil.
Reduce temperature to 180° and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
In a cooker, cook for 8 hours with lid on.
May stir in frozen peas for last 10 minutes, if desired.
If thicker stew is desired, stir in 1/4 to 1/2 cup dry potato flakes.
Bring stew to boil again.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook and season meat with taco seasoning and allow to cool. Mix meat and beans.
Chop lettuce, tomatoes and chips and mix with meat and beans in a large bowl.
Stir in bottle of Catalina dressing.
Mix well and sprinkle grated cheese on top.

title: raisin bread
directions: Combine raisins, water and soda; bring to a boil.
Cool completely.
Beat together eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add raisin mixture with flour and eggs.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: white fluffy frosting
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water over low heat.
Stir only until sugar is dissolved.
Then boil rapidly without stirring, to 242° or until syrup forms a firm ball when small amount is dropped in cold water. Add vanilla and salt to egg whites, beating until stiff, but not dry.
Pour syrup slowly in a then stream into beaten egg whites, beating constantly until mixture will stand in peaks and is spreadable.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Beat on low speed until mixed.
Add flour, baking powder and milk, a little at a time.
Beat at medium speed and add extracts.
(Add 1/2 cup chopped black walnuts, if desired.)
Put in well-greased angel food cake pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix and heat all ingredients, except the crackers.
Pour over the crackers.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: california sweet potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise.
Arrange in a shallow baking dish. Sprinkle lightly with salt.

title: deep-dish pizza
directions: In large bowl, mix the first five ingredients well.
In small bowl, mix the remaining ingredients, except flour, well.
Add small bowl mixture to mixture in large bowl.

title: slow-cook round steak
directions: Cut steak in small pieces and brown in oil.
Add chopped onion. Add salt and pepper to taste.
After browned, put golden mushroom soup and Lipton onion soup on top.
Cook, covered, on stove for 2 hours.
May have to add water at times.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: date nut balls
directions: Cook dates, brown sugar and margarine together, stirring constantly.
Cook until sugar dissolves and margarine melts.
Add coconut.
Remove from heat; add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Roll into balls.
Roll balls in granulated sugar, then powdered sugar.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together until potatoes are well coated. Bake at 450° until tender and golden brown.

title: cold turkey salad
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water according to directions; drain and cool.
Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: jiffy and delicious chicken
directions: Combine the onion soup mix, jam and dressing.
Pour over the chicken which has been placed in a heatproof casserole dish with a lid.
Cover and bake at 300° for two hours, basting, if desired. Serve over cooked rice.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain beef well.
Line bottom of pan with Tater Tots.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and sour cream to ground beef.
After layer of Tater Tots, layer of meat and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: beef barley vegetable soup
directions: Dredge the meat in flour.
In a 6-quart Dutch oven, brown meat and garlic in oil.
Add tomatoes, water, barley, Worcestershire sauce, salt, basil and pepper.
Bring to boiling; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 25 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender. Makes about 4 quarts.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually stir in milk.
Blend in dry mustard.
Serve with Salmon Loaf.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Ritz crackers and butter.
Cover with Ritz crackers; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peas and cheese casserole
directions: Mix together soup, onion, peas, pea juice, cheese, Worcestershire sauce and peppers; put 1/2 of mixture in baking dish.
Cover with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake in medium oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating batter hard after each addition.
Melt the chocolate and add to the batter.
Add the flour and the buttermilk, alternating in thirds and stirring only slightly.
Add vanilla and boiling water.
Grease three 9-inch cake pans and dust with flour.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Turn cakes upside-down on rack to cool.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add sour cream, cream cheese and 5 tablespoons margarine and milk.
Place in greased casserole; dot with remaining margarine and paprika.
(Can also add shredded cheese.)
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes at 375°.
Can make a day ahead and store in refrigerator before baking.

title: banana split dessert
directions: In a mixing bowl, toss together graham cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Press crumb mixture onto bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

In a small mixer bowl, beat the remaining 1/2 cup butter about 30 seconds until softened. Add powdered sugar. Beat until fluffy. Beat in eggs. Spread egg mixture over crumb mixture. Slice bananas lengthwise into halves and arrange over egg mixture. Spoon pineapple over bananas. Spread with dessert topping.
Sprinkle with chocolate and nuts. Cover.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Cut into squares and top with a cherry.
Serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla. Mix well.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together. Add nuts last.
Beat until blended.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves (grease pans).

title: 3 bean tofu chili
directions: Heat olive oil in cooking pot on medium high.
Add to hot oil the garlic, chili powder, chili pepper, carrots, onions, bell pepper, celery, tofu crumbles and salt to taste.
Cook until tender (approximately 10 minutes).
Add tomato and molasses.
Cook on low heat until all ingredients are blended together (approximately 5 minutes).
Drain all beans and add to mixture. Continue to cook on low heat until beans are heated through (10 to 15 minutes).

title: hot meat salad
directions: Cook the beef and garlic in a skillet until brown.
Add the next 4 ingredients; mix well.
Add the remaining ingredients except chips.
Mix.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole. Garnish with chips.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: To Make Crust:
Lay out and press together the crescent rolls on a cookie sheet.
Bake and cool.

title: shrimp fajitas with guacamole and pico de gallo
directions: In medium bowl, place shrimp, cilantro, garlic, jalapeno and olive oil.
Marinate 2 to 8 hours.
In large, heavy skillet, place 2 tablespoons of oil from marinade and heat on high until hot.
Add red and green peppers and onions and saute 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove shrimp from marinade and add to skillet.
Saute 2 minutes or until done.
Serve shrimp and vegetables with tortillas, Guacamole and Pico de Gallo.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in casserole dish.
Top with Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix or buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350°
for 40 minutes.

title: easy no-bake chocolate pie
directions: Mix pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk.
Let set 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip and peanut butter cups.
Pour into pie shell.
Replace plastic cover of graham cracker pie crust and freeze overnight. Take out about 15 minutes before serving.

title: billy's junk
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Scoop out into small Baggies.
A great healthy snack!

title: curry vegetable dip
directions: Combine, chill and serve with fresh cauliflower, celery sticks, carrots and radishes.

title: chicken strips
directions: Roll strips of chicken in crushed corn flakes.
(May be dipped in milk first and then in corn flakes.)
Sprinkle with Mrs. Dash salad dressing mix.
Bake on a baking sheet, with a tiny bit of oil, for 20 minutes, at 400°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender. Remove from container and cook egg noodles in the broth under tender. Remove chicken from bones and cut into small pieces. Mix chicken, noodles, soups and sour cream. (Mix in pot noodles were cooked in.) Salt and pepper to taste. Put in casserole and put Cheez-Its crumbs on top. Pour the melted margarine over Cheez-Its crumbs. Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: fluffy fruit dip or "fluff"
directions: Beat together. Spoon over fresh fruit or serve as dip for fresh fruit.

title: vegetable loaf
directions: Bake at 350° in a covered dish.
Bake 10 minutes uncovered.

title: ky cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on large cookie sheet.
Bake according to package directions. Cool crust while creaming the next 5 ingredients.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cooled crust.
Top with your choice of raw vegetables cut into very small pieces. Serve immediately.

title: ravishing rice
directions: Dice celery, onion and pepper.
Saute sausage.
Add vegetables.
Cook a few minutes.
Bring water to a boil.
Add soup and rice.
Cook seven (7) minutes.
Mix with meat and vegetables. Put in a 2 qt. casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Place foil on top and bake covered for 25 minutes; remove foil and continue baking for another 25 minutes.

title: fresh banana-lemon tea bread
directions: In a large bowl, cream shortening with sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Blend in bananas and lemon juice.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Blend into banana mixture.
Stir in lemon peel.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, or until bread tester inserted into center comes out clean.
Remove from pan; dust with confectioners sugar.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: Drain pineapple.
Combine ingredients in large bowl, folding together until blended.
Spoon into decorative serving bowl. Chill.

title: polish easter bread
directions: Melt Crisco in saucepan.
Beat eggs, milk and vanilla together and add to melted Crisco.
Important to keep all ingredients warm but not cooked.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In bowl add flour, salt and sugar together and pour in warm liquids.
Stir together; knead and set in greased warm bowl to rise in warm place.
Wrap well with towels.
Let rise until double in size.
Knead again and separate into 3 greased loaf pans.
Let rise again until double in warm place and well wrapped in towels.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°, then 10 minutes at 300°.
When done remove from pan and brush with melted butter.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and oleo.
Slowly blend in flour and vanilla.
Gently mix in potato chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until barely browned.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: stilton soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan, add onion and celery and fry gently for 5 minutes.
Stir in flour and cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat, stir in wine and stock, return to heat, bring to boil and simmer 30 minutes.
Add milk and cheeses, stirring constantly; season to taste.
Puree in blender and reheat without boiling. Stir in cream and serve with or without croutons.

title: mayonnaise salad
directions: Cut up in layers; do not stir.
Cover with mayonnaise.
Cover tightly and let stand at least 8 hours.
Before serving, sprinkle with cheese and Bac*Os.

title: ranch salsa
directions: Combine the tomatoes with green chiles, olives, green onions, cheese and salad dressing in a bowl and mix well. Chill until serving time. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine; cook 1 minute. Remove from stove and add peanut butter and extract.
Stir in oats and drop by spoonfuls on greased pan or wax paper.

title: heavenly kahlua cake
directions: Make cake according to package directions.
Make pudding according to directions. Make 2 (9-inch) cakes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar,
flour,
spice and salt.
Add vanilla, pumpkin, milk and beaten
egg.
Mix	well
and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: gram's scottish shortbread cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla in large bowl until smooth. Gradually work in flour with a wooden spoon to make a stiff dough; chill 30 minutes.
Roll out on lightly floured surface to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with cutter, or into squares with a knife.
Bake about 30 minutes in a 300° oven; do not overbake. Store in tightly covered container when cold.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine vanilla wafers, sugar, pecans, cocoa, corn syrup, salt, run and vanilla.
Shape into balls and roll in confectioners sugar. Store in tightly covered container.

title: quick easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt oleo or butter and peanut butter and blend together in top of double boiler.
Work in confectioners sugar.
Press into an 8 x 9-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; set aside.
Cook rice.
Mix rice, soups, milk and Cheez Whiz together in casserole with broccoli.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken with sour cream
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender.
Cool and cut up into bite-size pieces.
Combine in greased baking dish: chicken, stock, soup and sour cream.
Follow directions for Stove Top stuffing and spread on top.
Bake, 25 minutes covered and 10 minutes uncovered, at 350°.

title: no-bake bars
directions: In large bowl, combine first four ingredients; set aside.

title: pecan pie #2
directions: Cream butter with sugar; add corn syrup, beaten eggs, salt, pecans and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until firm.

title: granola bars
directions: Combine brown sugar, syrup, vanilla, peanut butter and oleo well. Combine remaining ingredients, then mix with peanut butter mixture. Pat in bottom of 11 x 15 jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool slightly and cut while warm.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix cabbage, carrots, green pepper and onions.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup water and chill.
Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup water.
Mix celery seed, black pepper, salt, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Cool and when slightly thickened, beat in oil.
Drain vegetables and mix with dressing.
Will store long time in refrigerator.

title: chocolate nut bark
directions: Melt chocolate bits in microwave.
Stir in almonds.
Spread thinly over waxed paper covered cardboard or cookie sheet.
Chill until firm.
Break into pieces.

title: whole wheat oat cookies
directions: Beat oil, eggs, salt, honey and vanilla until smooth.
Stir flour, baking soda and spices together, then add to honey mixture. Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on racks. Makes 50 cookies.

title: spinach or broccoli quiche
directions: Put all vegetables in casserole after you have thawed and drained them; cut into small pieces.
Add cubed cheese, cottage cheese, butter and whole beaten eggs and sprinkle with flour.
Mix well; will be kind of globby.
Pour into a deep casserole dish so you have room on top for it to bubble and not run over.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Is good as a leftover the second day.

title: fatoosh
directions: Blend and serve with pita wedges or blue chips.

title: skillet pizza
directions: Mix water, yeast and flour; knead.
Let rise 1 hour.
Spread dough in skillet and add pizza sauce and other topping ingredients.
Top with Danish Havarti cheese (or your favorite cheese).
Cover and cook for 25 to 30 minutes over very low flame or heat.

title: churros
directions: In saucepan, combine water, salt, sugar and butter.
Heat until butter melts.
Bring to a full boil over high heat.
Add flour all at once.
Remove pan from heat.
Beat mix with spoon until smooth, clings together and comes away from side of pan. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg until smooth and shiny.
Stir in lemon extract and cool for 15 minutes.
(Dough can be refrigerated here.)
Fill a large pastry bag with large star on plain tip and fill with half the paste.
Heat the oil 1 1/2-inches deep in a wide pan to 400°.
Start squeezing paste into oil until you have a ribbon of paste about 7 to 9 inches long. Cut it off with a small knife.
Fry 2 or 3 at a time.
Fry 5 to 7 minutes and drain on paper towel.
Roll in cinnamon sugar.

title: cold pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Roll out crescent rolls on a large cookie sheet.
Pat to fill out the sheet, pushing the seams together.
Bake until medium brown.
Let cool.
Mix the cream cheese, which has been allowed to soften, and the dry dressing mix together.
Spread on cooled crust.
Slice the green onions (including the tops) and olives.
Chop the tomatoes.
Arrange on top of the cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, cut into squares.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients in order, 1 at a time.
Pour cake batter into greased and floured pans.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool cake thoroughly.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Let cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: dream bars
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar and flour to a crumbly mass.
Spread it in bottom of 8 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 275° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Mix eggs, brown sugar, vanilla, flour, baking powder, salt, chopped nuts and coconut.
Spread over other mixture and bake at 300° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes. Cool.
Cut into strips.

title: apricot nectar
directions: Mix orange juice as directed on the can.
Add all other ingredients.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Bake pie
shell
at 425° for 8 minutes.
Remove and set aside. Reduce
heat
Brown meat in skillet.
Drain. Add tomato sauce,
pepper, onion and bouillon.
Cook and stir until bouillon dissolves.
Remove
from
heat.
Stir in eggs, flour and
cheese. Turn into prepared shell.	Bake 20 minutes or until hot.
Top with cheese.
Bake 3 minutes.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: egg souffle
directions: Optional:
Can add 2 layers of sauteed sausage or Virginia ham.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Beat eggs.
Add flour and sugar. Stir in pineapple.
Place breadstrips on top.
Pour butter over bread.
Bake in a 9-inch square casserole dish at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Very good with ham.

title: impossible chicken 'n broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch deep dish pie plate.
Mix thawed broccoli, 2 cups of cheese, chicken and onion in the pie plate.
Beat milk, eggs, Bisquick, salt and pepper until smooth, using either blender or hand mixer.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 25 to 35 minutes. Top with remaining 1 cup of cheese.
Bake just until cheese is melted, 1 to 3 minutes longer.
Cool 5 minutes before serving to allow it to set.

title: old fashioned coconut pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine flour and sugar; add salt, milk and egg yolks.
Mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
reduce heat; cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from the heat; stir in vanilla and 1 c. coconut.
Pour hot filling into pie shell.

title: renya's special dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Add taco seasoning.
In a crock-pot, melt cubed cheese, then add the meat and refried beans.
Cook on high for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Keep warm. Serve with any kind of chips.
I use Fritos.
Ro-Tel can be added for a spicier taste.

title: strawberry delight
directions: In a large bowl.
Fix Jello according to package directions. Just as jello begins to thicken, add cake, bananas, pineapple, and strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with nuts. Refrigerate at least 3 - 4 hours before serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with bread chunks, carrot strips, cucumber slices, green pepper strip, broccoli flowerets, etc.

title: 15 minute meat loaf midgets
directions: Mix all ingredients; pack into muffin pan.
Cover with the other 1/2 can of tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve 3 to 4.

title: cheese balls(microwave)
directions: Cut
cheese,
butter and cream cheese in 1-inch pieces. Place in medium
bowl in microwave at 30% power for 1 to 3 1/2 minutes or until slightly softened, stirring and rotating bowl every 30 seconds.
Mash the mixture with a fork until smooth. Stir in onions.
Divide
in
half.
Shape into 2 (3 1/2 inch) balls.
Toll in
a
coating
of
cup
finely chopped nuts. Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Store no longer than 1 week.

title: broccoli balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts. Freeze on cookie sheets.
Transfer to Ziploc bags and store in freezer until ready to use.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until firm and lightly browned.

title: crackling corn bread
directions: Mix flour and meal together.
Add salt, sugar and water.
Stir until well mixed.
Add water, enough to make soft batter.
Mix well.
Add cracklings and mix again.
Grease pan well with 1/2 cup shortening.
Place in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: baked red beans
directions: Dice bacon and fry until crisp; drain off grease.
Add onion and green pepper and cook until tender.
Stir in tomato sauce; simmer 5
minutes.
Put beans in casserole.
Add sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.

title: gram's spanish style swiss steak
directions: Pound flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder into both sides of meat.
Brown in shortening; sprinkle remaining flour mixture over meat.
Add onions, celery, tomato sauce and vinegar.
Cover and simmer 2 hours and 30 minutes.
Sprinkle olives and mushrooms over meat for 15 minutes or longer.
Add water if needed.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 2 1/2 to 3 cup casserole. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: portuguese sweet bread
directions: Mix half the flour and yeast.
Heat milk, sugar, shortening and salt just to melt shortening.
Let cool to lukewarm; add to dry ingredients with eggs.
Mix well and start adding flour.
Mix with hands until dough becomes stiff.
Knead until smooth. Grease tops of dough and let rise until double.
Form into 3 loaves; let double.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: grandma russ' rock cookies
directions: Mix raisins, shortening, soda in hot water and brown sugar together.
Add flour, walnut meats and chocolate chips.
Chill well.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: hot fudge upside-down cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, flavoring, butter and nuts. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased sheet pan.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix grated cheeses together.
Layer cheeses and chilies in 13 x 9-inch pan, ending with cheese. Reserve small amount of cheese for garnish.
Beat eggs, milk and flour with wire whisk until smooth.
Pour over cheese and chilies. Bake for 30 minutes.
Pour tomato sauce over top and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: three-month pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers in a 1/2-gallon jar.
Mix vinegar, alum, salt and spice together; pour over cucumbers; finish filling jar with cold water and seal.
Leave 3 months.
Wash cucumbers in cold water and split.
Heat 1/2 cup vinegar and 4 cups sugar until bubbly. Pour over cucumbers in bowl so you can stir.
Let sit for 24 hours or longer before using.

title: favorite coconut pie
directions: Beat cheese to soften.
Add sugar and then add milk gradually. Fold in coconut and Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze for 4 hours.
Garnish with toasted coconut.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Melt butter in boiling water.
Add flour and salt.
Cook to a smooth paste.
When done, mixture should form a firm ball.
Cool slightly; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one. Put by tablespoon on buttered tin.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: hickory nut pie
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for about 40 minutes or until center is firm.
Do not overbake.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat well.
Add oil and carrots and beat.
Sift together the flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to mixture and beat well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch or 3 layer cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes for 9 x 13-inch and 30 to 35 minutes for layer cake pans.

title: hot chili
directions: Brown, chop and drain ground beef.
Combine all ingredients with ground beef and simmer on low heat for 1 hour.

title: layered fruit salad
directions: Layer 1/2 each of strawberries and banana in a small serving dish; lightly spread with 1/4 of sour cream.
Top with half of pineapple and 1/4 of sour cream.
Repeat procedure with remaining ingredients.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: brisket marinade
directions: Mix well and marinate brisket overnight or 8 hours.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Blend flour, sugar and nutmeg.
Add eggs; beat until smooth. Pour over rhubarb in 9-inch pie pan.
Top with pastry cut in fancy shapes.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kindergarten pizza
directions: Get some cheese and a piece of bread and put sausage on it. It goes in the oven at very hot.
Take it out.
Put it on a plate and cut a triangle.
Then hold it and eat it.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients; spoon into prepared pie crust. Press edges to seal.
Slit top crust; top with egg.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: multi grain muffins
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and let cool.
Add eggs, flour, baking soda, salt and then buttermilk and raisins.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Batter may be stored in refrigerator for future use.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Flour chicken breasts and saute in butter until done.
Remove chicken breasts and set aside.
Clean the pan and place chicken back in pan with butter, garlic, juice of 1 lemon, capers, mushrooms and herbs.
Let reduce until slightly glazed.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: banana split cake 1
directions: Prepare pudding as per box directions; set aside in bowl in refrigerator.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Set margarine and eggs out at room temperature.
Boil sweet potatoes about 45 minutes. Drain and mash.
You may add 1/4 cup milk (optional).
Sprinkle nutmeg on top of pie and place in oven for 1 hour at 350°. (Preheat oven first.)

title: orange-coconut cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add orange rind.
Add juice and flour a little at a time until all is used.
Bake in oven at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix all together in a jar with tight-fitting cover.
Shake well to blend all ingredients and drizzle over fresh fruit salad. Best made in advance of serving.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple with juice and pudding.
Stir until dissolved. Add marshmallows and mix well.
Add pecans and mix well.
Add cool whip and mix well.
Refrigerate over night.

title: rolls
directions: Mix yeast in warm water.
Mix oil, sugar, milk and flour.
Add yeast mixture and mix well.
Pour on waxed paper.
Knead for 3 minutes.
Cover and let rise for 1 hour.
Put on waxed paper and roll dough to 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake in a oven preheated to 450 degrees for 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hungarian "csorge"
directions: Mix all together.
Roll out dough and cut into diamonds.
Make a slit in middle of each diamond and pull one end through the hole.
Fry with pulled side up.
Makes approximately 60.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except grated Colby cheese and crushed potato chips.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch pan. Sprinkle cheese and chips on top.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat egg, applesauce and butter together.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch loaf pan in a moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no-bake peppermint ice cream cake
directions: Cut cake 4 layers.
Chop patties and nuts.
Soften ice cream slightly.
Stir candy, nuts and extract.
Spread thick layer of ice cream mixture between cake layers and rebuild the cake.
Cover top with ice cream mixture.
Keep in freezer, no thawing necessary.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Slice bananas.
Toss in lemon juice to keep from turning dark. Mix other ingredients with bananas.
This will keep for several days in refrigerator.

title: clayton's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan. Bring to boiling point; stir well. Cook 2 minutes. Turn off heat and let sauce cool to room temperature without lid. Sauce will be ready to use.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together real good; pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: veal casserole
directions: Simmer veal in oleo, salt, green pepper, celery, onion and mushrooms, covered, for 20 minutes.
Brown down.
Add milk and thicken.
Put in casserole and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Heat noodles in can and sprinkle over top just before serving, along with the toasted almonds.

title: juicy apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously coat a 9 x 9-inch baking dish with margarine.
Place apple slices in large bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar, 1 tablespoon flour and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Toss to coat, then pour into baking dish.
In medium bowl, combine margarine, remaining 1/4 cup plus 1 tablespoon cinnamon and nutmeg until crumbly.
Stir in oats.
Sprinkle over apples, making sure edges are covered.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until apples are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: escalloped hamburg
directions: Put a layer of hamburg in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put a layer of thinly sliced raw potatoes and onions, chopped fine on top.
Dot with butter.
Alternate layers until dish is full.
Cover with enough milk to moisten and reach top layer.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in hot oven at 400°.

title: spaghetti-pizza casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and place in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine milk and eggs; stir well. Pour over spaghetti. Cook ground beef, onion and green pepper in a large skillet. Stir until beef crumbles; drain well. Stir in spaghetti sauce and spoon over spaghetti. Layer mushrooms and pepperoni on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle with cheeses; bake 10 minutes more or until cheeses are melted.

title: yellow angel food cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat egg yolks thick and lemon colored.
Add water and beat until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in sugar, fold in dry ingredients a little at a time.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff but not dry.
Fold into egg yolk batter; add vanilla.
Bake in 10-inch ungreased tube pan; 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: deep-dish blueberry pie
directions: Stir together 3/4 cup sugar and cornstarch. Toss with 6 cups fresh blueberries and 1 teaspoon grated lemon rind until coated. Turn into deep 1 1/2 casserole. Roll out single crust pastry 1-inch larger than casserole. Cover filling with pastry. Flute edge; cut slits in top. Bake in 425° oven 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly and crust is browned. Serves 6 to 8.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in orange juice and rind.
Measure flour by dip level; pour method or by sifting.
Blend dry ingredients; stir in .
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: wilshire salad cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses and mix thoroughly with mixer.
Add onion and mix well.
Refrigerate.
Shape into ball and roll in nuts and parsley.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Coat a casserole dish with the cooking spray (optional).
Mix all ingredients, then bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir after 15 minutes of cooking.
Continue cooking for about another 30 minutes.

title: low-fat almost fried potatoes
directions: Spray skillet with Pam.
Cook potatoes and onion on medium heat, covered, turning often with spatula.
Season to taste with Mrs. Dash, pepper and Parmesan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix the Miracle Whip and sugar together in a small bowl.

Cut broccoli flowerets into bite size pieces and put in large bowl. Add purple onion, cheese and Bac*Os to the broccoli; mix well. Add Miracle Whip-sugar mixture to large bowl; stir until well coated.

title: mexican dip
directions: Take Frito Lay bean dip and spread on a large round plate. Mix avocados, salt, and lemon juice until smooth and spread on top of bean layer. Mix together sour cream, mayo, and taco seasoning and spread on next. Mix together tomatoes, sharp cheddar cheese, green onion and ripe olives. Spread on top and serve with tortilla chips

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Mix the flour, salt and butter together using your hands, until crumbly.
Add cold water a little at a time until dough barely sticks together.
Form into a ball and roll out on a floured board.
Roll from center toward outer edges.
Put into an oiled pie pan.

title: green pepper cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together. shape into a ball and roll in pecans.

title: pull apart rolls
directions: Thaw bread dough, don't let it rise.
When thawed, cut each loaf into 8 slices and each slice into 4 pieces (64 pieces in all). Spread them in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, 1/2 cup brown sugar, cloves, nuts and Jell-O.
Sprinkle this evenly over dough.
Pour 1/4 cup melted butter over dough.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese supreme
directions: Cook and drain macaroni; add remaining ingredients and place in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: shepherd's stew
directions: Place ingredients in large casserole dish or Dutch oven in the order given.
Cover tightly and bake 4 hours in a 250° oven. Serves 6 to 8 persons.

title: linda's chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken in 4 cups water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Bring to a boil and simmer 45 minutes.
Drain 2 cups of broth.
Chop chicken into small pieces.
Cook carrot and onion in broth; add mushrooms and peas.
Dissolve cornstarch in 2 tablespoons water. Add to vegetables, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat; stir until bubbly.
Add chicken, 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper.

title: peppermint brownies
directions: Beat sugar, margarine and eggs until fluffy.
Add chocolate syrup.
Beat in flour, vanilla and salt.
Pour into greased 10 x 15 -inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes; cool.

title: mrs. gungle's sponge cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Set aside. Combine sugar and egg yolks.
Then add hot water.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg yolk mixture.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for cake.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes for cupcakes.

title: fannie date candy
directions: Combine sugar and milk in saucepan; stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add dates; cook to soft ball stage.
Turn candy onto cold damp towel; roll towel around candy and refrigerate for several hours.
Shape candy into balls.
Dip into lime juice and roll in sugar.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake! Mix Jell-O, boiling water and strawberries.
Stir until dissolved.
Place in refrigerator to cool for 30 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel mixture.
Pour cooled Jell-O on top and refrigerate.
Let set 4 to 5 hours before serving.

title: peach congealed salad
directions: Simmer the first 3 ingredients over low heat until jello is dissolved, then mix with the remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: grandma mag's dumplings
directions: In large bowl combine first four ingredients.
Cut up chicken.
Add to broth in large pot.
Roll dumplings thin.
Add to boiling broth. Cook, uncovered, until tender.
Stir often to prevent sticking.

title: porcupine bread
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, rolled oats, yeast, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Heat buttermilk, water and oil until very warm.
Add to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, gradually add raisins, sunflower seeds, sesame seed and enough flour to make a firm dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic (5 to 8 minutes).

title: strawberry daiquiri
directions: Mix ingredients together and freeze.
Will keep in the freezer for a few weeks.
Makes a great summer cooler.

title: old fashion stew
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Mix meat, vegetables, onion, tomatoes, tomato sauce, and tomato paste.
Add 1 large can of water.
Cook until onions are clear.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mash up Oreo cookies real fine and set aside.
Mix with mixer until smooth the cream cheese, sugar and margarine.
Mix together with the above mixture until thick the pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In a casserole dish, put a layer of pudding mixture, then a layer of cookie crumbs.
Repeat layers, ending with cookie crumbs.

title: hot sandwich
directions: Thaw bread dough and let rise.
Roll out dough in an oblong 9 x 13-inch pan.
In center of dough, put ham, salami and Mozzarella cheese.
Fold both sides in (like a blanket) and crease on each end.
Beat egg white and spread on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes or until light brown. Slice and serve.

title: taco dip
directions: Cream together cottage cheese and seasoning mix.
Add the cream cheese; cream until smooth.
Spread on serving platter. Cover with the sour cream.
Chop the lettuce, tomatoes, black olives, onions (chopped small) and Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle on top.
Cover with Doritos.

title: oven omelet
directions: Heat margarine in a 13 x 9 baking dish in 325° oven until melted. Tilt dish to coat bottom. Beat eggs, sour cream, milk and salt in large mixing bowl until blended.

title: baked eggplant slices
directions: Mix mayonnaise and scallions together.
Spread on both sides of eggplant slices.
Dip in crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 375° oven.
Turn over and bake for 15 minutes longer until tender.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in big bowl.
Pour into 2 pie shells and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned on top and bottom.

title: granolas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine, corn syrup, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and chocolate chips.
Stir in oats.
Pour into rectangular cake pan (smooth mixture down; do not pack). Bake for approximately 20 minutes.

title: potato bundles
directions: Prepare instant mashed potato mix as per directions on box. Add peas, cheese and onion powder.
Mix ingredients together. Open crescent roll. Place spoonful of mixture in center of opened crescent roll.
Fold in the corners to create a "bundle."
Place on cookie sheet and bake until golden brown at 375°.

title: caramel delight bars
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients together and press 3/4 of the mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and pour chocolate chips over mixture.
Combine the 6 tablespoons flour with the caramel and pour over chocolate chips. Sprinkle remaining 1/4 mixture on top.
Bake 15 minutes longer. Cool and cut into bars.

title: lemon (no sugar) pie
directions: Beat pudding and milk in electric mixer until blended well. Add Cool Whip and beat.
Add lemon juice last.
Pour into crusts and refrigerate overnight.

title: no bake cake dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water.
Add 1 cup boiling water and juice from pineapple.
Let cool until it starts to jell. Add pineapple and 3/4 of Cool Whip and nuts; mix.
Crumble 1/2 of cake and put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon half of pineapple mixture over cake.
Crush down until all cake is covered.
Crumble rest of cake over that.
Cover with remaining pineapple mixture.
Spread rest of Cool Whip over all.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate until set.

title: pizza macaroni
directions: Prepare macaroni; drain.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain. Add tomato sauce, 1/2 teaspoon salt and other seasonings.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Beat milk, egg and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Blend with macaroni.
Spread in greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan. Cover with meat; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes, then cut.
Makes 6 servings.

title: watergate cake
directions: Add coconut and pecans to remaining ingredients. Pour in 9 x 13 pan and bake 35 to 40 minutes. Let cool.

title: spanish cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together, then add the whole eggs and two egg yolks.
Add sour milk alternately with the flour. Dissolve the soda in a little of the sour milk.
Sift baking powder with flour.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add egg, butter, orange juice and water.
Mix until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in nuts, cranberries and orange rind; pour into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: pineapple slaw
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: pork roast with pineapple glaze
directions: Place roast, fat side down, on microwave roasting rack in 2-quart glass dish.
Microwave on High 5 minutes per pound.
Turn roast fat side up.
Make several slits diagonally through fat. Pour on half of glaze.
Insert probe; set temperature control to 165° and vari-cook on Roast.
Remove from oven.
Pour on remaining sauce.
Let stand 10 minutes, covered in aluminum foil.

title: cinnamon sticks
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolk.
Beat well.
Add the flour, which has been sifted with the cinnamon.
With your hands, knead the dough in the bowl until the mixture holds together. Spread dough on an ungreased cookie sheet into a 14 x 9-inch rectangle.
(The dough can also be rolled by a floured rolling pin.)
Beat egg white slightly.
Brush onto cookie dough. Sprinkle lightly with the nuts.
Bake at 275° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: crispy crunch sundae
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add brown sugar and heat slowly until blended.
Add crushed Rice Krispies; toss well to coat. Remove from heat and add nuts and coconut.
Save 1 1/3 cups mixture.
Put remainder in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread ice cream on top, then sprinkle with reserved mixture.
Freeze.
Serve cold.

title: cheesy ham sandwich
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together ham, cheese, mayonnaise and onion.
Place 1/3 cup mixture on bottom of each roll.
Cover with top half of roll.
Wrap individually with foil.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and cheese begins to melt.

title: pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add salt and oil, then add flour and mix.
Knead 15 minutes.
Grease pizza pan; dust with corn meal. Spread dough onto pizza pan.
Cover with sauce, cheese and meat. Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 pizzas.

title: italian bean casserole
directions: Brown meat; saute pepper and onion.
Mix with beans and seasonings.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put in roaster; cover with pieces of chicken.
Sprinkle with package of onion soup mix; cover.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and cream well.
Blend in eggs, 1/3 cup peanut butter, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Add flour and oats.
Spread in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 22 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let stand 5 minutes. Spread.
Mix confectioners sugar, 1/4 cup peanut butter and milk and spread on morsels.

title: baked salmon mousse
directions: In blender container, combine 2 eggs, 1 can salmon (drained), 1/3 cup heavy cream, 1 1/3 tablespoons each wine and capers, 1 teaspoon paprika, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Cover and blend 10 to 15 seconds until mixture is smooth, salmon still has texture.
Place salmon mixture in a large bowl.
Repeat blender process twice more with the same volume of ingredients, and add each new mixture to bowl.
Stir in scallions and chopped parsley. Pour salmon into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch glass loaf pan or 2-quart souffle dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 1 hour or until mousse is firm to touch.
This mousse may be served cold.
Cool, chill and then unmold before cutting into slices.
Accompany with horseradish cream made by beating 1 cup heavy cream, horseradish to taste and 1 teaspoon salt.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Combine sugar and honey in large saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring frequently, only until mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter; mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well coated.
Press mixture into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook lasagna.
Cut each strip in 3. Bake sausage links.
Cut each in 2.
On each strip (piece) of lasagna, lay a piece of sausage and a piece of cheese. Roll each one.

title: finger cheese cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk and blend well.
Unroll one package crescent rolls and place in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour cheese mixture on top and place the other package crescent rolls on top.
Froth egg white, brush on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool to room temperature, then refrigerate.
If desired, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Mix all ingredients, except sugar and milk, together loosely.
Boil sugar and milk for 3 minutes.
Pour over mixture and mix well.
Pack in pan of choice (tube, loaf, etc.).

title: the best lasagne
directions: In a heavy 3 or 4-quart pot, brown the meat, onion and garlic in the olive oil.
Add the tomatoes and paste, the mushrooms, basil, parsley, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Cook the lasagne noodles according to the package directions.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Melt Velveeta.
Brown and drain hamburger and sausage.
Add browned meat, melted cheese, Italian seasoning and tomato paste. Simmer 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Spread on bread.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: crock-pot chicken vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in cooker and stir thoroughly.
Cook on low 7 hours, on high 3 1/2 hours, or on automatic 5 hours. Remove chicken pieces from soup.
Discard skin and bones and return meat to soup.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Peel potatoes; cube and cook.
Drain potatoes.
Cube cheese and add to potatoes.
Mix through.
Put lid on pan and let set for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Mash with hand masher.
Cook shells according to directions on box.
Drain.
Cool and stuff with potatoes and cheese mixture.
Saute sliced onions in butter. Layer shells in pan and top with butter and onions.
Slow heat to warm all ingredients.

title: homemade donuts
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add to flour mixture, the milk and canola oil, then drop in the egg.
Mix until texture is somewhat smooth (a bit looser than cookie dough).

title: cheese-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms. Chop stems.
Cook and stir stems, green onions and garlic in margarine until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: rice and black bean salad
directions: Mix all together.
Serve at room temperature.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, reserving small amount of nuts and noodles
to
place	on
top.
Bake	40 to 45 minutes.
You may increase the amount of nuts and leave them whole.

title: hot pineapple side dish
directions: Drain the pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup of the juice; set aside. In a medium bowl, combine sugar and flour.
Add the butter and 1 cup cheese; mix well.
Gently stir in pineapple.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle crushed crackers on top; drizzle with reserved pineapple juice.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly around edges.
Remove from the oven and sprinkle with the remaining cheese.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate cheesecake bars(low calorie)
directions: Preheat 325 F.
Coat 9 inch square baking dish with cooking spray.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler and let cool slightly.
Place wafers or (chocolate graham crackers) in a plastic bag and crush with rolling pin to form a fine crumb. Sprinkle over bottom of prepared pan.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except beef.
Tear beef in small pieces.
Take cheese mixture and roll into ball.
Place beef all around cheese ball.
Chill for a few hours and serve.

title: chinese dressing
directions: Cook Rice a Roni as directed on box except use chicken broth instead of water. Melt 1/2 stick of margarine in a skillet and add bell peppers, onions, celery, sage and mushrooms. Cook until tender. Remove from heat and add to Rice a Roni. Add chicken and salt and pepper to taste. Pour into baking dish. Melt remainder of margarine and drizzle over top. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar gradually until thick.
Add remaining ingredients.

Fill container to 4-inches from top with regular milk or more half and half or whipping cream. Add other flavorings, if desired (2 to 4 cups fresh fruit or 1/4 cup finely ground coffee or instant coffee is yummy).
Makes 2 quarts.

title: tex-mex salsa
directions: In 8-inch skillet over medium-high heat, heat oil; add onion and garlic.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes, stirring frequently until onion is crisp-tender.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.

title: grandma's dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in greased baking dish. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 more minutes.

title: very best egg nog
directions: Sprinkle with nutmeg before serving.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, white sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/3 cup melted butter.
Pour in a greased casserole dish.

title: meat balls to impress
directions: Saute celery, onion and bell pepper with garlic in margarine. Remove garlic cloves.
Mix in large bowl: ground chuck, sausage, cheese, veggies, bread crumbs and egg whites.
Form into meat balls of desired size.
Lightly spray balls with Baker's Joy.
Mix together equal parts Welch's jelly and Heinz chili sauce.
Simmer balls in jelly and chili sauce until done.

title: grandma's barbecue chicken
directions: Mix first ten ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Salt and pepper cut up fryer.
Place in shallow pan.
Pour about half of the sauce over the chicken and place in a 375° oven.
Bake until chicken is tender and brown, basting occasionally with remaining sauce.

title: chicken for two
directions: Skin chicken breasts and dust with flour.
Melt the butter in a skillet and brown the chicken on all sides.
Add the remaining ingredients, cover and cook over low heat for 10 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Remove lid and boil juices down quickly.
Serve over rice.
Makes 2 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cream the butter and mix in the brown sugar.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time.
Add the syrup, vanilla and pecans.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 350°. Bake about 30 minutes or more until filling is set.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in floured, greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: corn bake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon and remove skin and bones.
Mash fine.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Place in greased casserole and bake in moderate oven at 375°, about 1 hour.

title: baked chicken(very crispy and easy to make)
directions: Mix Bisquick, salt, pepper and paprika together. Melt shortening and butter in jelly roll pan. Roll cut up frying chicken into the Bisquick mixture. Place chicken in the melted shortening. Bake for 1 hour at 425°, turning once.

title: western sheet cake
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to boil in saucepan.
Take off stove.
Mix in the remaining ingredients.
Pour into large greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: hot sauce
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Blend in food processor.
Chill before serving.

title: low calorie steak
directions: Brown steak in small amount of cooking oil with chopped onions.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1 or 2 cups hot water.
Pour over steak.
Simmer until tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: baked shrimp
directions: Melt oleo; add other ingredients and pour over shrimp in baking dish or casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, depending on size of shrimp.
Serve sauce in separate bowl to dip shrimp and bread in.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Separate 1 of the eggs.
Beat the white with the 1 tablespoon of water; brush over partially baked crust and set aside.

title: parmesan rounds(about 120 appetizers)
directions: Preheat broiler.
Using slicer, cut baguettes into 1/2-inch slices.
Butter one side of bread.
Arrange in single layer on baking sheet.
Broil until lightly toasted.
Turn and broil unbuttered side until lightly toasted.
Transfer to rack and cool.

title: easy chicken fricassee
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in a large skillet.
Dredge chicken in flour; saute until golden brown.
Remove from skillet. Set aside.
Mix remaining 2 tablespoons of margarine in same skillet.
Add carrots and mushrooms and saute until tender. Combine soup mix and remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add chicken; reduce the heat and simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water with a teaspoon of oil.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Drain at least half the water off the macaroni.
Mix with meat and both cans of soup.
Mix well.
Put slices of cheese on top.
Put in oven at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Makes a large casserole!

title: potato soup
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; crumble and set aside.
To bacon grease, add potatoes, onion and carrots.
Add enough water to cover the vegetables and boil until potatoes are tender. Meanwhile, melt butter in sauce pan then add flour and stir until smooth; cook about 1 minute.
Add milk all at once, blending until smooth then cook until mixture thickens, add to cooked vegetables. Add more milk if you like thinner soup.
Just before serving, add reserved bacon and garnish soup with grated cheese.

title: pumpkin ice cream
directions: In a large bowl, stir together all ingredients except ice cream. Add ice cream in large spoonfuls, stirring until well blended. Spoon mixture into 9 square pan, cover and freeze for at least 3 hours.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on package. Mix Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut in a bowl. Pour mix over cake as soon as it comes from the oven. Let cake cool completely. Spread Cool Whip on top and sides of cake. Sprinkle with coconut. Keep refrigerated.

title: edith's kentucky pie
directions: Mix all above ingredients by hand and pour into pie shell. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Brush graham cracker pie crust with melted butter or margarine; set in refrigerator while preparing filling.
Blend together cream cheese and powdered sugar until creamy.
Add peanut butter and 12 ounces Cool Whip; beat until fluffy.
Pour mixture into chilled pie crust; top with additional 8 ounces Cool Whip. Let stand in refrigerator at least 3 hours before serving.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Beat egg with 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Combine flour, garlic powder and paprika.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then flour mixture.
Saute chicken in margarine in a skillet.
Dissolve bouillon in boiling water and add remaining lemon juice.
Add to skillet.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken and onion; bone, skin and set aside.
Mix together and bring to a boil the soup, Ro-Tel, chilies, broth, salt and garlic.
Fry tortillas and tear in half.
Layer half of tortillas, half of sauce, half of grated cheese and all of chicken, cut in medium size pieces.
Then layer other half of tortillas, half of sauce and half of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes in a 2-quart dish.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all together put in
9 x 13 pan. Bake 350 for 25-30 minutes.

title: mexican cabbage
directions: Brown the first 3 ingredients and drain the fat. Add remaining ingredients and cook until the cabbage is tender.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients together, add eggs and butter, mix in rhubarb.
Pour all into pie shell and top with lattice work crust.
Brush top with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, lower temperature to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown meat with onion; drain.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste and whole tomatoes along with oregano, minced garlic, salt and pepper. Simmer 1 hour.
Place 3 noodles in bottom of deep baking dish.
Over the noodles, spread sauce, then spread Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Layer more noodles, more sauce, more cheeses.
When all ingredients have been layered, add tomato juice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach dip for chips
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate. Makes 4 cups.

title: fuzzy cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, vanilla and flour. Blend.
Roll into balls the size of a hickory nut.
Place on cookie sheet.
Make depression with finger.
Fill with jelly. Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook rice and shrimp.
Melt butter and add raw vegetables and simmer.
Add cheese to hot rice and mix until melted.
Add all ingredients; place in baking dish and cook until bubbly all over or about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift flour once, then sift into bowl with baking powder and salt.
Add shortening and milk and mix lightly.
Knead 10 seconds on a lightly floured board and roll out to 3/4 inch thickness. Shape with floured cutter.
Arrange on greased pan.
Bake at 450° about 12 minutes.
Serve hot.
Yield:
16 biscuits.

title: texas caviar
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Serve with corn chips.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients except marshmallows and put mixture in a greased casserole dish.
Bake 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover the top with marshmallows. Return to oven just until marshmallows begin to melt and brown slightly.

title: quesadillas
directions: Butter each flour tortilla.
Spread cheese generously.
Dot salsa or layer tomatoes.
Cover with tortilla.
Continue to layer until ingredients are finished.
Bake at 350° until crisp and cheese is bubbly.
Slice into triangle wedges.
Serve with hot sauce and sour cream scoops.

title: cheese cake surprise
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk.
Add vanilla.
Sprinkle chips and pecans on the bottom of pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture on top.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Chill at least 3 hours or until pie is set.

title: scratch cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add unbeaten eggs and vanilla; beat thoroughly.
Sift flour and baking powder, add mixture alternately with milk to sugar mixture.
Pour into well-greased pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) or layered pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: sue's salmon
directions: Place salmon steak in the middle of foil.
Sprinkle liberally with Old Bay Seasoning Mix. (Cover the whole salmon with seasoning.)
Place slices of lemon on top of seasoning, then onion slices and finally tomato slices.
Fold the foil around the salmon and crimp the edges.
Place on the barbecue with foil seams up and let steam for 1/2 hour.
Yummy!

title: cheese spread for triscuits
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients until smooth. Add next 4 ingredients; stir together with spoon. Spoon into 2 dishes or 1 large compote or dish. Top with chopped pecans. Freezes well. Served best with Triscuits.

title: glennis chicken casserole
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to package directions substituting reserved chicken broth for water.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan or larger, stir the chicken pieces, Rice-A-Roni and the soups (undiluted) together until evenly blended.
Mix crackers and margarine and put on top of casserole.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes until crackers are golden toasted.
(Freezes very well before baked and before crackers and margarine are added.)

title: wanda's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine vanilla wafer crumbs and margarine; press into bottom of lightly greased 8-inch pie plate.
Line sides of pie plate with whole vanilla wafers.
Gently press into bottom layer.

title: fight that fat potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients in 4-quart saucepan.
Cook until potatoes are tender; or longer, if you like them thick.
Tastes like buttered potatoes.
Almost no fat.

title: chocolate chip "pizza" cookie
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy; add vanilla.
Stir flour, salt, chocolate chips and nuts into beaten mixture.
Press into pizza pan.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool 15 or 20 minutes.
Turn out onto large tea towel.

title: tamale loaf
directions: Saute pepper and onion; add rest of ingredients.
Stir and place in greased casserole.
Bake at 325° to 350° for about 1 hour.

title: maple-walnut fudge
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with foil.
Lightly grease foil.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour butter into a 9-inch square pan; set aside.
Combine flour and next 7 ingredinets; spoon into prepared pan.
Arrange peaches over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: pumpkin custard pie
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add all ingredients, except margarine. Melt margarine and add to other ingredients.
Pour into 10-inch pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Turn down oven to 325°, bake 30 or more minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and flour together, add vinegar.
Mix well.
Cook on stove top until mixture becomes clear, stirring constantly.
Add drained beets and turn in sauce until coated with mixture.
Simmer approximately 30 minutes, turning beets several times.

title: temperance toddy
directions: Combine ingredients in a large saucepan and bring to a boil. Serve hot in cups.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: pink salmon croquettes
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Heat oil in deep skillet or pan.
Drop mixture with small spoon.
Cook until golden brown.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups hot water.
Add cold water, bananas, crushed pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill until gelled.
Cook sugar, flour, egg and pineapple juice until thick.
Allow to cool and spread cooked mixture over gelatin.
Whip cream and blend with cream cheese.
Beat until light.
Spread over second layer. Sprinkle grated cheese on top.

title: angie's potato salad
directions: Peel, cube and boil potatoes until cooked but firm.
Drain potatoes and put in a large bowl with chopped eggs.
Add celery seed, mustard, pickle relish, mayonnaise and sliced green olives (drained), saving some to garnish the top.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir and pour into serving bowl.
Garnish the top with sliced green olives and paprika.
Serves 12 people.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Combine all ingredients together with fingers or pastry blender until well blended. Roll into small balls, about the size of marbles (and marbles are quite small, by the way!).
Place 1-inch or so apart on cookie sheets and bake 5 to 8 minutes in preheated 425° oven.
Makes 10 to 12 dozen. Tastes like cheese puffs.

title: orange potatoes
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
While potatoes are boiling, cook onions and butter in covered pan about 25 minutes.
Mash potatoes. Add orange juice, onions and creams.
Beat well.
Top with orange zest.
Place in casserole and heat in oven until hot.

title: shrimp meuniere
directions: In large skillet crush garlic with salt to a paste.
Add butter and oil; heat.
Add shrimp and fry gently, stirring often, for 5 to 10 minutes (until done).
Remove from heat; add lemon juice and garnish with parsley.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Combine remaining ingredients and put in baking dish.

title: mag crump's apple bread pudding
directions: In buttered baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch) layer half the bread crumbs.
Combine applesauce, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Spread this over crumbs.
Layer remaining crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Combine eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Pour over bread mixture. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° about 55 to 60 minutes or until comes out clean.

title: cheese and beef casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in tomatoes, cheese, macaroni and seasoning.
Put in greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt margarine and add crumbs.
Top casserole with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all together well and put in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Dilute all of the above with stock (broth) until well moistened. Let set 20 to 30 minutes for spices to "come out." Right before putting into large (at least 13 x 9-inch) greased pan, add 2 eggs to mixture. Bake at 375° until edges are browned and center set.

title: corny corn
directions: Mix all together except margarine.
Pour into an 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Thinly slice 1 stick margarine over top. Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: mimi's fudge
directions: In a saucepan, melt together the milk, sugar and chocolate and bring to a boil, stirring gently.
Let the mixture boil over medium heat until the foam subsides, about 15 minutes.
Drop a small amount into a cup of ice-cold water.
If you can form it into a ball, the mixture is ready for the next step.
Beat in the butter until the mixture thickens and loses its sheen.
Beat in the vanilla.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch buttered pan and chill.

title: just like fresh corn
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in greased casserole.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: vegetable baked fish
directions: Place 1/2 of vegetables in baking dish.
Season fish with herbs, salt and pepper.
Place on top of the vegetables.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix Monterey Jack, 1 cup Cheddar cheese, onion, sour cream, parsley, salt and pepper.
Save.
Heat tomato sauce, water, green pepper, chili powder, oregano, cumin and garlic to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered 5 minutes. Pour into ungreased pie plate.
Dip each tortilla into sauce to coat both sides.
Spoon 1/4 cup cheese mix into each tortilla; roll tortilla around filling.
Put into ungreased baking dish (12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch).
Pour remaining sauce over enchiladas. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Can garnish with dairy sour cream and sliced olives or lime wedges if desired.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix biscuit mix with milk.
Have dough the same as you would for biscuits.
Mix sausage and cheese in mix.
Bake 2-inches apart at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Saute meat and onion together until meat turns white.
Pour over fat drippings.
Grease skillet as for regular corn bread. Heat and sprinkle with dry corn meal.

title: grandmother's best pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour in crust. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 40 pound brownie
directions: Cook pudding according to package directions.
When it reaches the bubbling stage, add the dry cake mix and stir until blended. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle on the chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool and frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, tomatoes, mushrooms, peas, cheese and onions in 2-quart serving bowl.
Spread dressing over onions, sealing to edge of bowl; cover.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Garnish with crumbled bacon and additional cheese if desired.

title: old fashioned raisin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Boil raisins in the water for 5 minutes.
Add shortening and stir until melted. Add sugar, eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Blend in flour and spices.
Stir in pecans.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
While warm, spread with frosting.

title: chicken (or turkey) asparagus au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: graham cracker surprises
directions: Bring butter, margarine and sugar to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Spread whole graham crackers on 2 foil lined cookie sheets in one layer.
Pour syrup mixture over graham crackers. Spread to cover all crackers.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: apple yam delight
directions: Mix together brown sugar, flour and oats. Cut in butter or oleo until evenly mixed and crumbly.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except margarine and crackers, in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake 45 minutes in 300° oven.
Mix margarine and crushed crackers; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until golden brown.

title: ranch style mexican casserole
directions: Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place 6 tortillas on bottom. Then layer meat, beans (undrained) and remaining tortillas torn up on top.
Mix soup and chopped Ro-Tel tomatoes together and spread over tortillas. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: heavenly fruit
directions: Mix whipped cream and sugar.
Add rest of the ingredients. Serve on sliced angel food cake.
Put whole strawberry on top of each.

title: spaghetti salad(prep. time: 30 minutes)
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Makes a large bowl.
Yields 8 servings.

title: eggplant and chicken
directions: To prepare chicken, cut it and brown it.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fold in 3/4 pound strawberries.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: hearty casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter or margarine until transparent; push aside. Add ground meat, salt and pepper; brown slightly.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Spoon into a 2-quart casserole. Cover. Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix together first 8 ingredients.
Spread in slightly buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together crushed corn flakes and melted margarine.
Sprinkle over top of potato mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: crispy chicken alfredo and rice
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions. Brown chicken on both sides in an oiled skillet on medium heat (make sure chicken is done). Empty rice in medium saucepan; add pesto and alfredo sauce. Over low heat, gently heat through. Serve rice with crispy chicken. Garnish with cheese, fresh basil and pine nuts, if desired. Serves 4.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Remove old maids from popcorn and keep warm in a 250° oven while syrup is cooking.
Combine butter, brown sugar, salt and corn syrup.
Bring to boil and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour syrup over popcorn and nuts. Stir mixture gently to mix.
Then separate out and pour on 2 large baking sheets and place in oven at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Store in airtight containers.

title: granola
directions: Mix and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 300°.
Turn often.
Bake until light brown, about 40 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: horseradish dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients well. Cover and chill.

title: jello mold
directions: Combine Jell-O, hot water and cold water.
Add whipping cream, mayonnaise and crushed pineapple and mix with mixer.
Fold in cottage cheese.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: poor man's goose(4 to 5 persons)
directions: Mix the flour and seasoning together.
Cut the meat into even-sized pieces and roll them in the seasoned flour.
Place in a pie dish with layers of sliced onion and sage.
Peel the potatoes and half-cook them.
Cut them in thick slices and place over the top of the meat.
Three-parts fill the dish with water; cover with greased paper and bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 1 hour. (WCB)

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, first sugar and margarine.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 6 minutes, then cool.
Mix until fluffy cream cheese, second 1/2 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over crumbs.
Chill.
Dissolve 2 packages of Jell-O in water and berries.
Chill until it starts to set, then pour and spread over other 2 mixtures.
Chill well.
Serve after 24 hours.

title: bread for dressing
