directions: Mix and bake like cornbread.
When cool, crumble and add chicken broth and 1 tablespoon of poultry seasoning or sage.
Bake dressing as you desire.

title: beef-tip with mushrooms
directions: In an electric frypan, heat to about 300° and melt butter. Pour in beef tips and cut pan down to 250°.
Cover beef with water and cook slow for about 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Let boil dry.
Mix gravy as directed on package.
Pour in mushrooms.
Let beef tips, gravy mix and mushrooms cook for about 15 minutes on low, then serve.

title: squash fluff
directions: Cook onions in butter.
Mix cracker crumbs, milk, salt, pepper and cooked onions into squash and fold in beaten eggs.
Pour in a greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple, reserving juices.
Add water to juices to measure 2 cups.
Place in saucepan and bring to a boil; pour over gelatin in large bowl.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved. Stir in sherbet until smooth.
Chill until partially set (watch carefully).
Fold in oranges, pineapple and bananas.
Pour into 6-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Add crushed cashews and noodles.
Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: chili con carne
directions: Cook and drain ground beef.
Add onion and cook covered, stirring frequently, until onion appears clear.
Stir in chili powder, salt and pepper; cook 1 minute.
Stir in tomatoes with their liquid, minced garlic clove, kidney beans and tomato sauce. Cook over high heat until boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring often.
Serves 8.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix all.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours, or until done.
Baste with sauce and turn balls while cooking.

title: hot herb bread
directions: Slice bread 1-inch thick.
Blend butter, parsley, oregano, dill and garlic.
Spread on bread.
Shape Reynolds Wrap foil around bread, leaving top open.
Sprinkle top with cheese and parsley. Heat for 10 minutes in 400° oven.
Serve hot.

title: peanut butter divinity
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and water. Bring to boiling.
Cook to hard ball stage (260°), stirring only until sugar dissolves.
In large mixing bowl, beat egg whites to stiff peaks.
Gradually pour syrup over egg whites, beating at high speed on electric mixer.
Add peanut butter and beat until candy holds its shape, about 3 or 4 minutes.
Test candy by spooning a small amount onto waxed paper.
Mixture should mound rather than flatten out.
Quickly drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed 5 minutes.
Ad sugar, then pumpkin and lemon juice.
Sift all dry ingredients.
Fold into egg mixture. Add nuts.
Place a sheet of tinfoil on 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet. Grease foil with cooking oil.
Pour and spread mixture on foil and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and while still hot, powder the front side of mixture with powdered sugar and turn over on a tea towel.
Pull off tinfoil and powder that side also. Start at one end and roll both towel and dough up.
Let cool for one hour, then unroll.

title: low-fat tallerine
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Cook turkey in oil in skillet, then drain off grease.
Place all ingredients in casserole dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: bean bake
directions: Drain tomatoes, reserving juice.
Brown beef in skillet; season with salt and pepper.
Add tomato juice; simmer until evaporated.
Saute onions in shortening until yellow.

title: crock-pot supper
directions: Put round steak into crock-pot.
Add cream of mushroom soup, water, salt and pepper.
Cook on medium heat.
Serve over hot cooked noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: two minute fudge(microwave)
directions: Stir together first five ingredients until all liquid is absorbed.
Slice stick of margarine around top of mixture. Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into wax paper lined glass pie plate.
Chill for 2 hours in refrigerator or 30 minutes in freezer.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Open kidney beans and pour into a sieve or colander.
Rinse under cold running water.
Drain well.
Put in a jar.
Cover completely with wine vinegar.
Add a garlic clove if you wish. Cover and store in fridge.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Lightly grease a large baking dish.
In saucepan melt butter and saute onions and garlic (3 or 4 minutes). Stir in green chilies.
Add soup and sour cream.
Mix well. Reserve 3/4 sauce.
To the remaining 1/4 of the sauce in a saucepan add chicken, 1/2 of shredded cheese.
Fill tortilla with mixture, roll up and place seam side down in baking dish.
In bowl combine sauce with milk.
Spoon over tortillas.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry jello cake
directions: Add water to cake mix and Jell-O.
Beat ingredients.
Add oil. Beat.
Add egg whites.
Beat.
Add strawberries.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 2 (9-inch) cake pans (2 layers).

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat together pudding and 1 1/2 cups milk and then add 1 can sweetened condensed milk.
Put in freezer for 10 minutes, then add Cool Whip and sour cream.
Layer with vanilla wafers and bananas.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix corn syrup and sugar in boiler.
Place over heat.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly; boil just long enough to melt sugar thoroughly.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and cornflakes.
Drop with spoon on waxed paper.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Saute onions in 4 tablespoons margarine until soft.
Stir in flour.
Add water and cook over low heat.
Stir until thickens and boils.
Blend in cheese and combine sauce in broccoli.
Add eggs and mix gently until blended.
Cover with bread crumbs and dot with remaining margarine.
Bake in an 8 or 9-inch square pan at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa in 3-quart bowl.
Add milk and butter. Do not stir.
Microwave at 100% power for 2 minutes; then stir well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until blended.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch dish.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut into squares.
Freezes well.

title: meat pie
directions: Put meat in pan with onions and cinnamon. Cook until meat is browned.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until crust is done and golden brown.
Can be served in thin slices with mustard and salad on the side.

title: jambalaya
directions: Use a large, heavy Dutch oven and begin by melting butter. Cook sausage and ham and when browned, stir in flour.
Add onions, garlic and rice.
Cook, stirring, until onions are wilted.
Rice will not be done.
Add all other ingredients, stirring after each. The pot should be slightly soupy.
Rice will absorb most of the moisture.
If too dry, add a little water or broth.
Jambalaya is done when rice is cooked, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift cornmeal and flour together.
Mix in buttermilk; add egg. Melt your oil unless Crisco oil is used.
Let your oil heat in pan.
Mix into your bread mixture.
Pour in pan and bake at 450° until done.

title: nacho rounds
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Cut potato vertically into 20 slices. Place in single layer on greased baking sheet. Brush each slice with taco sauce. Sprinkle with chilies and cheese. Bake 25 minutes until potatoes are tender and cheese is golden brown.

title: apple dessert
directions: Pour filling in cake pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over filling. Slice oleo into small pieces over cake mix.
Sprinkle top with nuts.
Bake 35 minutes at 375°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: world's fastest lasagna
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Spray with Pam.
Put a thin layer of sauce.
Lay strips of tortillas covering sauce.
Sprinkle with browned meat and then cheese mixture.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Top with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Blend together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Makes 1 pie.

title: autumn soup
directions: Brown beef in hot fat in a heavy kettle.
Add onions; cook 5 minutes more.
Add water, carrots, celery, potatoes and seasonings.
Mix thoroughly.
Bring to boil; cover.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes; cover and simmer 10 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: honey dew biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in greased and floured muffin pans.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pear cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken until tender; let cool.
Remove meat from bones. Cook spaghetti in 2 cups water or leftover chicken broth.
Set aside.
Saute onions and peppers in oleo.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add tomatoes and chicken and mix.
Stir in cooked spaghetti; add peas last.
Fold in evenly.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly hot.
Makes a 3-quart casserole.

title: lemon cheese pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350 about 25 - 30 minutes.

title: grape lemonade
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Chill for 1/2 hour. Serve in each glass a slice of lemon.
Pour over lemons and add ice.

title: eggplant in hummus
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Fry onions and garlic in oil.
Remove onions and garlic, set aside.
Add eggplant to oil.
Stir and fry.
Add chickpeas, stir well.
Add onion mixture.
Add tomatoes, lemon juice and salt.
Cook 15 minutes.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Blend all ingredients together and roll dough into small balls. Place on cookie sheet (not greased). The finished product is a cheese wafer that has a nutty flavor. Bake at 375° about 15 to 18 minutes or until brown. Depends on oven.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Be sure it is mixed well. Pour into greased casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Cut carrots 1-inch thick.
Cook in salted water about 20 minutes.
Drain.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and ginger in small saucepan.
Add orange juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in butter. Pour over hot carrots, tossing to coat evenly.
Serves 4.

title: tuna franks
directions: You will need aluminum foil for wrapping buns.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix and spoon into ungreased muffin pan.
Bake at 400°.
Makes 6 rolls.
For more rolls, double recipe.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapples.
Mix sour cream, coconut and marshmallows.
Fold in drained fruits and mix.
Set in refrigerator several hours before serving.

title: toffee
directions: Mix and beat butter and sugar over medium heat until candy thermometer reaches 290° or hard crack stage, approximately 15 minutes after it bubbles.
Sprinkle 1/2 pecans on wax paper or cookie sheet.
Pour brown sugar mixture on top of nuts.
Brush candy bars on top and let melt.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts. Let cool and break into pieces.

title: mud pies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Pour in milk.
Stir and bring to rolling boil for 3 minutes.
Take off heat; let cool for 2 minutes. Quickly add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Stir until thick.
Place spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool, then eat!

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Drain fruits and mix juices with eggs, sugar and flour.
Bring to boil.
Mix with macaroni, fruit and Cool Whip.
Let stand overnight.
Keeps up to 2 weeks in fridge.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Partially cook lima beans and broccoli; drain.
Mix all ingredients together in baking dish.
Top with 3 cups Rice Krispies browned in 1/4 cup butter.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine and stir into pretzels and 1/4 c sugar.
Press into 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cream sugar and cream cheese together.
Fold in whipped cream and spread over cooled pretzel mixture.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Top with bread crumbs.

title: dutch apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together margarine and sugar; add and beat well the eggs and vanilla.
Combine separate the flour, soda and salt; add dry ingredients alternately with sour milk or orange juice.
Fold in apples and walnuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan for 55 minutes or until loaf test done.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay crescent rolls flat in a large jelly roll pan.
Press edges together.
Bake according to directions.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese (room temperature) with mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Chop finely all the vegetables.
Mix chopped vegetables into cream cheese mixture and spread over cooled crescent rolls.
Sprinkle top with 2 cups shredded Mozzarella or Cheddar cheese.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil macaroni; add salt and 1 tablespoon oil.
Drain macaroni and stir in tuna and onion. Slice cheese and layer on top.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: yeast bread
directions: Cold weather (warm mixing bowl with hot water).
Measure into mixing bowl warm water and yeast.
Add, stirring to dissolve, lukewarm liquid, half of flour, sugar, salt and shortening.
Beat with spoon until smooth and batter falls from spoon in sheets. Using your hands, mix in enough remaining flour until dough cleans bowl.
Turn onto lightly floured board and cover.
Let rest 10 to 15 minutes.
Knead until smooth and blistered (about 10 minutes). Round up in greased bowl and bring greased side up.
Cover with cloth.
Let rise in warm place (85°) until double (about 1 hour). Press 2 fingers into dough.
It will leave indentation when dough is doubled; punch down.
Let rise again until almost double (about 30 minutes).
Divide into 2 parts and round up cover.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into loaves and let rise.
Bake at 425° (hot oven) 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pecan pie(chess pie)
directions: In a large bowl of an electric mixer, at medium speed, beat together until smooth the cream cheese, 1 egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread over the bottom of the pastry shell. Sprinkle with the pecans.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Mix all together and place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: light, thin buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Pour batter onto a heated, greased frypan or griddle (approximately 375°).
Serves 5 to 6.

title: pickled hot peppers
directions: Wash and slice enough hot peppers to fill 9 or 10 pint jars. Fill jars with peppers and mix sugar, vinegar and bread and butter pickle mix. Bring mixture to a boil and pour in jars over peppers. Seal. Process in canner for 10 to 15 minutes with boiling water.

title: another broccoli casserole
directions: Place frozen broccoli flowerets in medium casserole.
Drizzle 1/2 of melted butter over flowerets.
Pour melted Velveeta cheese evenly over flowerets.
Cover cheese with crumbled Ritz crackers. Drizzle other 1/2 stick melted butter over cracker crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon butter
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and lemon juice and rind until well mixed. Cook in double boiler and stir until it thickens.
Add butter last.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Do not drain kraut.
Mix all ingredients. Store in refrigerator for about 8 hours to get your best flavor. The longer it sits, the better the flavor. Some people think it's a different type of slaw.
The pimento, while it has its own flavor, makes it very pretty.
If more sweetener is needed, use your own measurements.
Serves 6.

title: cheese balls
directions: Soften cheeses at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients and roll into balls, then roll balls into chopped walnuts.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in large pan.
Boil until tender, making sure to keep plenty of water above chicken.
Once tender, remove chicken and debone; remove unwanted skin.
Breaking into small pieces, add back to broth.
After bringing back to a boil, turn to medium heat.
While chicken is boiling, add bouillon cubes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Now add dumpling slices to broth slowly, allowing the dumplings to cook in the hot broth.

title: oyster stew
directions: Strain oyster liquor into saucepan. Heat, but do not boil. Heat milk in double boiler. Stir in hot oyster liquor. Add butter, seasonings and oysters. When oysters puff and are crinkled at edge, serve at once. Serves 6.

title: dutch oven chicken fry
directions: Melt margarine in a 14-inch Dutch oven.
Dip chicken in egg mixture
and
then	pancake mix.
Season to taste.	Bake 1 1/2 hours
with
coals
on top and 12 coals on the bottom. Replenish coals if needed.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Place sugar, butter and milk in pan.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Add cocoa, oatmeal, vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Beat quickly, while hot, and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Wait 5 minutes before serving.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: This recipe is usually doubled, because it goes fast.

title: swiss honey butter
directions: Cream butter with honey.
Slowly add whipping cream, beating constantly until mixture is fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pennsylvania dutch pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Beat water, egg and vinegar together; stir into flour mixture.
Shape into 3 balls.
Chill.
Turn out on floured board; roll to fit pie pan.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes in a 425° oven.
Yield:
Pastry for 2 (2 crust) pies.

title: double chocolate chocolate pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix and milk in saucepan.
Add butter and chocolate.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full bubbling boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into shell and chill for 3 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping and chocolate curls, if desired.

title: grandma's crumb cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix together first 4 ingredients into coarse crumbs.
Take out 3/4 cup crumbs and set aside.
To the remainder of the crumbs, add the egg, milk and baking soda.
Beat hard to mix well.
Put in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle the dough with the 3/4 cup crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Good warm or cold; it stays fresh for 3 or 4 days.

title: taco soup ala cornwell
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in frying pan.
Mix all other ingredients in soup pot and add taco seasoning and ranch seasoning. Once ground beef is brown, add to soup mixture and bring to a boil. Simmer until soup reaches desired consistency.
Place Fritos and shredded cheese in each bowl and pour soup over -- EAT!!

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Mix all above
ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan or dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until done. Remove from oven and while still hot, pour glaze on top.

title: shrimp orleans
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until tender, but not brown.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Spread on top of melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: game day skins
directions: Bake potatoes and cool slightly.
Cut baked potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out potato, leaving a 1/4 inch shell.
Place potato shells on ungreased baking sheet.
Top each half with cheese and bacon bits.
Bake in a oven heated to 425 degrees for 5 -10 minutes until heated through.
Serve with sour cream.

title: oven fried chicken #2
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Dip chicken in dressing; dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Place, bone side down, in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: bbq brisket
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together, lay brisket in foil and pour mixture over and wrap tightly.
Store in refrigerator for 12 hours before cooking at 300° for 5 1/2 hours.

title: oreo pie
directions: Finely crumble up Oreos. Mix all except 1/2 cup of cookies with melted butter.
Spread this in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix half of the Cool Whip into cream cheese.
Put this on the Oreo crust. Mix the pudding and milk.
Add on top of the cream cheese mixture. Use other half of Cool Whip and spread over pudding.
Sprinkle the remainder of crushed Oreos on top.
Then refrigerate.

title: bean salad (no mayonnaise)
directions: Combine all ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: mexican bean loaf
directions: Drain liquid from beans.
Run beans through food grinder with the cheese.
Saute onion in butter.
Combine beans, cheese, bread crumbs, onion, eggs and seasonings.
Pack firmly into a buttered baking dish; cover with bread crumbs and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Garnish with green pepper rings and serve hot with heated tomato sauce.

title: lazy dazy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and let stand 20 minutes.
Cream butter and both sugars.
Add oats mixture to creamed ingredients. Then add eggs and vanilla.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour three each. Cream sugar and shortening with hot water. Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and soda and mix in alternately with milk. Add flavor last. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 to 25 minutes.

title: favorite chili
directions: Boil beans in triple their water for 10 minutes.
Let simmer on low for 1 1/2 hours.
Put all ingredients in slow cooker.
Stir to combine.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours (high for 3 to 4 hours).

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Wash and skin chicken, salt and pepper to taste.
Roll in the buttermilk, one piece at a time, then cover with flour.
Put 1/2 inch of oil in frypan; let it get hot.
Place chicken in it, one piece at a time.
Keep turning until both sides are a golden brown.
Cover pan and cook on medium-low heat for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs, pudding and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour and baking soda.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 8-10 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl; toss.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce.
Add to chicken mixture mixing well.
Spoon mixture into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish sprayed with vegetable spray.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle evenly over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken in butter and roll in cheese and bread crumbs until coated.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish; cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil for the last 15 minutes of baking time.
Serves 4.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Tear bread into chunks and put in a large bowl.
Beat eggs and add can of soup.
Mix in dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread.
Mix well and pour into an 8 x 10-inch casserole dish.
Top with sausage.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.
Make night before serving.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats; let it stand for 20 minutes.
Cream the sugar and margarine.
Add unbeaten egg, vanilla, soda, salt and cinnamon which have been sifted together.
Bake in greased cake pan 45 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter; add seasoning packet from corn bread mix.
Add celery, mushrooms, water chestnuts, chicken, half of soup, 1/2 can water and half of corn bread crumbs; mix well.
Cover with other half of soup, 1/2 can water and other half of corn bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Heat water and sugar until sugar dissolves, stirring constantly; cool.
Add all other ingredients in a large bowl; stir and freeze in containers.
When ready to serve, take out a container of punch and pour ginger ale on top a little at a time. Break up with a potato masher until slushy and serve in a punch bowl.

title: mocha angel food cake
directions: Dissolve coffee in warm water and use this mixture as part of the liquid when preparing cake according to package directions. Fold in maple flavoring.
Bake and cool as directed.

title: sinful brownies
directions: Place unwrapped caramels in a small saucepan with 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly until all candy is melted.
Set aside to cool.

title: womens guild punch
directions: Mix orange juice, lemon mix and a little water until dissolved.
Add pop and ice, pour into punchbowl.
Add several scoops softened sherbet just before serving.

title: linguine salad
directions: Mix all together. Keep cool.

title: baked beans for 100
directions: Place bacon in a roasting pan.
Brown.
Do not drain.
Add onions to bacon; cook until tender.
Add beans, catsup, brown sugar and mustard to bacon-onion mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 1 to 2 hours until browned.

title: rhubarb nut bread
directions: Stir ingredients together in order given.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans, filling 2/3 full.
Strew topping evenly over each. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes (do not overbake).

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix everything together cold (no cooking).
Let stand overnight at room temperature.
Put in jars and keep in refrigerator.
Happy eating!

title: oven pork chops
directions: Layer potatoes and cheese in baking dish.
Place browned chops on top of potatoes and cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer onions in butter, then place over chops.
Pour soup over ingredients; add milk.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries in blender.
Mix 1 cup sugar with them and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, drain berries and pour pineapple over.
When well drained, add to grapes and walnuts. Whip cream firm and mix all together.

title: papershell pecan pie
directions: Chill pie shell for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: summer fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme with a mixer.
Chill and serve with fresh summer fruits.

title: venison jerky
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1 gallon jar.
Put jar in refrigerator to marinate overnight.
Shake jar frequently to evenly coat meat.
Next morning, drain meat on paper towels. Laying drained strips on wire rack in oven, heat at 100° to 150° for 8 to 10 hours, until dry.
Turn off heat and let cool on racks with door partly open.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Put into buttered dish. Sprinkle top
with 3/4 cup shredded Cheddar cheese and 1/2 cup crushed Ritz crackers. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: easy sandwiches
directions: Peel and chop the eggs.
Place in a bowl along with the carrots and onion.
Stir in the mayonnaise, salt and black pepper. Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Spread filling on 4 slices of bread.
Top with remaining slices.
Cut sandwich in half.
Use a toothpick to skewer each sandwich
with a cherry tomato.
Makes 4.

title: cheese soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, melt butter and saute carrots, onions and celery for 8 to 10 minutes. Sprinkle in flour and seasonings; blend well. Add chicken broth; stir until thick and smooth. Reduce heat to simmer. Add cream, sherry and cheese. Stir until cheese melts. Serve garnished with chopped parsley or chives.

title: low-fat cheese cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend on high for about a minute.
Pour into the crusts.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour (until tops are golden brown).
Let cool in oven, then chill.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cookie mix, contents of peanut butter packet from mix and egg whites in large bowl.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Press in ungreased 13 x 9 x2-inch pan. Sprinkle peanuts over dough.
Press lightly.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes or until golden.
Cool completely.

title: country potato salad
directions: Peel, cook and dice potatoes.
Sprinkle sugar and celery seed on potatoes; add little bit of mustard to potatoes.
Combine onion, pickle relish, celery and salad dressing; mix well.
Add mixture to potatoes and refrigerate.

title: quick beef stew
directions: Combine oil and beef.
Brown in Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until onions and potatoes are tender.

title: hungarian pork goulash
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine until soft.
Add pork, 1 cup water, tomato juice, paprika and salt; stir well.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours until very tender.
Mix flour and 1/2 cup water, stir into stew until thickened.
Stir and blend Bisquick and milk. Drop by teaspoonfuls into simmering gravy and cook 10 minutes. Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: chocolate-strawberry mousse cups
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening in top of double boiler over hot water. Remove from heat, but keep top over warm water.
Spread thin layer of chocolate over insides of 12 pleated foil cupcake liners.
If sides of cups are thin, place in muffin pan cups. Refrigerate 1 hour or
until firm.
Coat a second time.
Extra chocolate can be used for dipping strawberries.
Gently peel foil from cups.
Keep refrigerated until ready to fill. Puree strawberries in blender. Transfer to saucepan. Sprinkle gelatin and 2 tablespoons of the sugar over top.
Place over low heat. Stir to dissolve gelatin and sugar. Transfer to large bowl. Place over ice water, stirring often, until mixture begins to thicken.
Beat egg whites until foamy. Beat in remaining 2 tablespoons sugar, a tablespoon at a time, until meringue forms soft peaks.
Beat cream in another bowl until stiff.
Fold whipped cream, then meringue into strawberry mixture.
Pipe mixture through large decorating tube into each chocolate cup.
Chill. Garnish with chocolate dipped strawberry, if desired.
Makes 12 servings.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for approximately 25 minutes at 350°.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, milk and molasses in heavy saucepan. Heat to boil over low to medium heat.
Boil for 2 minutes or until sugar is completely melted.
Have remaining ingredients ready; when sugar is melted, remove from heat and immediately add remaining ingredients.
Stir only until blended; spoon-drop onto buttered cookie sheet.
Allow to cool and enjoy.

title: light and fruity pie(diabetic)
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water.
Add ice cubes; stir until gelatin is thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Using wire whip, blend in whipped topping; whip until smooth.
Fold in fruit.
Chill, if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into pie crust.
Chill 2 hours.
Serve.

title: a bailey's dream(adults)
directions: Fill blender with the French vanilla ice cream; blend until soft.
Add Bailey's Irish Creme to taste and blend.
Serve in a stem glass with a strawberry on the rim!

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating constantly.
Add flour and salt and mix well. Add vanilla.
Bake in a tube pan at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini cake(or bread)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes at 300°.
Turn off heat and leave cake in the oven 10 more minutes.
This same recipe will make 3 loaves of bread.

title: cookies in a jar
directions: To Prepare Cookies:

Heat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine egg, water and vanilla. Mix well. Add contents of jar. Stir with fork until stiff dough forms. Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 13 to 16 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet. Remove. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: sausage cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream the sausage with sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg. Sift dry ingredients together. Add alternately with orange juice.
Add applesauce. Fold in raisins and nuts last. Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours. Let stand 15 minutes before removing from pan. Keep refrigerated.

title: coconut pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and butter.
Mix well.
Add eggs, pecans, coconut and vanilla.
Mix all together and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pizza muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In a large bowl combine dry ingredients. Add cheese. In a small bowl, beat egg with fork. Stir in milk and oil. Pour into flour mixture. Mix with fork until blended, batter will be slightly lumpy. Pour into lined muffin pan. Bake 25 minutes. Makes 1 dozen.

title: brownies
directions: Stir cocoa and baking soda in mixing bowl.
Blend in 1/3 cup melted butter.
Add boiling water; stir until mixture thickens. Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining 1/3 cup melted butter; stir until smooth.
Add flour, vanilla and salt; blend completely. Stir in chips and nuts.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely; cut into bars.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, chopped onion, chicken broth and water in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in soups and milk.
Heat thoroughly but do not boil.
Yield:
2 1/2 quarts.
Garnish to personal taste.

title: fruited chicken breasts(microwaved)
directions: Mix 1 cup orange juice and rind.
Pour over chicken. Let stand 1 hour at room temperature, stirring occasionally.

title: jello whip
directions: Bring to boil crushed pineapple, 1/2 cup sugar and 2 large boxes of orange Jell-O.
Stir well, take off of stove.
Put in freezer to set up as Jell-O should; not freeze.
Take out, put in extra large bowl.
With large spoon stir in Cool Whip, then add well drained fruit cocktail.
Stir lightly.
Serves 15.

title: chicken with sun-dried tomatoes and artichokes
directions: Season chicken with salt.
Coat with flour; shake off excess. Heat oil in skillet.
Add chicken; cook per side until no longer pink throughout.
Add wine to skillet; cook 30 seconds.
Remove chicken and cover.
Add broth, artichokes and dried tomatoes. Bring to boil.
Stir cornstarch mixture into skillet; boil 4 minutes until reduced to sauce like consistency.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with parsley and pepper.

title: creamy mushroom chicken
directions: In pan, slightly brown chicken.
Separately brown butter. Saute garlic, onion and tomatoes until well cooked.
Add the chicken and broth and simmer until chicken is tender.
Remove from heat and arrange in Pyrex dish.
Strain sauce.
Melt butter in skillet; blend flour, wine, carrot, mushroom soup, butter, mushrooms and strained sauce.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cool and cover with creamy mashed potatoes.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes uncovered until top is golden brown.

title: crystal candy
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup in a large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in food coloring.
Continue to cook, without stirring, until mixture reaches hard crack stage or 300° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and stir in oil of cinnamon.
Working rapidly, spread mixture onto oiled 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Let cool. Break into pieces.
Yields 4 dozen pieces.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix and freeze in a gallon freezer.

title: molasses cookies
directions: *Ground cloves can be added.

title: three cheese enchiladas
directions: Combine 1 cup Monterey Jack cheese, 1 cup Cheddar cheese, cream cheese, 1/4 cup picante sauce, the peppers, onions and cumin; mix well.
Spoon 1/4 cup cheese mixture down the center of each tortilla.
Roll and place, seam side down, in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon remaining picante sauce evenly over enchiladas; cover with remaining cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot. Top with lettuce, tomato and black olives.
Serve with additional picante sauce, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Mix all together and bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bride's pink punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar with hot water.
Dissolve Kool-Aid in cold water.
Mix Kool-Aid and Jell-O together.
Put in a gallon jar and add pineapple juice.
Finish filling gallon jar with cold water.
Chill until serving time.
Pour into punch bowl adding ginger ale and sherbet.
You can make any color with this punch. Use the same flavor Jell-O as you do Kool-Aid.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and oil.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with fruit to egg mixture.
Pour into 16 x 11 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, hot sauce and vinegar.
Put in baking pan.
Sprinkle dry dressing mix.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes, or until browned.
Turn once.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Save
juice
from
peaches and pineapple. Mix juice, sugar,
cornstarch
and
white
syrup.
Boil
until clear. Add gelatin to hot mixture.
Cool and pour over fruit. Then add about 4 bananas, cut in fairly large pieces.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cream margarine; add eggs, sugar and bananas.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: child's play popsicles
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, Kool-Aid and sugar in hot water.
Add the cold water and freeze in ice cube trays.
After adding ingredients to ice cube tray, place a piece of Saran Wrap on top of tray and place toothpicks in for sticks.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blanch broccoli in microwave until tender.
Cook rice.
Saute onion in butter.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Bake, covered, in microwave for 20 minutes.
Uncover to brown another 10 minutes.

title: pineapple bean bake
directions: Combine beans, onions, horseradish and mustard in shallow baking dish.
Slice corned beef hash into 8 slices and arrange with pineapple slices on top of beans.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Dot with butter.
Bake for about 25 minutes at 400°.
Serves 4.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and salt.
Pour over all other ingredients. Keeps in refrigerator for weeks.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Microwave Cheez Whiz slightly. Then mix together with vegetables and mushroom soup. Place in casserole dish. Melt margarine and combine with crushed crackers. Spread over vegetable mixture and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until browned

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Soak the cucumbers and lime in water to cover. Let set overnight.
Rinse and soak in ice water for 2 hours.
Make syrup to cover using 1 part sugar and 1 part vinegar (about 5 pounds sugar and 1/2 gallon vinegar). Soak in syrup overnight.
Add pickling spices and heat (do not boil).
Put in jars and seal while hot.

title: dutch babies
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Put 9 to 10-inch ovenproof pan or skillet into oven to preheat.
Melt butter in pan or skillet as it heats.
Mix together and beat until no lumps remain the eggs, milk, flour and salt.
Pour into preheated pan or skillet.
Cook 20 minutes.
Serve immediately with syrup, jam, whatever.
Dutch Baby should be puffed and slightly brown on top.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients with beaten egg yolks in bowl; mix well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Spread in greased casserole.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yields 6 servings.

title: easy autumn cider
directions: Heat cider in a large kettle on medium heat until simmered. Add cinnamon balls to hot cider.
Stir until melted.

title: cowboy soup
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion.
Drain.
Add beans, soup and tomatoes; heat.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Melt together the margarine, taco sauce, catsup, lemon juice and barbecue sauce.
Put chicken on grill and continue basting with the above sauce until done.
Salt and pepper chicken.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix together soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Put a layer of frozen peas in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Cut up chicken and place on top of peas. Put sauce over the chicken.
Cover with a layer of grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Blend dry ingredients.
Stir in.
Mix in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Make cake according to directions on box.
Bake cake.
When cake is done, make slashes through cake.
Mix jello with one cup boiling water.
Pour over cake.
When cool, mix pudding mixes as directed on box.
Put on cake, then cover with Cool Whip.

title: browned butter cookies
directions: Put butter into heavy skillet and slowly heat until butter is browned, about 5 minutes. Turn into mixing bowl. Beat the butter with the sugar, egg and vanilla until light.
Add flour and baking powder, stirring to make a stiff dough. Shape into little balls, using about 1 level tablespoonful of dough for each. Place on cookie sheet.
Press center down with thumb to make an indentation. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until cookies are firm, but not overly browned.
If they are overbrowned, cookies become very hard.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: I do not measure any of my ingredients.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone; layer in casserole dish. Heat chicken soup and broth; pour over chicken.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken chutney salad
directions: Toss together first 5 ingredients. Combine remaining ingredients. Stir into chicken mixture. Serve on greens.
Serves 4.

title: boiled dinner
directions: In a large soup pot, put ham bone.
Add water to cover.
Slice cored cabbage into 4 sections and add in.
Add bay leaves, allspice and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until almost done (cabbage begins to get soft).
Add potatoes, carrots, onion and season.
Add vinegar if desired.
While cooking, make sure there is enough water at all times to cover vegetables.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Make paste with the cocoa, food coloring and water. Set aside. Cream Crisco and sugar well. Add eggs and cream well. Add food coloring and cocoa mixture. Gradually add flour and vanilla. Mix well. Remove beaters. Add the vinegar. Mix with spoon or spatula well. Add the soda; mix well with spoon or spatula. Pour into greased and floured cake pan, 9 x 11. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean in 350° oven.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Separate the chicken wing drumsticks from the wing tips.
Deep fry the chicken in medium-hot peanut oil 5 to 8 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: corn baked bailey
directions: Warm to scalding first 3 ingredients; separate egg whites and beat stiff.
Add vanilla and salt and set aside to add last.
Beat egg yolks and add to warming milk/corn plus sugar and cornstarch, stirring frequently; fold in whipped whites.
Bake 1 hour at 325° in 2-quart buttered casserole.
Enjoy!

title: french dressing
directions: Put ingredients into a quart jar and shake until well mixed. Add equal amounts of vinegar and oil until jar is filled.
Shake well.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together egg, oil and sugar.
Combine the rest of ingredients.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Pour into loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: Combine.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: rice and sour cream
directions: Heat to boiling, first 4 ingredients.
Add Minute rice; remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes.
Add sour cream, stirring until rice is covered.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: jello salad
directions: Drain a little of juice from pineapple but not all.
Dissolve jello into boiling water.
Add pineapple, strawberries and nuts. Pour half into a 9 x 13-inch or so pan.
Put in refrigerator until firm.
When firm, spread sour cream on top, then pour remaining jello on top.
Place in refrigerator until firm.
Enjoy!

title: gigi's nachos
directions: Lay tortilla chips flat on a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Melt cheese and add chili (in a saucepan or in the microwave).
Dip nachos in sauce or pour on top of tortilla chips.

title: bridge tease
directions: Put half of the wafer crumbs in bottom of 8 x 10-inch pan. Cream butter and powdered sugar until fluffy.
Add beaten egg yolks, then fold in beaten whites.
Spread this (fluffy hard sauce) over crumbs.
Sprinkle most of almonds on top of this, reserving some for top layer.
Crush berries and mix with sugar. Spread on top of other layer.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla to whipped cream and top berries.
Sprinkle on remaining almonds and crumbs.
Cover with waxed paper.
Chill for 12 hours.
Cut into pieces.
Lift out one piece at a time to serve.
Do not try to unmold all at once.

title: christmas salad deluxe
directions: Mix the jello with the cottage cheese in a bowl and the rest of the ingredients.
Refrigerate at least two hours or longer. Can be served in a bowl or put in a pan and cut in squares.

title: busy night chicken lo mein
directions: In skillet over medium-high, saut chicken with butter for 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. Stir in 2 cups of water and vegetables; bring to boil. Stir in pasta with seasoning; return to a boil. Reduce heat to medium. Gently boil, uncovered, 4 to 5 minutes, until pasta is tender, stirring frequently. Stir in teriyaki sauce and let stand 3 minutes before serving.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and place in buttered dish.
Add topping:

title: cheez whiz casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Add onion and green pepper; simmer for 10 minutes.
In a saucepan, add soup, cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Stir until smooth.
Boil noodles as directed on package.

title: chocolate mix (for coffee)
directions: Mix all together very well.
Keep in a sealed container.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons to a cup of coffee.

title: pesto
directions: Put basil into blender.
Add rest of ingredients, except cheese.
Finely chop, punching down as needed.
Add additional oil, if necessary, to attain a loose paste that is not too soupy or runny.
Remove from blender into bowl.
Add cheese.
Great over pasta, fish, bread, etc.

title: lazy fruit pie
directions: Melt a stick of oleo in a Pyrex dish.
Make batter with sugar, flour, milk, baking powder and salt.
Pour batter on top of butter.
Then pour on can of fruit.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Batter will rise to form a crust over fruit.
Serve warm with dip of vanilla ice cream.

title: survivor dip*
directions: *This dip makes a great dinner for two while watching Survivor!

title: devil's food cake(red)
directions: Cream butter; slowly add sugar.
Cream thoroughly.
Add well beaten eggs and soda, dissolved in a little hot water.
Also add cocoa, mixed with a little hot water.
Alternately, add sour milk and flour.
Mix to smooth batter; add vanilla.
Bake in moderate oven 35 to 40 minutes.
Use Boiled Frosting, same as frosting for Angel Food Cake.

title: taco casserole
directions: Mix all together and cook in saucepan until cheese melts. Pour over bag of taco flavor Doritos.
Bake about 5 minutes until bubbly at 400°.

title: fudge scotch ring
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips with milk over hot water in double boiler until chips melt and mixture starts to thicken. Remove from heat; add chopped walnuts and vanilla.
Blend well. Chill about 1 hour until mixture thickens.
Line bottom of a 9-inch pie plate with a 12-inch square of foil.
Place 3/4 cup walnut halves in bottom of pan forming a 2-inch wide ring.
Decorate with rest of walnut halves.
Chill in refrigerator until firm enough to slice.

title: mixed pickle
directions: Simmer water, vinegar, sugar, salt, mustard seed and turmeric 5 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple (1 cup). Dissolve pudding with juice of pineapple. Stir in pineapple, marshmallows and Cool Whip. Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan and refrigerate.
Cut in squares and serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Boil the sugar, vinegar and spices together for 20 minutes. Place a few peaches at a time in the syrup and cook until tender. Pack in clean sterilized jars.
Cover with lids (sterilized) after covering peaches with syrup.

title: cake dessert
directions: Beat egg yolks slightly in top of double boiler.
Stir in 3/4 cup sugar.
Slowly add lemon juice.
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly, for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatine, dissolved in water, mix well and cook slightly.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites until peaked; gradually add 3/4 cup sugar. Beat well by hand; fold into custard.

title: potato soup
directions: Fry bacon.
Add celery and onion.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add thyme, potatoes, salt, pepper and enough water to cover potatoes. Simmer until potatoes are soft.
Stir in hot milk and flour. Simmer 5 minutes.
Can use leftover mashed potatoes instead of raw ones.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Combine eggs, strawberries, nuts and vegetable oil mixing well.

title: lemon loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well.
When the batter is smooth, pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: potato hors d'oeuvres
directions: Wash potatoes and steam until fork-tender.
Cut off a thin slice on the bottom of each potato to allow it to sit without rolling.
Cut off a thin slice on top of each potato and scoop out the inside "meat" of the potato.
Reserve the inside of the potato.
Poach the mushrooms in a saucepan with the dill, parsley, apple juice and lemon juice for 5 minutes.
Pour off liquid.
Put mushrooms and potato "meat" in blender and chop until fine.
Stuff potato skins with mushroom filling.
Sprinkle with cheese. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chop suey
directions: Drain vegetables and bean sprouts, reserving liquid.
Measure liquid and, if necessary, add water to make 2 cups.
Cook rice and water until water is absorbed, stirring occasionally.

title: crab cutlets
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour and add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add salt, pepper, beaten egg, celery salt and onion and cook until thick.
Remove spines from crab meat and add to first mixture.
Chill for several hours.
Form into cakes or cut into small steak-shaped pieces; dip into flour, then spread generously on both sides with mayonnaise and roll in crumbs.
Brown in hot butter.
Serve with creamed peas, cheese sauce and lemon wedges.
Serves 6.

title: corinne's (easy) finger-lickin' chicken
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Add chicken pieces and cook until brown.
Turn flame down and add soup and wine.
Cook, covered, 30 to 40 minutes.
Add onions.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: monkey bread cake
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces and place in Baggie with sugar and cinnamon and shake.
Melt 1 stick margarine and 1 cup brown sugar.
Dribble over biscuits in well-greased Bundt pan. Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch spectacular
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts for pie crust.
Pat in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: garlic cheese bread
directions: Combine Parmesan, oregano and parsley; mix well and set aside. In a large mixing bowl, beat butter and garlic.
Gradually beat in oil until smooth.
Spread over one side of bread.
Place, with buttered side up, in greased, large, shallow baking pans.
Top each slice with 1/4 cup Mozzarella.
Sprinkle with Parmesan mixture.

title: summer fruit with yogurt honey sauce
directions: Combine peaches, grapes, strawberries and blueberries in a large bowl.
Sprinkle fruits with sugar and lemon juice.
Toss.
Let stand, covered, for 1 hour.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Roll ground beef into bite size balls.
Mix chili sauce and grape jelly in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add enough meatballs to cover bottom of pan.
After meatballs have cooked about 5 minutes, remove from sauce and add another batch to cover saucepan.
Continue until all have been slightly cooked, then place all back into pan and cook, uncovered, about 40 minutes on simmer.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix carrots, bell pepper and onion; put in casserole dish. Blend remaining ingredients together and pour blended sauce over the carrots, pepper and onion.
Marinate for 3 days.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: no knead cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Blend in egg.
Add flour; mix until well blended.
Cover and let stand 15 minutes.
Roll out dough on floured surface into rectangle.
Spread with butter, 1/4 to 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon. Roll as for jellyroll.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Put in greased pan.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: okra-corn-tomato medley
directions: Saute onions in margarine until tender.
Add okra and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Cover and simmer about 15 more minutes or until corn is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese and brown sugar together, then add vanilla and fold in peanuts.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Cook in double boiler the first 2 ingredients until chocolate chips are melted.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Chill until set about 1 hour.
Store in refrigerator.

title: shoe peg salad (relish)
directions: The corn, beans and peas are drained.
Chop onions and green pepper.
Put first 6 ingredients in large bowl.
Next, bring last 6 ingredients to a boil and pour over vegetables.
Mix; keep in fridge overnight.
Keeps 10 days to 2 weeks.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent roll wedges and place on a cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Bake crust at 375° for 8 or 9 minutes.
Cool at least 10 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break the spaghetti into short lengths and cook in boiling, salted water until tender. Drain and cool. Place in a bowl. Add the eggs, celery, pickles, onions, cheese and parsley and mix. Combine the mayonnaise, salt, pepper and vinegar.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together; set aside. Separate eggs.
Beat the yolks, milk and oil together.
Add dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Beat egg whites fairly stiff and fold in.
Heat griddle before greasing it.
Pour batter onto griddle, using a 1/4 cup plastic measure cup.
I cut this recipe in half for two.
You may mix dry ingredients the night before to save time.
Full recipe makes 18.

title: fork cookies
directions: Mix together in order given and stir well. Roll in balls the size of a walnut and press down with fork. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool.
Freezes well.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients with sufficient water to make a stiff dough.
Place in a covered bowl and let set for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Pinch off small balls and work out into large circles.
Fry in deep hot fat until golden brown.
Serve with butter, syrup, jelly, vegetables or meat.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put frozen
hash browns in large pan.
Put green onions on top.
Sprinkle
with
salt
and pepper.
Pour 1/2 of melted butter on
top.
Heat
together
soup,
cheese and sour cream. Pour
over potatoes.
Mix
corn flakes with remaining butter. Sprinkle on top.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Uncover last 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda. Combine butter, sugars and pudding mix in bowl; beat until creamy. Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in oats and raisins. Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy does it spaghetti(crock-pot)
directions: Brown beef well in skillet and place in a crock-pot.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 7 hours or on high for 3 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in 8 x 8-inch pan or iron skillet in 350° oven.
Coat pan with margarine.
Mix other ingredients until blended.
Pour batter into hot pan.
Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes.

title: old salem pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix wet ingredients thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients just until blended.
Put in muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Cook onion in a small amount of butter.
Stir in broccoli, soup, cheese, eggs and onion.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes; cool.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Spread on crust and refrigerate.
In large saucepan, cook to a rolling boil the remaining 6 ingredients, stir constantly.
Remove from heat and let cool, stir occasionally, then spread on top of cream cheese mixture; refrigerate.
When firm, spread on 3/4 of an 8 ounce carton of Cool Whip, sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: brown sugar chewy brownies
directions: Mix Bisquick, sugar, eggs and water.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lime cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate until set.
Makes a fine salad for any meal.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter.
Cream until smooth.
Add powdered sugar, beating until light and fluffy.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Sift directly into the pan:
sugar, flour, salt, cocoa and baking soda.
Add vinegar, vanilla, salad oil and cold water.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, stir until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: harold's famous peanut brittle
directions: Butter one large baking sheet; set aside.
In iron pan, combine sugar, syrup and water.
Cook over medium-high heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Add raw peanuts and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches hard-crack stage.
Add butter and mix until well combined.
Sprinkle baking soda over mixture, stirring constantly.
Immediately pour mixture onto prepared baking sheet.
Hold sheet at angle to make candy spread.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients in a 2-quart Corning Ware deep casserole dish. Bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry-peach cobbler
directions: Combine pie filling and cranberry sauce in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Set aside.
Combine cake mix and spices.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly; stir in pecans.
Sprinkle over fruit mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chicken divine
directions: Place broccoli and chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In small bowl, mix soup and mayo.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and beat well.
Add other ingredients. Will be thick!
Bake in Bundt pan for 45 minutes to one hour at 350°.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in large mushrooms.
Bake 15 minutes.
Put a slice of bacon over top.
Place in buttered pan with 1/2 cup water.

title: vanilla fruit dip
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill.
Serve with fresh fruit (strawberries, apple, bananas, etc.)

title: baked turnips
directions: Peel and slice turnips thin.
Cook in a little salted water, barely covering.
As soon as they are barely tender (do not overcook), drain and mash.
Add milk, margarine, salt and sugar. Put in greased casserole.
Add bread crumbs and cheese.
Put into 375° oven, about 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: blueberry betty
directions: For serving:
vanilla ice cream or frozen yogurt or sweetened whipped cream can be used.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: In saucepan scald milk.
Add other ingredients.
Heat over low heat until thickened and well blended.
Pout into pre-bake pie shell.
Beat meringue from 2 egg whites and 4 Tbsp. sugar.
Top pie.
Bake until browned.

title: water chestnuts with bacon
directions: Cut bacon and water chestnuts into halves.
Wrap water chestnuts with bacon slice.
Secure with toothpicks.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes; drain.
Combine catsup, sugar and Worcestershire sauce in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Combine sauce and water chestnuts in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add water and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Pour batter into well greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool cake in pan for 15 minutes, then turn onto plate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs, onion, salt and pepper in bowl.
Stir in cooked broccoli.
Put all in baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Prepare stuffing mix with melted butter to hold together. Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sorrel soup
directions: Heat butter and stew vegetables for 6 minutes gently.
Add potatoes and water and simmer for 25 minutes.
Stir in cream and serve.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Add 2 cups of chopped meat, if desired (bacon, ham or shrimp).

title: cornbread salad
directions: Prepare cornbread as on package and bake.
Crumble cornbread as mix together with other ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Dip balls into chocolate using toothpick.
Drain on wax paper. Makes 200.
Store in freezer.

title: scalloped potatoes with ham
directions: Combine milk, cream cheese, salt and pepper in a saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until creamy.
Remove from heat, then add flour.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix well, roll into balls, press flat with wet fork.
Bake at 325° for 12-15 minutes.

title: chicken with goop(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Put raw chicken in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer cheese on top.
Mix soup and wine and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over chicken. Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken casserole supreme
directions: Boil chicken and remove bones.
Mix stuffing with melted butter or margarine.
Mix soups, broth and peas together.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; spread into an ungreased cake pan and mix again.
Add the remaining ingredients; pour over the cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli rice bake
directions: Heat margarine in hot skillet and cook chicken, half at a time, until browned.
Add broccoli and carrots.
Cook until tender-crisp.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cover.
Simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff before serving.
Serves 4.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Combine flour and cheese.
Make a well in the center of mixture.
Combine egg, milk and butter.
Pour into center of dry mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin pans. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Melt shortening and add to beaten eggs and water.
Sift dry ingredients and add to eggs, etc.
Add crushed bananas and vanilla.
Beat 150 strokes.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 75 minutes.

title: english toffee
directions: Need candy thermometer, heavy 3-quart pan and well-greased 12 x 16-inch cookie sheet.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix yogurt or cream well.
Add apples, grapes and celery to dressing to prevent apples from discoloring; add nuts.
Mix lightly, chill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together with your hands. Form into small balls and flatten slightly as you put them on the cookie sheet. Cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown. Can be frozen and reheated.

title: veggie pizza
directions: *Veggies should be as tiny as possible.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Combine
all
ingredients,
except potatoes, in plastic bag. Moisten
potatoes with water and shake in bag with flour mixture. Melt
margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay potatoes in pan.
Bake at
375° for 1 hour.
Turn potatoes after first 30 minutes.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, saute green pepper, onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon olive oil until tender.
Remove; set aside.
In same skillet, heat remaining oil and brown chicken on both sides; drain fat.
Return vegetables to skillet.
Add pasta sauce, olives, basil, salt, oregano and pepper.
Heat to boiling. Cover; simmer gently over low heat for 20 minutes or until chicken is thoroughly cooked.
Serve chicken and pasta topped with sauce.

title: no crust custard pie
directions: Butter a pie plate heavily.
Mix the ingredients; pour into buttered pie plate.
Bake at 375° until brown, about 1 hour.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In large pot combine soup, broth and water.
Blend Velveeta in blender with 2 or 3 cups of milk.
Add to pot with remaining milk. Add broccoli.
Simmer over low heat 30 to 45 minutes.

title: baked mackerel
directions: Place fillets in one layer in a glass or ceramic baking dish. Heat vinegar, water, onion, herbs and spices.
Pour over fish. Allow to marinate for at least one hour.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 375°.
Yield:
6 servings.
Carbohydrate 11 g, protein 39 g, fat 6 g, calories 246.

title: caramel heath bar cheese cake
directions: Mix all,
press into 9 inch spring form pan, covering bottom and one inch up sides.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: south carolina stew
directions: Heat beef in oil.
Cook until tender. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 1 hour. Serve over rice.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer cauliflower, broccoli and onion in a bowl and put mayonnaise on top.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and sit overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: susie's pork barbecue
directions: Cook pork slowly in crock-pot.
Cool and shred pork.
Cook celery and onion in water and butter.
When onions and celery are tender, add tomato sauce and ketchup.
Season with salt, pepper, oregano and garlic powder to taste.

title: coconut battered shrimp
directions: Bake coconut in a 325° oven until brown (about 10 minutes; stir several times and watch carefully).
Coarsely grind coconut. Mix spices in a large bowl with eggs; coat shrimp.
Dredge in coconut.
Transfer to
greased baking sheets and refrigerate 1 hour to 1 day.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 12 minutes.
Serve with Mango Chutney Sauce.

title: philadelphia cream cheese cake
directions: All ingredients should be at room temperature.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, flour and eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add heavy cream.
Grease a spring cake pan; dust with graham cracker crumbs.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 200° and bake until done.
A total of 1 hour.

title: creamy baked cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar; pat firmly on bottom of buttered 9-inch spring-form pan.
In larger mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Beat in Eagle Brand milk, eggs and salt until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon; pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool to room temperature; chill.
Spread sour cream on cheese cake.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: golden harvest corn casserole
directions: Mix
all ingredients together and put into well-greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper.
Drain well.
Add soups, enchilada sauce and enchilada dry mix and cook over medium heat for 15 minutes.
Keep stirred well.
Pour over crushed Doritos and add cheese.

title: stuffed jalapeno peppers
directions: Combine cheeses, bacon and seasonings; mix well. Spoon about 2 tablespoons into each pepper half. Roll in bread crumbs. Place on a greased jelly roll pan and bake uncovered at 300° for 20 minutes for spicy flavor, 30 minutes for medium and 40 minutes for mild. Serve with sour cream, onion dip or Ranch dressing. Makes 24 appetizers.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In heavy pot, mix sugar into evaporated milk.
Once this is done, start cooking the mixture on medium heat, while stirring almost constantly.
Bring the mixture to a boil and cook to a soft ball stage.
If you have a candy thermometer, you can use it to denote when the mixture gets to this stage.
If you don't have one, you can test a drop of the mixture in a small amount of ice water placed into a small bowl.
Continue to test the mixture at one to two minute intervals until you can
form a soft ball with the mixture when rolled into a ball in the ice water by hand.

title: butter beans and rice
directions: Fry bacon, mix with beans and two cups of water.
Cook for thirty minutes.
Add rice and cook until done.

title: 10 minute supper
directions: In large pot, combine both packages of noodles in boiling water.
Boil 7 to 10 minutes.

title: gourmet golden squash
directions: Prepare and boil cubed squash until tender.
Heat oven to 400°.
Mash squash.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn mixture into ungreased 1-quart casserole. Bake uncovered 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon, soda and
salt
together
and set aside. Mix oil, sugar, pumpkin and
egg.
Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Add 1 cup butterscotch
chips and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake in greased and
floured
(jelly roll type) cookie sheet
at 350° for 12 to
minutes.
Sprinkle
with powdered sugar.
Cut while warm.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Drain pineapple, fruit cocktail and oranges.
Reserve 3 cups juice.
Drain and rinse cherries.
Mix together pudding and fruit juice.
Bring to a boil.
Let cool and mix with fruit.
If desired you can layer fruit with angel food cake and pour pudding mixture over it.

title: seafood macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water, drain and cool.
In a large bowl combine macaroni, shrimp, crabmeat, celery, onion and chopped eggs; set aside.

title: sweet and sour glazed ham
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Set aside.
Slice away skin from ham.
Score fat on ham in a diamond design and stud with whole cloves.
Place ham, fat side up, on rack in a shallow roasting pan. Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Baste every 15 to 20 minutes with sauce.
Heat remaining sauce and serve with ham. Garnish with parsley.

title: butterfly pork chops
directions: Brown the chops in lard or drippings in frying pan.
Pour off drippings.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add water; cover tightly and simmer for 45 minutes or 1 hour, or until done.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: husband pleasin' baked beans
directions: Brown beef.
In a separate skillet, saute onions in margarine until beginning to brown.
Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, salt and milk.
Line a rather small pie pan with dough.
Fill pan with mixture.
Sprinkle nutmeg over the top.
Bake in moderate oven.
Test with knife.

title: mom's cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°; melt margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a saucepan, heat sugar and water until it is dissolved. Cut Crisco into flour until fine crumbles; add milk and stir with fork until dough leaves side of bowl.
Turn onto floured counter; make into a ball.
Flatten and roll out until 1/4-inch thick. Sprinkle with cinnamon; add pears or apples.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Now slice up in circles about 15 of them.
Place in the buttered casserole.
Pour the sugar water over the dough.
(This looks like too much liquid, but the dough will absorb the liquid.) Bake about 50 minutes.
You can use dewberries, peaches or other fruit.
Serves 12 to 13.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt butter and mix with brown sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each one.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in long pan for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: cooked broccoli
directions: Go with Grandmama to the garden.
Pick just the broccoli that is real green but not the ones that have little flowers on them. Bring home and wash; make sure there are no little bugs on it. Put water and a little salt in a boiler.
When the water has little bubbles, put the broccoli in it.
Cook it until it's done, then eat it just like it is or you can put cheese sauce on it.

title: lumberjack cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add and beat molasses and eggs in.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and ginger together and mix in.
Chill.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Wash lettuce and cut in 1/4-inch strips.
Drain.
Then add shallots, onion, shrimp, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Add mayonnaise and stir all together.
Put in refrigerator for a couple of hours before serving.
The longer it sets the more flavorful it becomes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into large 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sensational sweet potato cake
directions: Beat all ingredients at low speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Pour into three 9 inch round cake pans coated with vegetable cooking spray and dusted with flour.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire racks 10 minutes; remove from pans onto wax paper and cool on wire racks.
Spread cream cheese frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine the cake mix, eggs, vegetable oil, pudding mix, milk and sour cream; mix well.
Fold in the chocolate chips and nuts. Bake at 350° in a greased and floured pan for approximately 45 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Mix some of the Hershey's syrup in with the cream cheese frosting; spread over the cake when completely cooled.

title: potato spinach casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except cheese. Spoon in greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes. Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Bring to a boil and seal hot.
Yields 9 pints.

title: gramma's hot cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake on preheated griddle, turning once.
Serve with heated syrup.
Tried and true.
Very good with children and grandchildren.

title: neiman-marcus tuna-pecan salad with water chestnuts
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well to evenly distribute and coat well with mayonnaise.
Adjust seasoning to taste.
If salad is dry, add a bit more mayonnaise.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: Mix together all ingredients except the broccoli.
Let stand 1 hour, then fry in a wok in small amount of oil.
In another wok, stir-fry the broccoli in a small amount of salt water.
Cook until tender.
Drain and add to the meat mixture.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: pepper steak
directions: Preheat oil in heavy skillet.
Prepare meat with seasonings. Press fresh cracked black pepper on one side.
Cook, pepper side down.
When meat is cooked to preference, drain grease.
Add margarine to meat and continue cooking.
Saute shallots with meat for approximately 1 minute.
Add parsley.
Add brandy and flame for a few seconds.
Remove meat.
Add gravy mix and stir.
Add half and half.
Cook until thick.
Pour over meat.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream softened butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add alternately flour and egg (1 cup flour/3 eggs) until all flour and eggs are used.
Bake in prepared tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
This makes a very large cake.

title: "last-of-the-turkey" soup
directions: Remove meat from carcass of turkey and set aside in refrigerator.
Crack bones of turkey carcass and place in kettle. Cover with water.
Add skin and seasonings.
Simmer 2 hours. Chill.
Skim off fat and remove bones, skin and bay leaf.
Add the turkey meat, celery, carrot and onion.
Simmer until vegetables are desired consistency.
Add salt to taste.

title: fruity tea
directions: In medium saucepan, pour water over tea bags. Brew 4 minutes. Remove tea bags and stir in sugar and juices. Heat. Serve in mugs.

title: sour cream pancakes
directions: Must follow directions closely!
Make sure you are home alone. Get in car and start your engine.
Look around to make sure none of the neighbors see you leave.
Drive to town.
Ease into Kentucky Fried Chicken drive thru and order enough food to feed the family.
Hurry home before anyone gets there and set the table.
Now, be sure you mess your hair a little and be sure to put a little flour on your face and look tired!!
Very important, be sure to destroy all evidence of the Kentucky Fried Chicken containers.
Now you are ready to feed the family when they get there.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Unroll crescent rolls.
Keep 2 triangles together to form a rectangle.
Lay rectangle on counter or wax paper.
Flatten it some with your hands or a rolling pin.
Sprinkle tidbits of uncooked sausage and cheese to cover dough.
Roll up dough longways to form a long roll.
Pinch together dough so it will stay rolled up.
Put in wax paper and freeze 30 to 45 minutes. Remove from freezer and slice to make pinwheels.
Cook on a cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes great holiday pick-ups!

title: million dollar cupcakes
directions: In small saucepan, melt chocolate and margarine on low heat. Add pecans and stir until well coated.
Blend sugar, flour and eggs on low speed of electric mixer.
(Do not beat.)
Stir in chocolate and pecan mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
(Do not beat.) Place paper baking cups in muffin tins and completely fill with batter.
Bake in a 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 8 to 10 minutes in muffin tins before removing.
Makes 14 to 16 cupcakes.

title: ore-ida tater tot casserole
directions: In skillet, cook onions and meat; drain off fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in soup and place in greased shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Top with single layer of frozen Tater Tots. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 5 large servings.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons of sugar. Pat into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Beat the margarine and brown sugar until fluffy. Sift together flour, soda and salt. Stir into butter mixture.
Add oats and blend thoroughly.
Press 2/3 over bottom of greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix jam and lemon rind.
Spread evenly over bottom crust. Sprinkle with remaining 1/3 crumb mixture.
Pat lightly onto jam filling.
