Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with sugar. Mix flour and salt together. Add yeast mixture with flour mixture. Knead for 10 minutes. Divide into 16 pieces and roll 10 to 12-inches.
Place on foil lined cookie sheet.
Brush with egg yolk and water. Sprinkle with salt. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until browned.

title: frozen punch
directions: Combine sugar and water; bring to a boil.
Stir until the sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Combine with remaining ingredients (except ginger ale).
Freeze.

title: texas cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer in order given: cherry pie filling, pineapple with juice, yellow cake mix, chopped pecans and coconut.
Pour 1 stick melted oleo over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (do not preheat oven).

title: buttercream icing
directions: Cream butter and shortening in large bowl using electric mixer. Add vanilla and salt. Gradually add sugar, one cup at a time, beating well at medium speed after each addition. Scrape bottom and sides of bowl often. After all sugar has been added, icing will appear dry. Add milk and beat at high speed until light and fluffy. Keep icing covered with damp cloth until ready to decorate. Keep icing bowl in the refrigerator when not in use. Yields 4 cups icing.

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Lightly grease a large, flat casserole dish.
Spread well- drained green beans in a dish.
Mix soup and sour cream together. Spread evenly over beans.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Layer sliced cheese on top.
Top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until crackers lightly brown and cheese bubbles.

title: chocolate chip picnic bars
directions: Combine sugar and oil.
Add beaten eggs.
Beat until smooth. Sift together twice the flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into first mixture.
Add chocolate chips, raisins, oatmeal and nuts. Mix well.
Spread evenly in greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into 30 bars.

title: german apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 305°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch square pan. Combine butter, sugar and eggs in large bowl and beat thoroughly. Add flour, baking powder and vanilla and beat until well blended. Spread evenly in pan.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Peel and core apples and thinly slice into large bowl.
Add sugar-cinnamon mixture to taste, coating apples thoroughly.
Arrange slices on top of batter in overlapping rows, pressing lightly into batter. Bake 1 hour.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: colorado filling for croissants
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill overnight.
Chop vegetables and meat finer and put on dinner rolls instead of croissants if you wish.
Also, green olives may be substituted for the red pepper.
Sam's Wholesale Warehouse in Omaha has miniature croissants that work great for these.

title: creamy cake dessert
directions: Bake Jiffy cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan according to box directions.
Let cool.

title: striped delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix the flour, margarine and nuts. Cut together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: french toast with maple-pecan butter
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Let bread rest overnight and get stale. In a large bowl, whisk ingredients, except clarified butter. Place egg mixture in a flat pan and add bread slices.
Let bread soak up mixture, turning once.
Heat a 10-inch saute pan over moderate heat and add clarified butter.
Place 4 slices of bread, slightly overlapping, in pan.
Spread Apple Compote (recipe follows) over bread and add remaining pieces.
Press down lightly. Cook one minute, then flip.
Place in oven and bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove and serve.

title: the big cheese dip
directions: Combine ingredients and add dashes of Tabasco to suit (not too many).

title: gina's chocolate balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together; form into balls.
Chill.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Slice tomatoes thin. Bring to a boil with juice of lemon and 4 tablespoons water. Simmer until translucent. Add 4 tablespoons cornstarch, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: chiffon cake
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
In another bowl, mix all other ingredients, then fold into egg white mixture very gently.
Place mixture into ungreased angel food pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When done, invert pan on funnel until cool.
Very good with canned fruit or berries and whipped cream.

title: our family's apple crisp(servings:  8)
directions: Sprinkle apples with white sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon. Dot with butter.
Stir egg into dry ingredients and put on apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: fruit-pudding and cheese
directions: Mix the cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill pan.

title: creamy ham and cheese
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Combine milk, cream cheese, garlic and salt in pot over medium-low heat until cheese is dissolved.
Saute onions and peppers.
Mix together noodles, ham and sauce; layer in casserole dish with Parmesan cheese on top of each layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Mix together in large bowl, sugar, salt, shortening and hot potato water with potatoes.
Cool.
Add yeast dissolved in 1 cup warm water.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Add enough flour until the consistency of biscuit dough.
Grease top.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Make rolls 2 hours before baking.
Let rise and bake at 400°.
Brush with butter or margarine.
Dough will keep for several days in refrigerator.

title: green rice
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in a 325° oven.
Use a shallow pan.

title: broccoli-onion deluxe
directions: Slit fresh broccoli spears lengthwise; cut into 1-inch pieces. Cook in boiling salt water until tender or cook frozen broccoli according to package.
Drain.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti as directed.
Mix sauce, cottage cheese, oregano, 1/4 cup Mozzarella cheese and ziti.
Place in greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: savory sauerkraut
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: can't fail divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and salt until hard ball forms in cold water.
Place Creme in mixing bowl.
Stir in hot syrup.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: fruit bowl supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill about 1 hour. Serve as a dessert.
Makes 6 cups or 12 servings.

title: jellied chicken salad
directions: Dissolve softened gelatin in chicken broth.
Add other ingredients.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in pineapple, chicken, chopped celery, chopped green pepper and chopped pimiento.
Pour into 6 1/2-cup ring mold.
Chill until firm. Unmold on lettuce leaves.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed.
Mix well and bake in a 400° oven about 40 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: artichoke pie
directions: Saute garlic in oil in a large pan.
Add artichokes and brown. Transfer to mixing bowl and stir in eggs, cheese, Mozzarella, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into pie pan.
Cover with top crust.
Press edges of crust together.
Makes holes in top of crust.
Brush egg yolk on top crust.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake until golden brown, 30 minutes.

title: nacho cheese tacos
directions: Cook beef with onion; drain.
Add chili powder and 1/2 cup soup.
Stir occasionally.
In a 1-quart saucepan over low heat, heat remaining soup until hot.
Spoon about 1/4 meat mixture into each shell.
Spoon soup over each.
Top with lettuce and tomatoes. Serves four.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Break up angel food cake, line pan or layer it.
Mix vanilla pudding, milk and Cool Whip; pour over cake.
Then mix boiling water in strawberry jello and pour in package of frozen strawberries.
Let cool.
Pour this over cake mixture.

title: taco dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread over a cookie sheet.
Layer beans over cream cheese.
Sprinkle taco seasoning mix on next. Garnish with shredded lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Dot sour cream on top and put black olives on top.
Use with taco chips to serve dip.

title: three hole chocolate cake
directions: Put dry ingredients in sifter and sift into ungreased 10 x 7-inch pan.
Make 3 holes and in first hole, pour in oil; in next hole, pour in vinegar and in third hole, pour in vanilla.
Pour cold water over all.
Stir completely with fork.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fresh beet pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, water, sugar, spices, and salt. Simmer 10 minutes. Add beets. Simmer 15 - 20 minutesor until beets are tender - don't over cook. Put in desired containers and seal.

title: warm german potato salad
directions: Place cubed potatoes into bowl.
Add onion, bacon, salt and pepper, oil, vinegar and water.
Add cucumbers, if using.
Mix well.
Serve warm.

title: brie with brown sugar and almonds
directions: Place first three ingredients in saucepan on medium heat until melted and mixed well.
(Use half of almonds.)
Place half of crescent roll dough on cookie sheet.
Skin Brie cheese and place on dough.
(You can break up Brie and spread evenly on dough.) Sprinkle 1/2 cup of less of almonds on cheese.
Place other half of dough on top and press edges together.
(Make sure all holes and edges are sealed!)
Pour first mixture on top of prepared pastry and bake according to directions on crescent roll can or until golden brown.
Serve with sliced apples and grapes or whatever fruit you desire!

title: peppernuts(christmas cookie)
directions: Mix together sugar, shortening, sour cream and corn syrup. Add dry ingredients for stiff dough, using more or less flour; you may have to use your hands.
Mix in crushed anise seed.
Wrap dough in waxed paper and chill a few days.
On floured surface, roll small handful of dough into a snake-like strand, the thickness of a husky pencil.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes; watch very closely, bottoms burn easily.

title: cheese 'n chili rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Saute onion in butter and remove from heat.
Stir in hot rice, sour cream, cottage cheese, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly to mix well.
Layer half the rice mixture in bottom; then spread chilies over that layer, then 1/2 the grated cheese.
Layer other half of rice and top with remaining cheese.
Bake 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift and add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and vanilla.
Add mashed blueberries, then fold in additional blueberries.
Grease a 12 muffin tin. Divide batter into tin.
Sprinkle tops with additional sugar, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan delights(turtles)
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt. Cook over medium heat until all sugar is dissolved. Gradually add milk and mix well. Continue cooking until candy thermometer reads 248° (firm ball stage). Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla until blended.
Fold in pecans. Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Chill until firm.
Melt chocolate chips and shortening in microwave bowl.
Drizzle over each cluster. Cool.

title: sweet onion bake
directions: Saute the onions in the butter.
Cook the rice in the boiling water for 5 minutes; drain and mix with onions.
Add the cheese and the half & half.
Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: healthy muffins
directions: Mix oat bran, oatmeal and baking powder together.
Stir in olive oil, egg whites, skim milk and brown sugar.
Mix together. Add bananas and raisins.
Mix together.
Grease muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Crumble 1/2 cake in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cream margarine, add egg yolks and powdered sugar; mix well.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread 1/2 mixture on top of cake.
Crumble 3 candy bars on top.
Repeat procedure using remaining cake,
creamed mixture and candy bars.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: orange glazed carrots(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart casserole combine juice, honey, butter, lemon peel, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in cornstarch; mix until well blended.
Stir in carrots.
Cover with a lid.
Cook on High for 8 to 10 minutes.
Stor once.
Stir.
Let stand, covered, for 3 minutes before serving.

title: salmon salad sandwiches
directions: In small bowl, combine salmon, cucumber, mayonnaise and French dressing; blend well.
Spread margarine on cut sides of buns. Place 1/4 cup salmon mixture on each bottom half of each bun.
Top each with 2 spinach leaves and top with bun.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: sheet cake brownies
directions: Put in a large bowl the flour and sugar.
Bring to a boil the margarine, water and cocoa.
Pour flour mixture and mix well.
Add eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 12 x 16-inch pan (jelly roll pan).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Pour frosting over hot cake.

title: rich corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except margarine.
Melt margarine in black skillet, coating sides and bottom.
Pour off excess butter and save.
Pour batter into skillet and top with excess butter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cone treats
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake according to package directions in large bowl.
Fill cones 3/4 full of cake mix and place in large muffin tins.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
When cool, frost and decorate with sprinkles or toppings of your choice.
Great for children's parties!

title: pound cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour and extract and beat 2 minutes.
Pour in greased tube pan and bake approximately 1 hour at 325°.

title: tossed green salad
directions: Break up cauliflower and broccoli in small pieces.
Slice red and green peppers in rings; also Bermuda onion and tomatoes in rings.
Break up lettuce in small pieces; drain chickpeas and add to salad.
Garnish with pimento.
Add salad dressing desired and toss.
Sprinkle croutons on top.

title: caroline's snacks
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oil, in a large bowl.
Add a small amount of oil and stir; cover bowl.
Every 30 to 45 minutes, add more oil and stir from bottom of bowl.
This process is supposed to take a couple of hours.
Place in covered containers, no need to refrigerate.

title: "secret sauce" for barbecue
directions: Blend together and use as a universal barbecue sauce prior to grilling any barbecue item.
Great flavor!

title: apricot-angel dessert
directions: Cook nectar, sugar and cornstarch until thickened; cool. Spread over torn pieces of angel food in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Cool Whip; refrigerate.
Garnish with sliced almonds.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine brown sugar, Crisco, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended. Beat in egg.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add gradually to creamed mixture at low speed.
Beat until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoon, 3-inches apart, onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hunter sauce
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add mushrooms, salt and pepper. Saute briefly.
Add chopped shallots and dry white wine.
Mix together.
Cook over low heat until wine is reduced by half, about 10 minutes.
Mix together beef stock and cornstarch.
Add to skillet with tomato sauce, parsley and tarragon.
Simmer uncovered until it bubbles slightly.
Serve with venison or other game.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Mix well.
Add melted butter.
Add remaining ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skins until tender.
Peel while hot and allow to cool only enough to slice about 1/8-inch thick.
Add oil, salt, pepper, onion and vinegar.
Pour hot beef stock over potatoes.
Mix gently together in order to not break up potatoes. Let set at room temperature for at least 1 hour.
Mix again just before serving.
Garnish with chopped green onion tops.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, cocoa and milk in a pot.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and oats.
Drop on wax paper or put in a pan and cut.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast in 2 cups warm water.
Cream oleo and sugar together in a large bowl.
Add egg and cream a little more.
Add yeast and water mixture.
Stir and add flour.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Place in airtight bowl and keep in refrigerator. To cook, drop by spoonfuls into well-greased muffin pan and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until well browned.
Will keep in refrigerator about 1 week.
They go from refrigerator to oven. Don't have to be left out to rise.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix cocoa, margarine and boiling water.
Mix rest of dry ingredients; add to cocoa mixture.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add buttermilk and vanilla; beat again.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 40 cupcakes; bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pecan crunch cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and vanilla. Add chips and pecans. Stir in flour. Form into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press balls flat with bottom of glass dipped in sugar. Decorate with pecan half. Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into an 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Make 3 small wells into flour, then add remaining ingredients and mix in pan. Don't attempt to get all lumps out.
Do not grease or flour pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: harvest salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in well-sealed container in refrigerator, turning upside-down every so often so dressing can mix with vegetables.
Serve cold.
(Best if made a day ahead of time.)

title: stove-top beans
directions: Add beans to boiling water.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, cover and soak 1 hour or overnight in refrigerator.
Add salt. Bring beans to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and boil gently until tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Drain.
Save 1 cup bean cooking liquid. Mix with beans and remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and boil gently 30 minutes.
Continue cooking, uncovered, until sauce is of desired consistency, about 10 minutes.
Serve half of the beans and refrigerate remaining 2 cups for use at another meal within 3 to 4 days.

title: sugar-free chocolate fudge
directions: In a small mixing bowl, blend cream cheese, chocolate, sweetener and vanilla until smooth, then add the nuts.

title: yellow cake with cinnamon mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: oriental stir-fry
directions: Cut up chicken breasts into bite size chunks.
In a large skillet or an electric wok, over medium-high heat, heat up cooking oil.
Add chicken, pressed garlic and onion salt.
Stir regularly until chicken takes on a light color.
Once chicken has a little bit of golden brown on surface, add Chinese Five Spice.
Add in water chestnuts, bamboo shoots and chickpeas; turn down to medium heat.
Cover skillet or wok and allow to cook for about 10 minutes; stir regularly as it may stick.
Add a little more oil if necessary.
Add bean sprouts; cook about 5 more minutes.
Season with soy sauce, as desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In vegetable oil, warm each corn tortilla so they are soft and leave aside.
Mix all other ingredients with 1/2 of the grated cheese.
Spoon into shells and fold, then place in cake pan with folded side down.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and heat in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Fills 2 cake pans or 1 large pan.

title: marinated mushroom salad
directions: Thoroughly combine oil, vinegar, onion, salt, sugar, black pepper and dry mustard in large bowl.
Rinse and slice thin the mushrooms and add to marinade.
Toss to coat.
Slice cauliflower flowerets.
Slice celery.
Cut the green pepper in strips.
Add all to mushrooms and let marinate at least 1 hour.
Just before serving halve the cherry tomatoes and add.

title: cherry supreme dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple with juice in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon cherry filling on the top.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over and spread pecans and coconut on top.
Dot with oleo.
Do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cream cheese mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve juice.
Add water to juice to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl, 2 minutes.
Stir into measured liquid.
Pour 2 cups of the gelatin into medium bowl.
Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in pineapple.
Spoon into 5-cup ring mold.
Refrigerate about 2 hours or until set, but not firm (should stick to finger when touched and should move to side when mold is tilted).
Stir remaining 1 cup gelatin gradually into cream cheese in small bowl until smooth. Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours or until thickened.
Stir in walnuts. Spoon into mold.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.

title: chocolate meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Add sugar. Mix in pecans and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonful on well greased cookie sheet.
Turn off oven. Place meringues in oven.	Let stay there overnight.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Rinse chicken breasts with cold water and pat dry.
Dip in sour cream.
Add garlic powder to bread crumbs and dip chicken breasts in bread crumbs.
As an option, add Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce to sour cream.
Place chicken on a rack and broil for 5 minutes on each side.

title: hamburger-macaroni casserole
directions: Boil hamburger meat in 4 cups water until meat is done.
Skim top of broth.
Add elbow macaroni and salt; cook until tender. Drain meat and macaroni.
Add cheese cubes and stir until melted. Serves 6.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Bake chicken or turkey in a preheated oven at 325° about 3 hours or the time listed under poultry.
Boil the neck and liver in a separate boiler for stock.
Combine minced onion, chopped celery, cornbread crumbs, saltine cracker crumbs, salt and pepper in large mixing bowl.
Pour in the stock.
Mix well.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: lola elizabeth gilpen schoppert's panhauss
directions: Take skin off liver pudding and cut up into pan.
Add salt and pepper.
Add 3 cups water; stir well.
Cook until boiling, mashing lumps up, then simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add 1 cup water to the cornmeal.
Mix well.
With the heat as low as possible, add to pudding mixture.
If it needs more cornmeal, add, then stir well and beat.
It should be thick enough to just barely pour.
Pour into a loaf dish.
Let cool.
Cover and put in refrigerator.
When ready to use (after it sets awhile, I like to leave it overnight), slice (thinner slices about 1/4-inch or less), fry in buttered iron skillet until well browned on both sides, turning once.
Serve with maple syrup poured on top like pancakes.

title: mom's homemade dressing
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and flour; stir good. Add water and vinegar. Cook over low heat stirring all the time. It will get thick and bubbles will appear. Cool and it will keep for months in the refrigerator.

title: strawberry lust
directions: Soften margarine.
Blend with flour and 2 tablespoons sugar. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: favorite rice
directions: Heat oven on its lowest setting.
Combine beans, onion, garlic and water in a large, lidded, ovenproof casserole and place in oven.
Do not add salt.
Cook in slow oven overnight or all day 6 to 10 hours.
Check liquid after 6 or 7 hours and add more if necessary.
When beans are tender and liquid is thick and soupy, add salt to taste and stir in cooked brown rice and some pepper.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Wash cranberries and crush in blender.
In mixing bowl, add sugar to berries and let stand 15 minutes.
Add pineapple.
Heat orange juice and add jello.
Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.
This is delicious!

title: german drop dumplings
directions: Mix milk, egg, baking powder and salt together.
Add sifted flour to make extra thick batter.
Drop by teaspoon into boiling chicken broth.
If more dumplings are desired, start out with 1 cup of milk and add same amount of other ingredients.

title: fried onions
directions: Slice as many onions as desired for a meal in a dish of milk. Separate rings and drain for 1/2 hour.
Lay on waxed paper, season with salt and pepper and cover with shortening.
Fry as you would potatoes, watching to prevent burning.
Turn carefully.

title: southwestern pasta
directions: Cut chicken into strips or small chunks.
Coat well with taco seasoning mix.
Saute in olive oil, add peppers and onions and cook all together, season with salt, pepper, chili powder.
Cook pasta and drain.
Mix pasta and chicken, peppers, onion, etc. Serve in pasta bowl.
Top pasta mixture with sour cream, salsa, and grated cheese.

title: goulash soup
directions: Melt shortening or oil in Dutch oven.
Put in meat and fry until it starts to brown.
Add onion.
Cook until golden.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add 2 quarts of water, bay leaf and cinnamon.
Cook for 45 minutes, covered.
Then add the tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover.
Cook 30 minutes more.

title: brown sugar icing
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until bubbly.
Remove from heat. Stir in confectioners sugar.
Beat until consistency desired and spread on cake before it hardens.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Dot with butter and sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Remove.
Top with cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix together.
Put into buttered pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Prepare bread crumbs and onions.
Heat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl beat eggs.
Mix in chopped meat, crumbs and onion.
Add horseradish, salt, mustard and milk; combine.
Put meat loaf in a shallow pan.
Add quartered potatoes and onions and pour tomato soup over it.
Bake for 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Stir together 1 slightly beaten egg, pumpkin, 1/3 cup sugar and pie spices. Spread over bottom of pie shell. Beat 2 eggs; add 1/2 cup sugar, white Karo, oleo and vanilla. Fold in nuts. Spoon over pumpkin mixture. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Serve with whipped cream.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar, beat well.
Add eggs.
Sift flour and spices with baking soda and salt.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add carrots, a little at a time, and mix.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes until center is done.

title: ham rotel
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes longer.

title: baked white potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake 4 large oblong potatoes until done (do not grease skins).
Cut in halves lengthwise and scoop out baked potato, reserving shell.
Add salt, butter, milk, pepper and grated onion.
Mash thoroughly.
Spoon into shells, sprinkle with grated sharp cheese and paprika.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°. Serve hot.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Peel and slice peaches. adding 1/2 teaspoon Fruit Fresh or 1 teaspoon lemon juice.
Measure 2/3 cup of peaches and mash in 1-quart measure.
Add water and 3/4 to 1 cup sugar, depending on sweetness of peaches.
Microwave 5 to 6 minutes on High, or until mixture thickens, stirring once.
Stir in butter.
Cool.
Fill baked pie shell with remaining peaches.
Pour cooled glaze over top.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Lacerate flank steak across the grain of the meat, both sides.
Marinate for 1 day, turning occasionally.
Broil 5 minutes on both sides.

title: six layer mexican dip
directions: Mash avocados and add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Spread bean dip in a large, shallow dish.
Spread avocado mixture on top of bean dip.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning together, spread over avocado mixture.
Top with green onions, tomatoes and cheese (in that order).
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil thighs in water seasoned with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
After chicken is done, use the broth to cook rice according to package directions. Chop up chicken.
When rice is done, add soups and a can of broth. Add chicken and mix well. Pour into 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: tuna pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F.
In a bowl, mix the tuna, soup, vegetables and seasoning together.
Dump the whole mixture into a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish and top with pieces of the biscuit dough.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Use on a fruit tray to dip fruit into such as strawberries, grapes, bananas, fresh peaches, apple slices, etc.

title: baked turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 475°, very hot, about 9 or 10 p.m. the night before you are planning your meal.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Freeze beef bottom round or top round.
Put in refrigerator overnight and slice in the morning.
Dredge with flour.
Brown in oleo; add minced onion, mushrooms and hot water with beef bouillon.
Let simmer until tender, about 1 hour.
Add sour cream.

title: double lemon cake
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients and beat for 4 minutes. Spray Bundt pan with cooking spray and sprinkle with granulated sugar. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes and turn out onto plate. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar or glaze.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Wash, drain and stem berries.
Crush 2 cups of berries and combine with water, sugar and cornstarch.
Bring to boiling point and simmer about 2 minutes or until clear.
Add butter and enough red food coloring to give good color.
Fill baked and cooled pie shell with cooled berry mixture.
Cover with remaining sliced berries.
Chill. Top with cream before serving.

title: linguine with salmon and mushrooms
directions: Heat oil in heavy, large skillet over medium-high heat. Season salmon with salt and pepper.
Saute in skillet until just cooked through, about 3 minutes.
Using slotted spoon, transfer salmon to plate.
Add garlic to same skillet; saute 30 seconds. Add mushrooms; saute 2 minutes.
Add green onions, tomato, wine and capers; cook until mushrooms are tender, about 5 minutes.
Add linguine, dill, lemon juice and salmon and toss.
Serve with salt and pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions together.
Drain.
Layer in casserole one layer of Tater Tots and cheese.
Repeat.
(Cheese should be the top layer.)
Pour cream of mushroom soup over mixture.
Bake about 1 hour at 350° or until golden brown.

title: chiffon pumpkin pie(diabetic)
directions: Mix gelatine, Sweet 'N Low, salt and spices in top of double boiler or nonstick pan.
Beat 3 egg yolks and milk together.
Add to the pumpkin and gelatine mixture.
Cook over boiling water or nonstick pan, 10 minutes.
Cool and chill until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add 1/2 cup sugar gradually, then fold into the cold pumpkin mixture.
I did not use Sweet 'N Low in the egg whites.
Pour into cool pie shell, graham cracker is good.
Refrigerate and serve with lite Cool Whip.

title: hamburger-corn bake
directions: Cook noodles until done; drain.
In a large skillet, brown hamburger and onion; drain off fat.
Stir in soup, corn, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in cooked noodles. Put mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Toss bread crumbs with melted butter on top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, about 50 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Soak bread cubes in milk.
Add ground beef, onion, Worcestershire sauce, catsup, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Shape into small meatballs.
Place in baking pan.

title: tuna salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together the mayonnaise, lemon juice, cucumber, red and green onions, celery dill, salt and pepper. Add the tuna and toss to coat. Serve with slices of Rustice whole wheat round bread.

title: cake brownies
directions: Combine about half of the flour, brown sugar, peanut butter, shortening, egg, milk, vanilla and baking soda.
Beat with an electric mixer on medium to high speed until thoroughly combined. Beat in remaining flour.
Stir in oats.
Spread batter into an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 18 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack.
Frost with Peanut-Butter Frosting.
Cut into bars.
Makes 20.

title: pronto mild chili
directions: Over medium heat, brown ground beef in large pan; drain. Return to heat and add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Cover pan with lid and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: jiffy devil's food cake
directions: Put all ingredients into a bowl.
Beat with mixer at low speed for a few minutes, then at high speed.
Mix good and pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple; save the juice.

Heat 1 cup of the juice to boiling; add to jello in a large pretty bowl and stir making sure that all of the jello is dissolved. Heat coke and add 1 cup cold water; add to jello. Refrigerate and let partially thicken.

Cut cherries in half and add to pineapple, set aside. Add a small amount of partially set jello to the cream cheese in a small bowl and stir; keep adding jello until cream cheese is almost a liquid; add it to jello and mix well.
Add cherries, pineapple and pecans; mix well and chill until firm.

title: lollipops
directions: Line 2 cookie sheets with foil.
Lightly grease.
Arrange lollipop sticks (15) or oiled cookie cutters about 4 inches apart. Put first 3 ingredients in 2-quart microwave bowl.
Put in microwave, uncovered, on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes until margarine melts.
Stir in flavoring and color.
Microwave on High 5 to 5 1/2 minutes until candy thermometer registers 270° to 290° or a small amount of syrup dropped into cold water separates into threads that are hard.
For round lollipops, drop 1 tablespoon syrup over end of stick.
Let cool completely.
For shaped lollipops pour into cookie cutters.

title: old fashioned chocolate pie
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients, stirring constantly until thick. Add butter, salt and vanilla; stir well. Pour into pastry shell. Top with meringue and bake until golden brown.

title: thanksgiving bread
directions: Cover apricots with hot boiling water 15 minutes and drain. Mix fruit and nuts.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add brown sugar and blend well.
Add egg and milk, then syrup.
Stir all well.
Put into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Combine water, onion, salt, lemon juice and celery in kettle and bring to boil.
Boil for four minutes.
Add fish and bay leaf; boil for 3 minutes.
Remove fish.
Brush with melted butter (garlic); sprinkle with paprika.
Broil for 2 minutes on cookie sheets.
Serve with melted butter.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions with margarine in skillet for 15 or 20 minutes over medium heat.
Place 1/2 the onions in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with 1/2 the crackers and 1/2 the Parmesan cheese. Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: meat filled jumbo shells
directions: Cook shells according to package directions. Drain and cool in single layer on wax paper. Brown beef and pork in skillet. Drain. Combine meat, eggs, bread crumbs, Mozzarella cheese, onions, oregano, salt and pepper. Fill each shell with approximately 2 tablespoons of meat filling. Spread a thin layer of sauce on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Place shells, open side down, in single layer in the pan. Cover with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Fills about 36 shells. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: broccoli and cheese sauce
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Put in casserole dish with a little milk at bottom of dish.
Slice cheese thin and put over broccoli.
Heat some butter in a skillet and soak cracker crumbs. Sprinkle crumbs over top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy vegetable cheese soup
directions: Simmer bouillon cubes, water, celery and onion in large pot until celery is tender, about 20 minutes.
Add the potatoes and bag of vegetables and simmer until tender, about 15 minutes.
Add the cans of soup and cheese.
Simmer until the cheese is melted and the soup is hot.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Fry hamburger and onion in a little Crisco until brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let simmer about 10 minutes.

title: easy dessert
directions: Beat together sugar, oil and vanilla. Add eggs, 1 at a time. Beat well after each addition. Add flour, baking powder and salt. Pour half of the batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with fruit pie filling. Pour remaining batter over filling. Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes. Serve either hot or cold with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: orange pie
directions: This is made from sour oranges.
Mix milk and egg yolks and slowly add sour orange pieces.
Beat 1 egg white until stiff. Fold into sugar and orange mixture.
Pour in baked shell.

title: chicken and asparagus casserole ole
directions: Boil the chicken breasts in seasoned water until tender. Cook, debone and tear into bite-size pieces.
Set aside.

title: bar-b-cups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown hamburger and onion. Drain.
Add barbecue sauce and brown sugar.
Press biscuits to sides of muffin tins and fill with beef mixture. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from oven and top with cheese.
